Item_Response: An Archeologist job                                                            by: Brenna Lindsey              The job of an archeologist is an exciting job but can be tricky at times as well. Archeologist have a very unique job as well, they dig up artifacts left from historical times. They also help discover artifacts that have never been found before, as well as things we know of but have no clue where to look for them at.               An archeologist has many different tools that are available to them when excavating, they have a pick and shovel most digs often start with these two items. They are used to dig into the earth, fairly close to artifacts. They also have a whisk and Dustpan these are used to brush dirt from artifacts and clear it away from the dig site. They can also use a knife the knife is used for scraping dirt away from the ground and artifacts. Wheelbarrows are also available to archeologist, a wheelbarrow moves items from one place to another place that are to fragile to carry or it can be used to carry dirt away from the excavation site.                        Archeologist also have lots of ways to use technology to help them as well. Computers can find were objects are in the ground by digitally scanning the area, computers can also tell how deep some artifacts might be berried in the ground. Computers can also tell where objects are and where to dig to find them at. Also computers can also tell an archeologist were to start digging.                                                         Archeologist also have to be very careful when working on a dig site mainly because they could skip artifacts and or break artifacts. Archeologist have to use there special tools very carefully to insure they find as much artifacts and objects they can. Archeologist also have to be very careful with what tool they use for excavating. They have to use a different tool for each different type of soil.                         Archeologist have a tough job that can be exciting, scary and fun at the same time. Many Archeologist have helped discover things of the past and things no one had ever knew existed. That's why today we can thank archeologist all over for helping us to discover some of the worlds most famous artifacts and pieces of history. We can also thank archeologist for the help they give and all the artifacts and treasures they have found for all the museums all over the world. Archeologist are a great help to the world and without them we would not have all the knowledge we have today, we would not have hardly any of the artifacts in museums or in galleries, nor would we have the knowledge on objects like dinosaurs and fossils without the help of archeologist.

Item_Response: Fort James           By: Jade L. Jones                   Most people think that Fort James was washed away by a river, but now people are finding the Fort James's secrets. The Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project has found clues that hinted that Fort James my still stand. The fort's history goes way back to 1607 when settlers started a new life and built Fort James. Most believe that Fort James was built by a river but not curtain that it was. For over 200 years people thought that the structure was washed away by a river.                         Over 100 years later a group found the exact spot the fort was built at. The giveaway for this spot was having all the floors on the ground and finding armor and guns and remains of bullets. The National Park Service (N.P.S) led a five-year study of Fort James to figure out what the land was used for. The N.P.S used a computerized system to make a map of the land. Item_Response: Digging for History Informational Performance Task      By Tyler   April 11, 2013               If there are people who think that archeologist's jobs are not important, then they are very wrong. There are very few jobs in the world that are more important than an archeologist's job. One reason an archeologist's job is so important because we would barely know anything about our past if there were no archeologists. We might be able to find little pieces of evidence, but we would still only know little bits of evidence about our past. One of the many things that we might not know about in our history if we didn't have archeologist's are what happened to George Washington as a child, because George Washington didn't write down what happened in his childhood (at least that we haven't found yet) archeologist's first had to know where George Washington grew up as a kid to find evidence of his childhood. Then they had to do lots of digging to find evidence.               An archeologist's job is very hard. One reason an archeologist's job is very hard is that when they are digging for artifacts, they can only dig tiny bits of soil at a time because the artifacts would probably be very fragile because it is from a while ago and if they dig too much soil at one time, they might accidentally break the artifact with the shovel and then we might not know a part of our past because the evidence for it happening would be broken. Another reason archeologists job is hard is because they have to use shovels that can only dig up a small part of the soil, it can sometimes take day's to dig up 25 square inches of sand! That is a very long time for that amount of soil. If I had to do that job, I would start getting very bored and frustrated because it would take forever to dig up a tiny part of soil that might not even have any artifacts in it. One other reason an archeologist's job is very hard is for the archeologist's that work in the lab. They can study one artifact for days. That is a long time to focus on one object. Again if I had that job I would start getting very frustrated.               An archeologist has to have a tremendous amount of patience if they want to do their job well. Archeologists have a shovel that can dig a lot of sand in one dig. If the archeologist did not have very much patience, then they could take that shovel out and start digging with that shovel and if they did do that, then they would probably break a lot of the evidence and the evidence can't just appear in that spot again so the evidence would be broken and we might never know about a really important part of history. Also, the archeologist's that work in the lab have to have a lot of patience because if they didn't have a lot of patience, then they could just say that they studied every little detail of the artifact even if they didn't and again we might not know about a very important part of our history. If the people who carry the artifacts that are too heavy to carry by hand don't have patience, when they start taking the heavy artifacts away, they might want to speed up the process by running to wherever they have to take it. If they run with the wheelbarrow full of artifacts, two things might happen. One thing that might happen is that the artifacts could fall out of the wheelbarrow and break. Another thing that could happen is that the archeologist could drop the wheelbarrow with the artifacts inside of it. If either of the things happen the artifacts will probably break because the artifacts are from a long time ago and are very fragile. Those are a few reasons why an archeologist has to have a lot of patience.

Item_Response: Finding Fort James & Digging up George Washington's Past       All of these sources are about the past, so if you want to go more into detail go ahead and read this report on the past. In the past things were a little different and wasn't exactly like you would think it is. Most people think the past is just something that already happened and we don't need to worry about it but really it's how our world came to be today.       In Finding Fort James it talked about how the Fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life, and most thought that James Fort was built near the river. So they were all thinking ' Oh we will get there and we will get to see that fort, and experience what it's like to have hat fort.' But really when they got there the fort wasn't there. So they thought ' Well it must of been washed away by the river.' But seriously could a river wash away a fort? I would think not just because usually a river doesn't have waves and waves would be what could have knocked it down and washed it away. But there were hints in the area that the Fort was still around so was it really around somewhere else? It made sense that it wasn't there because they probably moved the fort to a new place to protect from enemy ships. So this was important in history, did they move it? What happened to it? They couldn't just forget about this.       The first objects were found in 1861, 254 years after the fort was built, they found uncovered armor and weapons, and they also discovered floors of buildings. So if they lost weapons and armor what could have happened? Did they get attacked? Over 100 years later a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built again. What they were trying to do is relive the moment do it over again see why the fort was in that exact spot. And they were trying to see what happened to the fort, they wanted to see what caused it to fall down or leave.       In Digging up George Washington's Past like in Finding Fort James they were looking for a shelter, they were looking for where George Washington lived. No one knwe exactly where George Washington and his family lived since the actual building was long gone. Archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there, so they decided to start digging in 2003, it took over a year but after that long year of digging they finally found it. They looked at it for a long and hard time trying to figure out what kind of rooms were still there. What they found was kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. And they didn't think that that was all that was still there and so later they found the main farmhouse a couple years later. So this was all very good information in history because they found out where George Washington lived and what some of the rooms in his house were.       All of these facts that archeologists found that they needed to know for some history. As you can see shelter was also very important in history so that was something very good that acheologists found. So all these facts were how the world became today and these are things that were very long gone but we worked long and hard to find them to make our world better today.

Item_Response: Being an Archeologist is very hard work.  An Archeologist is a person that digs up bones from prehistoric animals from dinosaurs to wooly mammoths.  When they finish digging up the animals bones they ship them to a museum, and from there they put them together like a really big puzzle and put them on display in the museum.  They yous many tools to help them dig up the bones like.       Pick axe and shovel- Most digs start with these two tools.  Used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts.       Whisk and Dustpan-Used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.       Knife- Used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around artifacts.       Wheelbarrow- Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site.       Skim shovel- A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.       Trowel- Probably the most common tool in archeology. Used to scrape and cut to view the   different layers of soil.       As you can see there are many tools to help them find the artifacts.  Archeologist are very important in life  because if we didn't have them we wouldn't know as much as we do if they didn't dig them up and tell us about the bones and what animal it was.  The museums wouldn't   have as much cool dinosaur bone if there weren't any archeologists.  In conclusion, archeologists    are more important in life than we ever imagined.

In 1994, a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river, but some discoveries  in the area hinted that it might still be around.            The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fort was built near a river. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The new spot probably gave the settlers  more protectoin from enemy ships. Item_Response: An archeoligist's job is one of the most coolest jobs when it comes to history. They discover hidden secrets. They find historical objects all over Earth. They can gather in groups of 35 people. Archeoligists can find hidden objects explorers can't even find! Archeoligists are famous for finding dinosaur bones and many other historical things.           The tools they use range from pickaxes to trowels. They,if it is absolutely necessary to mine,can use a pick to mine with. If archeologists have to scrape and cut the surface,they use a trowel to do that. They also use shovels,wheelbarrows,knifes,whisks,dustpans,and skim shovels. And,if necessary,they use their hands to dig also.           Archeologists can come upon many dangers in their expeditions. There co.uld be cliffs,holes,caves,sink holes. If they are in a snowy mountain,there could be a tragic avalanch. Another danger is freezing weather. And,of course,they can come upon dangerous creatures.           If there are expert archeologists in a group,the others are lucky. Experts know how to avoid creatures like snakes. They would also know how to avoid the other dangers. They could find areas the other archeologists couldn't. Also,more secrets could be revealed. There would also be a great leader for journeys into places like caves.           When it comes to history,archeologists are the greatest. They can uncover hidden secrets. They can dig up fossils. Experts can find that stuff quickly. Archeologists have an amazing job.

Item_Response: What are do archeologists do? Archeologists study objects from the past. The article 'Finding Fort James,' talks about how archeologists found artifacts at Jamestown island. The archeologists were working on discovering the secrets of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years, people had thought that James Fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries say that the fort might still be around.         The James Fort was built in 1607. Most people believed that James Fort was built near a river. The settlers that came from England went there because it was easier to dock their ships there and the fort was located further away so it probably gave the settlers more protection from their enemies and their ships. The archeologists uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. over a 100 years later, archeologists made a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built         The National Park Service led a 5 year study to figure out how the land was used. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area. Finally, that's when they found James Fort. The archeologists found out where the walls used to be and that the fort would be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and they found out that the fort went all the way til the river. The archeologists also found cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the fort.         The article 'Digging up George Washington's Past,' is about archeologists working at George Washington's house. George Washington's home is also known as Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years. It's not surprising that George Washington's father, Augustine Washington, moved his family there. Nobody exactly knew where George Washington's home was located since the real building was gone. Still archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there. They started digging in 2003, and it took over a year but they finally found it. The first buildings they found were the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. They also found the main farmhouse a few years later. There were at least 4 houses that had been built on the Ferry Farm land so they need to find concrete proof that that was George Washington's farmhouse.        The archeologists found out that the Washington's had a fire in their house. The diggers found pieces of burnt pottery and they also found part of a clay pipe. The archeologists knew that George Washington smoked clay pipes, so this gives more proof that that was the right house.         These are the kind of jobs archeologists do. They find nearly 1 million objects each year. For example, pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children. Objects from the past helps us understand how people lived in the past. It is more than exciting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago. It also ties us to the people who first started the American colonies.

Item_Response: Archeologists And What They Do             By: Nicholas Manske                  I bet you would think of Indiana Jones if you thought about an archeologist. First of all Indiana Jones is not your typical Archeologist. Second of all he was not real. Archeologist's are people who discover the lost and mysterious, treasures of history. Archeologist's have found some of the most historic places in history such, as the mythical city of troy. Howard Carter was a famous archeologist who found the tomb of king Tut. The discovery was amazing because most of the tombs in kings valley where robbed by grave robbers but, king Tut's tomb was completely untouched.Archeologist's find history and that is what they do for a living.                  An Archeologist's job dig up the past, basically. The common tools for an Archeologist is an pickaxe, a shovel, a whisk and dustpan, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim shovel, a Trowel, and a whip 'Just Kidding'. Sorry for the Indiana Jones reference, anyways those tools have specific uses. The pickaxe and shovel are used usually to start a dig. The whisk and dustpan is used for dusting of dirt and dust delicately. The wheelbarrow is used for carrying dirt away and some times it is used for carrying artifacts away. A skim shovel is used for removing a thin layer of dirt. Trowel is the most common tool for archeologist's. It cuts away different layers of soil.                   In 1993 Archeologist's were looking for the seventeenth century Fort James in Jamestown, Virginia. People had thought that the fort had disappeared because they thought it was washed away by the river that was next to it. The fort was built in 1607 for a new settlement in the America's. The first discoveries of the fort were found in 1861. They had uncovered weapons and armor. Then over a hundred years later Archeologist's finally found it. The used computer mapping and drawings to find where it was. The first thing they found was the marks in the ground. Those marks are they indication of where the walls were. The fort was in a triangle shape. They soon found the stone ledges that held the cannons for the fort. Archeologists found four cellars. They found ten buildings within the perimeter of the fort. They found dozens of burial sites around the fort too. Every year nearly one million objects are taken from the site each year. Those artifacts include coins, pottery,tools and children's toys. That excavation is an example of what the Archeologist's do every day for a living.                   Archeologist's work hard to find history. They work hard to protect the history of the world. The things they uncover are amazing. Fort James is one of many excavations that archeologists do. Archeologist's find most of the things you can find in the museum. Archeologist's are my hero's. I want to be one when i grow up.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                Archeologists thought that the stone base of the home of George Washington was still there. In 2003 they started digging. It took over a year to dig but they had found the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage rooms. A few years later they found the main farmhouse.        The diggers needed  to find proof that that was George's farmhouse. They had also found burnt clay pipes, so it gives more prooof that it's the right house.                 On this site, each year a group of archologists will work on the site. The first group uses 3D computers to check out what is underground. That data is recorded so that they know what it looked like before it was dug up. The second team is focused on the digging. This group uses shovels that can remove thin layers of soil. but one at a time. This team also does a job called trowling. Troweling is when they use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt from the artifacts.The third team stays in labs studying the objects found by the two other teams.          Some of the tools they used are skim shovels, wheelbarrow, knives, and a trowel.                             This job takes time, but it can be worth it!

Item_Response: An archeologists job is to dig up artifacts, bones, and other things.  People not trained to do this job could wreck the things they are digging up or uncovering.  Archeologists can work at one site for a couple of years.           The objects found at Fort James found can include pottery, coins, tools, and metal toys for children.  The settlers at Fort James use to throw their garbage down a pit/well and the archeologists found that pit/well and now we can see what they ate.  Also, the archeologists found a wall that was used to fire cannons.     No one knew exactly were George Washington's childhood house was actually located.  Archeologists believed that the stone base of his house on Ferry Farm was still there. It took a little over a year, but the archeologists finally found it.  Some of the first buildings they dug up were the slave quarters, the kitchen, and some storage houses. And a few years later the archeologists found the actual farm house.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                                                               By: Faith Henry          The job of an archeologist is to uncover artifacts and study them. We do it every single day. I Cameron Cancha am an archeologist that is in the team that studies the artifacts after they have been uncovered, so basically I get to see what the artifacts are.             One team maps the site on 3D computers that can track what is below the ground. Another team actually digs, the place they dig is called a dig. Those archeologists start with a shovel called skim shovels. Skim shovels are so small sharp and flat that they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. The soil that has been removed then is placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. The soil falls out and the artifacts stay in.                 The diggers also use a tool called a trowel that is a tool that is the most common, it is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. Troweling is the hardest process in archeology. You use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It takes a lot of time and effort!                Then comes the last job, my job. My team and I spend DAYS in the lab studing the objects that were found. But finally we finish. My eyes get SO tired that I almost fall asleep, but I keep on working, my team needs me and I need them!                            Well those are the different jobs of the archeologists. If you want to be one then be my guest! But it truely is a tiresome process, it takes a lot of time and effort so just be ready!                                             Your Friend,                                                  Cameron Cancha

Item_Response: ALL ABOUT ARCHEOLOGISTS           Archeologists are people who study artifacts from the past.       How do Archeologists collect the objects that they will study?       The awnser to the question that is listed above is: The first team of  Archeologists start to dig with an object called a skim shovel. Next, the Archeologists place the dirt in a box with screen at the bottom which sifts the dirt out of the box and keeps the artifacts inside. But it is not as easy as it sounds. The skim shovels are small and flat and only pick up a small amount of dirt at a time and so it takes longer to fill the box with dirt.Then the Archeologists do something called troweling. Troweling is using paint brushes, small shovels, and wooden or metal picks to remove the dirt in and on the artifacts. Next, the Archeologists do a study and find the history of the artifact.The other team spends a few days in the lab studying the artifacts that are found.The process is very slow but to the archeologists, it is worth every minute. And that is how Archeologists do their job.           SOME INTERESTING FACTS ABOUT ARCHEOLOGISTS ARE:           sometimes, it can take up to two weeks to dig up a twenty five square foot area!        some tools used by Archeologists are a pick and shovel, a whisk and a dustpan, a knife, a skim shovel, a trowel, and a wheelbarrow.       the computers used by archeologists can track what is underground.       QUESTION TIME!!       What are the teams in the process of the Archeologists?       The awnser to the question that is listed  above is: Each year, many people will work on the site. There is up to 30 people on each team. Each team does a different job.

Item_Response: In 1994, a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed by the river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life.  Most beleved that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to the dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot. However , objects found nearby suggested the settlers more protection from enemy ships. The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologist, the name for scientests who study objects from the past, a group effort to find the exactspot where the fort was built began. The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used.

Item_Response: Tools for archeologists                                  There are many tools archeologists use for finding artifacts during an excavation. Two of the most common are the whisk and dustpan and a trowel. Tools are used for different purposes in archeology but all of them help in their own way.                         First we have the whisk and dustpan. If an archeologist ever needs to clean an artifact he/she probably will use this tool. It's bristled end can brush dirt off artifacts, which can be important if there are any inscriptions on the artifact. The whisk and dustpan can also clear away any dirt from the excavation site, this is important if animals live near by. The whisk and dustpan is and always will be an important tool for any archeologists.                          Finally, we have the trowel. it is probably the most common tool in archeology. Why, you might ask. the trowel is the most common because it's sharp end can cut and scrape through dirt to view different types of soil. The trowel is important because you can find many fossils in soil. Fossils are valuable after they are analyzed by an archeologist.Without the trowel, archeologists wouldn't find nearly as many fossils as they do with the trowel.                           Tools are by far the most important element of archeology, two of the most important tools being the trowel and the dustpan and whisk. With these tools archeology is a lot easier. Archeology would be nothing without tools so all archeologists are thankful to have them.

Item_Response: The Life Of An Archeoligest's           It's not as hard as most people think. It's accualy kind of fun.         You get to spend a lot of time with the people you know. And you find new things every day. We also study a lot of old artifacts from a lot of famous people's things and clothes.         We also use a lot of cool stuff such as a pick, shovel, whisk dustpan, knife wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowl. And do a a lot of work in the field. Sometimes we get cold so we bring a jacket every day, but if hot we make shure to bring an exra pair of clothes.           Most of the time on the field we don't find anything, but when we do we make shure we do an exra good job analyzing it. When we were looking for George Washington's old house we found so many things such as his clay pipe, burnt pottery, and with all of this information they found out that there was a fire.         They also found the kichin some floor bourds and a room. In the Fort James they found the fort, wall, and the how big was. It's really dool when we analize the artifacts, because we use 3D computers.         When I was a little kid I always wanted to be an archeoligest and I hope you do to.

Item_Response: Archeologists and What They Do   by ♦ Jackson Holmstead               Archeologists do lots of amazing things! One thing I learned is there always on the verge of discovery. How do they do this? Whats the process? Well that's what I am about to dig up for you.           When archeologists first start they use a 3D computer to see whats under the ground. The information is the sent to the dig site that way they know what and were there looking for. But it can spend a couple days at the computers depending on how big the site is but that's only part of the process!            Secondly the send the lay out to the dig site were it`s examined carefully. Then the digging begins! The diggers start the dig with skim shovels. they are used to remove thin layers of soil with every scoop. Then they can use the pick and shovel. the are mainly used to tear up the ground close to the artifacts.Thanks to the handy trowel they can usually find one million artifacts a year!  but seriously we can`t forget the whisk and dustpan, it sounds like something you would use at home right? Well its also used to clear dirt off artifacts and get dirt off the excavation site. Last but not least is the wheelbarrow its used to carry things on and off the site.            Now lets talk about why they would do this. Is it just for fun? well not really. You see its archeology that brought us the dinosaurs, its archeology that puts suits of armors in the museum! Like I said archeology is amazing! Oh big deal right. Well did you know that kids can get involved to?  archeology is also educational. Who knew?            you are all familiar with the name George Washington well did you know that archeologist found his house. You see archeologists aren`t two year old's playing in the sand box no, these people all have families but they choose to help dig up historical sites because they know how important it is. There like detectives of the past. and I`d just like to tell them thank you. I`d encourage you to do the same.Well now you know about archaeologists and what they do. That`s my report and I hope you enjoyed it.                                                    (But there is lots more to find out)

Item_Response: The Dream           One day while my friends and I were walking home from school we were talking about the hardest job. I said being a football player is the hardest job. Jake and Bobby both said that being a archeologist is the hardest because you could spend two years looking for stuff and find only one thing. Plus you have to dig up a bunch of dirt in the hot sun.I told them that they were so wrong and that football's way harder, but that night everything changed.            When I got home I did my regular routine. I ate a snack, did my homework, watched some TV, and went to football practice. It was eight o'clock when I got home, so I ate dinner and went to bed.                I woke up the next day, and got out of bed but something was different. I was already wearing clothes! They weren't just regular clothes they were digging clothes! I went outside and guess where I was? I was in 1994, digging to find Fort James! I didn't know how I had gotten there but some guy yelled at me to keep working. So grabbed a shovel and starting digging trying to figure out what just happened. I woke up In digging clothes went out my door and ended up at Fort James. Something was wrong!                 It was really hard to dig because it was so hot out and I was getting tired. Not to mention that the ground was really hard to dig up and it felt like I'd dig on forever.After awhile we finally got a water break. I was so happy I sprinted over to get some water. This was hard work you have to be strong and have a lot of endurance. The thing is that we haven't even found anything yet. This was hard work, long, and tiring work I know I wouldn't want this for a job!                  After I drank some more water I got back to work. I still didn't understand what was happening, but I decided not to ask. i  was about to pass out from digging so long but when I stuck the shovel in the groung it made a thunk sound so I started to dig around it. With just a knife I started to dig aroundand guess what I found. It was a cannon every was watching and cheering but in between that someone was yelling at me to wake up. Every thing got fuzzy and I was back in my bed with my P.J's on. It wasall a dream! I told my mom when I grow up I want to be an archeologist. She asked me why and I said, 'It's because It's reall herd but in the your is making a discovery that no one's made before.' I know now never to dought a job before you do it!

Item_Response: Archaeologists studied many things about finding James fort. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England. The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground that marks where the fort's walls used to be. Archaelogists studied the area by using a computer mapping software. The stories they heard and read, they knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle. Archaeologists wanted to find artifacts of James fort. By the time they found the fort they found many artifacts. They found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings. They were all within the border of the fort.       Today,the group finds nearly one million objects each year. The objects are pottery, tools, coins, and metal toys for the children. The settlers that were there long ago, threw their trash in wells or into a big pit. While the archaeologists were digging to find more artifacts, they found the trash the settlers threw away also including the bones of the animals. The objects they found helps us learn how the settlers that were there lived in the James Fort. We now learned how the settlers did to survive the difficult years when they barely had any shelter.       Settlers that were in James Fort lived in difficult years. Archaeologists studied about James Fort and learned how the settlers lived back then by finding the animals bones that they ate. Also, the ones that they threw in the unusual well or into the big pit. Back then, they didnt have any money or that much clothes.They had to hunt for food and when their clothes ripped the had to sew it back on. Settlers had a difficult life. Archaeologists learned how the settlers fought against the Powhatan tribe. The Powhatan tribe mostly attacked them when they were in there James Fort. Settlers in the James Fort lived a difficult life when the the Powhatan tribe attackted them.       Archaeologists studied many thinga about George Washington's farmhouse. George Washington's father, Augustine Washington, moved to Ferry Farm. So the archaeologists went to Ferry Farm, but know one knew exactly where the Washington home was located. They didn't know because the actual building was long gone. However, the archaeologists still believes the stone base that was under the Washington's home, was still there. They digged until 2003, they kept searching for the stone base, then finally, one year later, they found it. The first buildings they found were the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. After a few years later, they have found the Washington's main farmhouse.       There are more than one archaeologists trying to find the farmhouse. They were split into teams. There are almost thity-five people on just one team! The archaeologists  trowels. Troweling  is when they use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the dirt. There are three teams. One team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what's underground. The second team focuses on the digging part. The second starts their digging by using skim shovels. Skim shovels are so small, flat, and sharp they can remove thin layers of soil. The third team spends days in the lab. They spend days in the lab because they study objects that the second team has found.

Item_Response: Archeologists                            Acheologists have a very important job in history. They have discovered most of the historical articals or books you have read. Archeologists dont just have to dig up things and write about it. They have to figure out who it used to belong to, what the item is, and if it is important. But, they do much, much more. An archeologists job is tough.            Archeologists have to be thinking about what they are looking at very carefully for many different reasons. One reason is because they have to see if it can be useful. Another reasons is so they can figure out who it belonged to. This job is not easy. Archeologists have to run the object into many different tests. But they have help by many different kinds of help, by many different things. They get help by machines, people, and their brains. This means they have to understand their job completely, and they have tovery smart! Archeologists are tough and have to be brave at times.            Archeologists dont just use their hands, they use many other tools. Their tools are very special and have their own special use. Some of their tools are: the pick, shovel, whisk, dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and the trowel. Archeologists use much many tools, but these are a few I can name. these tools come in handy at times. They all have their own use. The pick and shovel are used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. The whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. The knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from arounnd the artifacts. Also, the wheelbarrow is used to carry items from one place to another, or to carry dirt away from the excation site. Another tool is the skim shovel, it is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Now last, is the trowel. This tool is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. There is a lot of tools involved in a archeologist's job.            Archeologists were trying to discover more about Geoge Washington. They have found bones the animals have chewed on. They have found broken pottery. They have even found George Washington's old clay pipes! This was an amazing discovery! The pottery they found looked burned, so they think they had started a fire in their house. But they are not positive. There is still a chance this could hve happened, but, it is not a fact yet. Archeologists still have a lot to discover and I don't think they will stop searching.            In conclusion, I think archeologists are super smart and are ready to face anything. Hopefully, they will figure out plenty of more things in history, but we just have to wait. There is no dought in my mind that they won't find out anything else.

Item_Response: Finding artifacts in the past are very exiting to see, but how do they find these old artifacts? Here's how they discover it. Archeologists go to sites to look for where a well-known person used to live. Like, George Washington for example, recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home have helped archeologists know more about him as a young boy.          Archeologists recently went to the Ferry Farm to discover George Washington's past and recovering about this long gone farmland. The process of digging at the Ferry farm is a careful one. Each year, many teams will work on the site. The can be up to 35 people in one team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information will be recorded so that the archeologists will know what it looked like before people before started digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the digging is called a dig. Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat, and sharp that they can remove thin layers one at a time. Then that soil is placed in a box with a half-inched screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! And another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. the whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's really worth it.

Item_Response: Archeologists                                                                          This report is on Archeologists. An archeologist is a person who finds rare artifacts about a certain topic. Lots of archeologists want to find artifacts that would impact on others people's life. Archeologists find facts about history and try to find the special details from that period of history. Archeologist don't always find the artifacts they want, they sometimes have to go by what the have.        People think an archeologist job is exciting. That is true, archeologist have a great job. They go back in time and find the history so they can present it into today's world. Most of the artifacts go in a museum. If they are very fragile and need to be handled with care they will probably leave them in a lab of take more care of it.       Discovering an artifact is something really exciting to do. When archeologist find an artifact they put them on wheelbarrows. A wheelbarrow is used to move items from one place to another or to carry excess dirt and soil away from the site. After they collect all the artifacts they can find they take them to the labs so the workers of the labs can do their job. Archeologists have found artifacts from George Washington's house and from Fort James. Archeologist do have a cool job!       There are lots of different teams that archeologist have to work. There is the team that find the artifacts. They use 3D computers to find where the artifacts are in the ground. Then there are the actual diggers who dig the artifacts from the ground. Everyone has a certain job that really does matter!       The tools are really important while having this job. A few really important tools are      the skim shovel and the trowel. A skim shovel has a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of dirt and soil from the ground. The trowel is the most common tool an archeologist uses. It is used to cut the different layers of the dirt or soil.       Every person a job that needs to get done. We need to look in the past so we can understand about life back then. Thing that we think are not important actually are important. Going back in history can never happen, so that's why an archeologist's have a job.

Finding something that most people haven't seen yet is a very exciting experience, one that will also help others with their research.           An archeoligist's job is all of these things, and that is why we know so much about our past today. Being an archeoligist helps more than anything, and knowing that you just helped humans discover more things must feel really, really, good.

Item_Response: In 1994, a group of people interested in finding Fort James.For over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.The fort was biult in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fot was built near the river.However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.The first objects were found in 1861.Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.The National Park Service led 5 year study of the area to figure out how the land was used.The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make image of the area.That's when they finally found James Fort! The first thing thet found was a set of marks on the ground.The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be.Between all the stories they heard and read, and drawing they made, the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a tringle.               Today, the groups find nearly 1 million objects each year. In the 1600s, peopleused to throw their trash down unused well or into a bid pit. While digging in the area, the archaeologist found trash that settlers threw away, including the bones of animals they ate.The information learned from these objects help us understand how the people in James Fort lived. We noe know what the settlers did to survive the difficult years when they had little food. It is exiting to discover objects that were regulary used by people who lived hundreds of years ago. It gives us a peice of our last and ties us to people who first started the American colonies.

Item_Response: To be an archeologists you have to work hard and travel a lot. For an example Fort James it took a long time for it to be found. But in 1861 archeologists uncovered armor, weapons, and floors from houses. Over 100 years latter archeologists found James Fort. Today archeologists finds nearly 1 million objects each year.             Archeologists have a long order of doing things. They have to map the areas using 3D computers that track what's underground. The information is recorded so that people what it looks like underground before they start digging. Then they start digging, the place were they dig is called a dig. When they start digging they use skim shovels. The soil is placed in a box with a screen in the bottom, the dirt falls while the artifacts stay in. They use paint brushes, small shovels and wood picks.             The job of an archeologists is very important. If archeologists didn't do their job we wouldn't know much about our past. Like we wouldn't have known much about George Washington's child hood. Or where fort James was. Archeologists use lots of tools. For An example Archeologists use a pick and a shovel to dig close to the artifacts. A whisk and dustpan is used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away the dirt from the site. A knife is used for digging and to scrape dirt around the artifacts. A wheel barrow used to move items from one place to another or carry dirt from the site. A skim Shovel is used for removing a thin layer of soil.  A trowel is a common tool in archaeology, It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: Archeologists have an important job. To be an archeologist, you have to be patient. Finding artifacts from years and years ago is not easy, but it can be made slightly easier with the right tools.     Most of the archeologists dig at the site where they think an artifact is. They use several tools, including the skim shovel, the trowel, and the pick and shovel. The many diggers dig through a very large area, and it can take weeks. You don't always find something though.     As mentioned before, you must be patient when digging. There were settlers in 1607 and the first artifacts found from them were discovered about two hundred years after. You also have to study, and a lot. The National Park Service studied for five entire years just to figure out how the land was used. Sometimes, it doesn't take as long, but it usually takes a while.     Also, you may not know whether the artifact you have found is from that time. People may have later settled in that same area and left more modern things behind, and you have mistaken it for something ancient. Or, you might just be looking in the wrong spot and not find anything at all. You might mistake something useless for something valuable, or vice versa. Archeologists have to be very careful when they examine the things they have found because it might be worth something. You never really know until you study closely.     When a group of archeologists is lucky, they can find nearly one million artifacts each year.

Item_Response: This is what it is like to be an Archeologist.  It is hard work.  You would need a lot of patience.  Let's get started!       Archeologists are people who dig up ancient artifacts and see what they are, who they belonged to and when it was from.  It can take days to find something valuable.  Archeologists use special tools such as shovels, brushes, and picks.  They use picks to move dirt.  They use brushes to clear away dirt from the site and to clear off artifacts.       This is how they find artifacts.  First, they use computers to locate the artifacts.  Then, they dig up layers of the Earth's soil with a big shovel.  Then, they use smaller shovels to get to the last layer.  Next, they use the brushes to clear away the dirt on the artifact.  Lastly  they give it to the archeologist team who study it.       A 25-square-foot section can take up to two weeks to dig!  Finding things can be important.  They can tell us important things from history like finding George Washington's things.  They tell us about him as a child, maybe.  Or they can tell us what he liked to do for fun.  It'd be boring, but it would be worth it.       That is partly what it'd be like to be an Archeologist.  Maybe you'd like to be one someday.  It might actually be fun.  You could find coins, clothes, or a pipe!

For example in the passage Digging up George Washington's Past They are talking about the artifacts that Archeologists have found. They use other tools too like Whisk and dustpan, Knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, they also use a trowel like people might use in their garden.                     An Acheologist is a very interesting job, they have to dig for treasures all day in the hot sun long but they get to learn about people and places while they are doing it.  The bad thing about being an archeologist is when your digging by a river your hole might start to fill up with water or you might dig up a coffin covered in bugs and termites.                       A nice thing about being an Archeologist is that you might get to travel around the world to dig.  Now, that would be nice unless you have to dig in the desert.                    Archeologists have to learn how to use all the tools that they need for digging. So they have to learn how to use a knife the way their supposed too because they have to use it to carefully dig the dirt out from around an artifact so they don't damage it or to use a special kind of shovel called a skim shovel because they have to use it to scrape just a thin layer of soil of the top of the earth!              Acheologists jobs can go for more than a week so they might be a way from home for a long time.  In 1961 The National Park Service ran a five year study to find where Fort James was and they found where it was after five years of searching they found a mark in the ground.  Archeologists can Find very big things to during the five year study the archeologists found 11 cellars, dozens of burial sites and ten buildings. The National Park Service led a 5-year study to the area to figure out how the land was used. During the 1600s, archeologists found trash that the settlers threw away, including the bones of animals they ate.                    Objects found over years include pottery, tools, coins, rocks, and also metel toys for kids. Today, gruops all over the United States find millions of objects a year!

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                                                               Archeologists have an important job of learning about the past. Without them we would not know much about things like what tools people used or even where they lived. They teach us about how the people survived and also how they fought enemies. It also lets us know why people made the decisions they made and what they were like.       How do archeologists find all that information? First, they must find the site that the place they want to find out about is on. They look for artifacts that were used at the place and when they find some they know that the place was near or where the artifacts are. Next, they use a 3D computer that track what is under ground so that the archeologists know what to look for. Then, they start digging. They are very  careful not to damage any artifacts that are under the ground so they only dig up a bit a of dirt at a time. Finally, they study the artifacts they found and decide what they mean.       What tools do the archeologists use? Some examples of what they use include:       A pick and shovel for digging A whisk and dustpan for brushing dirt off the artifacts A knife for careful digging and to scrape dirt off artifacts A wheelbarrow to transport dirt and items from one place to another A skim shovel to remove thin layers of soil A trowel to scrape and cut to view different layers of soil       This is a bit of an archeologists job.

Item_Response: The Life of an Archeologist   An archeologist has a very hard and interesting job. Basically, they have to investigate the lives of those who lived long ago. But, they also have to have the correct items to identify what people ate, did, etc. After cleaning those items, they relate them to what they would have been used for. For an example, if an archeologist was examining the life of Native Americans in one of their ancient huts, and he/she found a rabbit skeleton, then he/she would know that Native Americans ate rabbits. They study the past, discover new things about it, and can teach others about what they've learned.       An archeologist studies the past in order to get information on what they are trying to discover more about. That way they already have an idea of what else they need to know. Then, they head out to explore more about the subject. It might not be as fun to just learn about something, but it pays off when archeologists get to uncover artifacts and discover things about them.       An archeologist discovers new things while obtaining old artifacts. By finding one item, the archeologists are able to find out more things based on this 'newly discovered' object's uses and relate them to what people did. As I said earlier, we could find out that Native Americans ate many rabbits, and if rabbits were extinct today, we'd know what caused that extinction. It is also very useful to learn about because we can discover the cause of things that have happened. For an example, if we didn't know why the sky is blue (even if we do), and let's say that we found out that there was some 'blue chemical' released into the air because there were hints of it in crumbling caves from long ago, we could get rid of other fears that we have, like excess carbon dioxide makes it blue or some nonsense like that.       Lastly, archeologists can teach others about what they have learned. Obviously, they don't just find information and store it in their brains. They tell others, let's say some scientists who will then scientifically analyze that artifact and find out even more. Then those scientists will put what they learned out to the public, in a book, most of the time, to educate others. It is always good to know more about a subject because it benifits you with more knowlege. So, technically, archeologists teach the world about what they've learned.       Archeologists have a challenging job that benifits the rest of us. They study the past, discover new things, and can teach others about what they've learned. They have an important job in our society. They dig for history!

Item_Response: Archeologist                    Have you ever dug in your backyard and found something like a piece of what looks like broken glass? That may have been an artifact from long ago! This is what some people do for a living. They are archeologists.                How do they do it?Archeologists use special 3-D computers to track what is underground. next they record the information. Then they go to the site where they found the artifact and then they go dig. First, they use a small, sharp, and flat tool called a skim shovel and remove each layer one at a time. Next they put the dirt they had just shoveled out and put it in a sifter so that the dirt goes out and the artifacts stay in. Diggers also use troweling to find things as well. Troweling is where people use paint brushes wooden picks and small shovels to find the artifacts. It can take up to two weeks to dig a twenty-five-square-foot hole! Then they go to the lab and examine all the different things they found. Trying to find the artifacts is very difficult, tiring, and a lot of work, but it is worth it because we find out so much about our history through the artifacts.                Some tools they used include: the pick and shovel, whisk and dust pan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. The pick and shovel and used to start digs and tom penetrate the earth to get to the artifacts. The whisk and dustpan were used  to brush the artifact clean and clear the dirt away from he digging site. The knife was used to scrape thick layers of dirt that are on the artifact off, and to carefully dig it out. The wheelbarrow is used to move the found items and dirt to different locations. The skim shovel is used to remove a thin layer of soil at a time with its sharp flat edges. Finally, the trowel is is used to cut soil so the archeologists can see the different layers. It is probably the most common tool an archeologist uses.                        Archeology can give us a better understanding and more knowledge of someone and/or a time period. For instance when they found George Washington's home that he grew up in, we learned more about: him as a boy, what led him to make the decisions he had made, how people lived in colonial times, etc.                In conclusion, archeologists have a hard, fascinating, long, and knowledge-gaining job. We can learn so much about history from archeologists work. I want to be an archeologist when I grow up so that I can dig up our past!

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is not an easy one. You don't just get a shovel and dig until you find something. You'll need the patience, passion, and precision.      You might have to wait a while before you start digging. And even if you do dig you might not find what you are looking for. Most archeologist have to search for decades for the artifacts they want to find. Sadly, sometimes when they do find artifacts they are entirely fragile and break within seconds. It is important to wait for things to come before you start looking like clues of its existence. Often, seeking something without patience will quickly diminish.      You need some passion for discovery if you are going to become an archeologist! Don't just say,' Oh I'm going to be rich and famous because when I am an archeologist I'll find a gigantic chocolate city!' That's not how it works. You want to be an archeologist because you are doing it for fun. It is important to think about what doing a job is really like. In life, don't look in the past or future, focus on the present.      Precision with tools is what you also need to be an archeologist. The pick, shovel, whisk, dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skin shovel, trowel, and many of tools are involved with the job. Item_Response: Archeology   Archeology is the study of artifacts and digging for artifacts.  Archeologists search for many things.  They look for artifacts from certian people in history.  But they also look for all artifacts in general too.  They look for artifacts from a famous person in history's childhood.  They look for historical places and boundries too.  If they find a historic site they'll search for artifacts within that boundry.  Artifacts they find are from all times in history.  They could find artifacts from the dinosaur time to Rosa Parks' time.Once they do find an artifact they restore it.           It takes lots of work to find an artifact.  They use lots of different tool too.  They use:   A pick and shovel A whisk and dustpan A knife A wheelbarrow A skim and shovel And a trowel   They use a pick and shovel to simply dig into the soil.  That is how most excavations start.  The whisk and dustpan is for brushing away any loose dirt from the artifact, or taking dirt away from the site.  A knife is used to scrape the dirt off the artifact.  It is also used to dig very carefully under the soil.  The knife is used for very careful projects.  The wheelbarrow is used to carry dirt away from the excavation site.  It also carrys different items away too.  The skim shovel is used to dig a thin layer of dirt at a time.  And a trowel is used to cut and to scrape the dirt away so they can view the different layers of soil.  A trowel is probably the most common tool.      Some of the items I read about that archeoligists have found are items from George Washington's barn and James Fort.  They have found George Wasahington's clay pipe.  they also found where his family barn used to be.  At Fort James they found armor and weapons, floors of buildings, ledges to hold cannons, eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, ten buildings, pottery, tools, coins, metal toys for children, and where they through all their trash.  All this helps us learn things.  Thats why people are all still searching today.  That is what an archeologist does.

Item_Response: In 1994,a group of people where interested in studing the past  to rediscover  archaeological project The project was desined  by James Fort in Jamestown, Virgina. For over 200 years,  people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock  ships there, so it made  sense that the settlers would  choose that spot. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The new spot probably gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships.       The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew that this would hep them decide where to look for proof of the fort. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.       That's when they  finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. Between all the stories they heard and read, and drawing they made,the archeologists knew that  the fort would be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and found out that the fort stretched  all the way to the river.Then they realized there were stone ledges built over the river. The ledges were designed to hold canons.The archeologists also found eleven cellars,dozens of burial sites,and ten buildings all within the border of the fort.       Today, the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year.The objects include pottery, tools,coins, and even metal toys for children.In the 1600s, people used to throw their trash down an unused well or into a big pit. While digging in the area, the archeologists found the trash the settlers threw away, including the bones of animals they ate.The information learned from these objects  helps us understand how the settlers fought the Powhatan tribe that often attacked them. We also know how the settlers did to survive the difficult years when they had little food.       It is exciting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago.It gives us a piece of our past and ties us to the people who first started the American colonies.

Item_Response: Archeologists                                 By: Kaila Martindale                   Archeologist are people who study objects from the past and use these objects to do the job. 1.picks 2.shovels 3.whisks               4. dustpans 5.knifes 6.wheelbarrows 7.skim shovels  and 8.trowels. There can be up to thirty-five people on a team just to find one artifact! The first team can map the area by using 3D computers that can track what is right under our feet. The information is recorded so that people will know what the item will look like before people start the actual digging.                    Another team has to focus on the actual digging, and the spot the team does the digging is called 'a dig'. Those archeologists start their dig with skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat, and sharp that they can remove layers of soil, one  at a time. That soil is then placed in a box with a screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out well while the artifacts stay in the box.            The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.              The discovery of Washington's house is important for many reasons. First, it gives the people of the United States a better understanding of who George Washington was before he was famous. We also begin to know why he made the decisions that he did. Another thing it does is help historians learn about the life Colonial Americans lived. All of these things are parts of our past as Americans.                        And that is the job of an Archeologist.

Item_Response: The job of an archaeologist is not an easy one, thought it is interesting. It may take months or years to find what they may be looking for, and they have specific tools. Archaeologists may find everyday objects from years ago, or one of our old presidents houses!        Archeologists use tools you may even use in your garden. Some of them are: wheelbarrow, trowel, and a shovel. Though some aren't everyday objects for example: Whisk, pick, or a skim shovel. A skim shovel is used to remove small amounts of dirt at a time. The soil removed is placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This screen allows soil to fall out while found artifacts stay in. Another tool is a whisk and dustpan, these are used to clear soil off artifacts. one tool that is a good use outdoors in general is a wheelbarrow. wheel barrows can be used to move artifacts and/or other items. they may also be used to clear dirt away from the dig.       Finding one item or place can take many years of work from many teams. When finding Fort James,   Archeologists uncovered armor and weapons, they also found floors from buildings. Over 100 years after those discoveries, multiple teams  put in effort to find where the fort was built. These teams took more than 100 years to just begin searching for where Fort James was built. finding objects from hundreds of years ago may take a hundred years.       Some things or places Archeologists searched for were fameous landmarks, such as George Washingtons house as a young boy. No one knew exactly where THe WAshington home was located because the building was far past gone. Archeologists believed that the base of the house was still there. they began digging in 2003, It took over a year to find it. but they only found few rooms at first, the kitchen,, slave quarters, and storage houses. They found th farmhouse years later. The diggers needed to prove that this house did belong to the Washington family. Rocords had shown that there had been a fire. THey found pieces of burnt pottery, witch shows a sign that there had been a fire there. They also knew  that Washington smoked clay pipes, when they found part of a clay pipe, that gave more evidence that this was george washingons house as a boy.       Argheologists look for things over very long periods of time, with specific tools and artifacts could be part of a fameous landmark.

Item_Response: Digging up History!                 Is an archeologist's job fun? Well of course it is! Here's why this is my belief: Archeologists discover a lot of artifacts and they even discover long lost places. They dig for certain things with certain tools. That's super interesting! Archeologists find bones, marks in the ground, and they even find fossils. But most of all, they dig up history.                You see, archeologists discovered dinosaur bones. But they also discovered Jamestown's Fort James. The story behind the fort was that it was washed away by a river flood. But soon, archeologists discovered that it still exists. Actually, none of it was still actually there but the memories and marks in the ground showed that was exactly where the fort was. Archeologists found artifacts near the marks in the ground where the fort was so then they new that the fort was there because of the evidence. That's how archeologists rediscovered Fort James.                   So far, archeologist's jobs sound fun! Not only did archeologists discover artifacts and Fort James, but they discovered George Washington's childhood home. Now, Washington's home is still around...Still standing...Still active! Archeologists decided to keep the house open for visiting, so people can check out how it was like to live like a colonist. Also, they hold classes where children learn to become a junior archeologist and to solve puzzles about the colonial time period right inside and near Washington's home at the site where you can see the giant artifact, his home!                   The tools are most important to archeologists! If an archeologist doesn't have tools, how is he or she supposed to discover artifacts. Think about it, if archeologists don't have tools, then museums wouldn't be around today. Picks and shovels are used for digging. When digging, these are normally the ones that archeologists use first. They use whisks and dustpans, too. The whisks are for dusting off dirt and the dustpans are to collect that dust. Knives are used for scraping off the dirt and cutting the dirt to dig. Wheelbarrows are used to carry an artifact from one place to another. Skim shovels are used for removing one layer of soil every scoop. Trowels are used most commonly because in archeology, they truly are the most helpful.                  So, I hope everyone thinks that archeology is important to history. Archeologists truly do have an fun and important job. They sure do know how to dig up history!

Item_Response: Life as an Archeologist                  Life as an archeologist is exciting in many ways. You can dig in histroical places that aren't open to the public. You can study ancient artifacts and maybe become famous for a discovery. You will have an exciting but tiring time in the digs or the lab. Here are some things that you can experience as an archeologist.                  Here is how you find and study artifacts. First, a team map the area so that you can find what's underground. Next, another team called the dig does the actual digging. They start the dig with skim shovels to remove thin layers of soil one at a time. The soil is placed in a special box where there is a half-inch screen at the bottom so the dirt can fall out while the artifacts stay in. Then, the archeologists use a whisk and dustpan, small shovels, paint brusthes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. Finally, the objects are taken to the labratory to be studied.                As an archeologist, you will use many different tools while you are working. The pick and shovel most commonly starts the digs. They are used to dig into the soil, close to the artifacts. The whisk and dustpan is used to brush dirt off artifacts and away from the digging site. The knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the objects. The skim shovel is used to move a thin layer of soil with each scoop. A trowel is the most commonly used tool. Its used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. The wheelbarrow is used to carry items from one place to another or to take dirt away from the excavation site.                Kids, if you're intrested in becoming an archeologist when as a job when you're older, here are some suggestions. You can go to the place where George Washington's home was discovered before he became famous, Ferry Farm. You can go to their summer workshops with both indoor and outdoor activities. Kids can explore the site, experience colonial life, and become junior archeologists by signing up for classes, games, and crafts. You can even go to their website and solve puzzles about work at Ferry Farm.               Being an archeologist is a nice experience. Item_Response: Sources for finding Fort James.      source#1 http://www.nps.gov/jame/historyculture/chronogoly-of-jamestownarcheolgy.htm   And http://historicjamestowne.org   the last for source#1 is http://apva.org/rediscovery   Tools used by archeologists        Pick and Shovel: most digs start with these two tools.Used to dig into the Earth, close to the artifacts.   Whisk and Dustpan: Used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.   Knife: Used for careful digging and to scrape dirt around the artifacts. Wheelbarrow: Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site.   Skim Shovel:A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.   Trowel: Probably the most common tool in archeology. Used to scrapeand cut to view the different layers of soil.           Finding Fort James   In 1994 a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeologcial Project. The project was disigned to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia.                     The fort was built in 1607 when the setters came from England to start a new life. Most believe that James Fort was built near the river. It was eaiser to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.                   The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists, the name for scientist who study objects from the past, uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later , a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.

Item_Response: Archeologists use many tools to help them find artifacts. They usually start with picks and shovels to dig into the earth. When they are getting closer to an artifact they might start using the skim shovel to take off layers of dirt. Once they get to the artifact, they would probably dust it off with the whisk and dustpan.After that they would take it away in the wheelbarrow.                 Archeologists usualls work in teams of up to 35 people. They would map the site using 3D computers first. Using that, they can track what there is underground. Another team focuses on the digging. they start using skim shovels. The soil is placed in a box with a half inch screen at the bottom. Some archeologists use a process called troweling. That is when they use small shovels, paint brushes, and picks to remove dirt. Another team spends time in the lab studying the objects.            Some projects they might work on are trying to find out more about the things they find. They would probably try to connect their discoveries to tell a whole story. Some examples are the colonies and more about the American Indians. Others might try to find more about famous people's past.

You can find out more about what they made and how they made it. Also you can figure out how and what they use to hunt and make food. If you do dig up bones you can see what kind of animals use to live in the world there. Maybe you can even see different type of rocks and jewelry they use to make back then and sell it and make a lot of money.            You can find out new way they use to do things. Like maybe they don't wash dishes like we do. Or maybe they don't wash clothes  like we  do. We could find tools they use to help them. And we could probably find weapons they use to fight with during war. And if you do find a tool you can always find out how it works too.
