Item_Response: Archeologists       Archeologists are scientists who study objects from times in the past and discover things that no one has found before. Sometimes archeologists will study some historical sites from where some past presidents have lived. Just like where George Washington lived when he was a boy before he became president. Or maybe you could explore a fort like Fort James! Being an archeologists could be a fun job for a lot of people.       Archeologists have to use many tools. Some examples are: a pick and shovel, a whisk and dustpan, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim shovel, and a trowel. A pick and shovel are used for digging into the Earth and getting close to artifacts. A whisk and dustpan are used for brushing dirt of the artifact  and clear away dirt from the site. A knife is used for for careful digging and to scrape dirt away from around the object. The other objects are used for different things too. Those are just some examples.       Finding the things that archeologists find at the location has a long process behind it. Especially the project at George Washington's house. Their process is a very careful one. Each year they have A LOT of teams work on the site. There can be up to as many as 35 people on a team! Now that is a lot! The first team will map the area using a 3D computer, that can track what is underground. The information is recorded  so that the people on the teams know what it looks like underground before they start digging.One of the other teams that are on the project will focus on the actual digging. The place where the actual digging is done is called a dig. Well that makes sense!       Once they have finished digging up the soil, it is placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This will let all the dirt fall out while artifacts stay in. The diggers use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It could take up to 2 weeks to dig up a 25-square-foot section! Then one more team spends DAYS in the lab studying the artifacts that were found. The whole process is slow and not so fun, but it is totally worth it.       As you see, being an archeologist is hard work. Even though it seems hard, I bet you would still want to be one! To find more information go to:       http://www.smitsonianmag.com/history-archaeology/digs-wahsington-200809.htm?c=yge=1       http://www.kenmore.org       http://diganthro.wordpress.com/ferry-farm       http://www.uwlax.edu/mvac/ProcessArch/ProcessArch/field_excavationtech.html       http://diganthro.wordpress.com

Item_Response: Finding Fort James                             In 1994, a group of people that were interested in studing the past stated te Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. It was created to find the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 2 hundred years, people thought that James Fort was swept away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around. When the fort was built ,in 1607, settlers came from England to start a new life. Most belived that James Fort was built by the river. However, objects were found nearby showed that the fort was further away. The new spot probably gave more protection from enemy ships.                          Digging Up George Washington's Past                              Most of what we know about George Washington comes from his years as a soldier and president. Biographies don't have very good infromation of our first president's childhood. That's changing, however recent discoveries have helped historiansknow more about Georges childhood. People have lived on a land called by the name Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years. It is a perfect place  to build a house and thats what Augustine Washington did. Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                                        By; Ellie Villalta                                          This report is about the job of an archeologist on what they do, how they do it, and what tools they use.           An archeologist is a person who study's objects from the past. Archeologists are sorted into teams, there can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the digging is called a dig. Those archeologists start to dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat, and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling. Trowling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.

Item_Response: Archeologist's Work                     An archeologist's job is to study artifacts from the past. They find the artifacts by doing a dig. A dig is where archeologists go to a site and use computers that make a 3-D image that shows a picture of what is under ground. Once they find the spot where the artifact is they will Start digging.                 To start a dig they get into teams of about 35. One team gets the 3-D image ready and the other team digs. Some digs are really long, like the Ferry Farm Dig. Ferry Farm is where George Washington lived. In the Ferry Farm Dig they found a clay pipe witch George Washington used to smoke.                 Another major dig was the James Fort Dig. This dig was to find James Fort. Before they started the dig people thought that the fort got washed away. But as they started to dig they found that the fort stretched miles out from the river. They found signs of the forts walls which was one of the clues that told them that the fort stretched out so far.                 Some tools used for an archeological dig are:       Pick and shovel   Most digs start with this tool. Used to get further into the soil and closer to the artifacts.       Skim shovel   Used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil.       Whisk and dustpan   This tool is used to clear away soil from above or an an artifact.       Knife   Used to carefully remove dirt from around the artifact.       Wheel barrow   Used to move dirt and artifacts around.       Trowel   This tool is probably the most common tool used in archeological digs, used to scrape and cut through the soil to see the different layers.                 To review an archeologist is a person who studies artifacts from the past. A dig is when people dig to find artifacts. To start a dig they split into two teams and use a computer to get an image of what is in the ground. to finish there are seven main tools used.

For your directions to beginning you will look at several sources.You can look at any sources you like.Source #1 will be on the article about how archeologists find artifacts at Jamestown Island which is based on information in the following sources:     http://www.nps.gov/jame/historyculture/chronology-of-jamestown-archeology.htm   http://historicjamestown.org                                                                                              http://apva.org/rediscovery.                                                                                                                                        FINDING FORT JAMES                                            by  Cheryl Bradley             In 1994,a group of people were interested in studying the past starting at the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project.this project was designed to discover the secrets of James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia. For around 200 years,people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.The fort was made in 1607 when settlers came from England to begin a new life.Most believed that James Fort was build near the river.It was easier to dock ships there,so it finally made sense that the settlers would choose that spot.However,objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.Their new spot probably gave the settlers more protection from the enemy's ship. WHISK AND DUSTPAN                                             Used to brush off dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.       KNIFE               Used to careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.       WHEELBARROW                                  Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away away from the excavation site.       SKIM SHOVEL                            A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.       TROWEL                   Probably the most common tool in archeology.Used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: Archeologists help us understand the past. In this statement you will see how they teach us about the past, find valuable artifacts that help us under stand parts of history, find helpful diaries and books, how they find important inventions from long ago, and how they find ancient civilizations.      Archeologists teach us about the past. They find old ruins and evidence about battles that have taken place. They find skeletons of warriors, cavemen, and so many more. Scientists can study these skeletons and see how they died and other tings that answer questions society has for that specific time period. We have even found Noah's Ark from the Bible.      Archeologists find valuable artifacts that help us under stand parts of history. We have found many artifacts in James town that have helped us figure out how they lived, even some of the food them and their pets ate. Also, just by studying the trash from the time period, we know more than we did before about James town. Also, from the fossils we find we can know about many of the species at the time.      Archeologists find helpful diaries and books. We have found diaries of many presidents and other important people we didn't have much history about before because of archeologists looking in the right places. Also, we have also have found many books such as the bible, we even have the first bible ever made or so people say. We now many things about different time periods because of diaries and books from long ago.      Archeologists find important inventions from long ago. Without archeologists, we wouldn't know how people from long ago wrote, collected water, and much more. Also, they have found many useful things that we would wonder about like, how people sowed and what did they use, where did they store their trash, and these are just a few of the questions I have myself.      Archeologists find ancient civilizations. Archeologists have found civilizations such as James Fort, temples, and what used to be great fortresses. By finding these, we now know about the ancient civilizations. We now know about what conditions they lived through, how well they built their structures, and how they survived threw what they did.   Also, we also know who or what they worshiped.      Archeologists help us understand the past. They help us figure out so much about our peoples history. I hope now you realize how important archeologists are. They help us find valuable artifacts, civilizations, diaries and books, and important inventions.

Item_Response: Archeologists are scientists that study items from the past. They study American history and ancient history. They use tools to dig up things that have been buried underground for many years. They use tools like a pick and a shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. The pick and the shovel are used to dig into the ground and dicover things. The whisk and the dustpan are used to brush dirt off of artifacts. The knife is used to do careful digging around the artifacts. Now, the wheel barrow is used to carry items around or to move dirt from the digging site. The skim shovel is used to carefully remove soil that is thin. Last but not least there is the trowel. The trowel is used to scrape, cut, and view different layers of soil. Now that is what an Archeologist is and what him or her does.

Item_Response: Archeologists, the name for scientists who study objects from the past, uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was began.           People have lived on the land known as Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years. Its location makes it a perfect place to build a home. Therefore, it's not surprising that George Washington's father, Augustine Washington, moved his family there. George was just six years old at the time.       No one knew exactly where the Wahington home was located since the actual building was long gone. However, archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there. They started digging in 2003. It took over a year, but they finally found it. The first buildings they found were the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. They found the main farmhouse a few years later.       How do the archeologists find all these things that were in Washington's house all those years ago? The process of digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one. Each year, many teams will work on the site. There can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started igging. Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the dissing is called a dig. Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat, and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling.       Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. it can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.       The discovery of Washington's home is important for many reasons. First it gives the citizens of the United States a better understading of who George Washington was before he became famous. We also being to know why he made the decisions he did. Another thing it does is help historians learn about the type of life Colonial Americans lived. All of these things are key parts of our past as Americans.

Item_Response: Archeologists   What does an archeologist do? Do they perform tricks? Do they sing and dance? Actually archeologists are people who find things in the past or in history as you call it. Archeologists find dinosaur bones, villages, statues, and many other things. They actually found Fort James and George Washington's house! Read on to know what these people do for a living:       Archeologists found many things in the past. For example, Fort James. When they found Fort James it was hard cause the area was underground from storms and floods. What they had to do first was scan the area with computer mapping systems to locate the area. Then they had to finally dig with tools such as picks, shovels, whisks, knifes, skim shovels, trowels, dustpans, and wheelbarrows. It took more than a year and then somebody found a broken down house with the items still in it! They found pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children. Then somebody found the pit on where the settlers at Fort James put their trash in. They found in the pit for example bones from animals which they ate. Soon enough they instantly found villages of houses in the area. Now thats a huge place!       Then archeologists had another mission to do finding George Washingtons house. Of course they did the same thing. They started digging in 2003 and then they found it a year later. The buildings they found were a kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. Soon they found a farmhouse. But after they found their victory nobody believed them. So they had to find some proof. In stories, people say that a fire accured there. The diggers found burnt pottery and ash. That means a fire occured. Also history says that George Washington smoked and they found clay pipes! Soon the discovery was proofed to be the right house.       Archeologists still do many other things, but thats just some of them. They still are working right now to figure out the past themselves. Let's just hope that this history will still exist.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist         Archeologists have special and amazing jobs. They work hard every day at one poject. They have one job, many tools, and determination.         One example is from a article called 'Finding Fort James', by Cheryl Bradley. Archeologists searced long and hard to find the outline of the walls to James Fort. They also uncovered many other things, such as cellars, burial sites, and buildings. It took five years to finally uncover the site of the walls. Archeologiss never ave up. They researched the shapes of forts and other important location hints. Other people have found pottery, coins, tools, and toy like objects since the time they had found the outlines.         Another example is 'Digging up George Washington's Past'. Archeologists had to infer that it was indeed Gearge Washington's house they had found. It took them a long time, but they eventually found the kitchen, slave room, storage rooms, and the farmhouse. They used a mix of different tools to excavate he area.         Archeologists use many different tools for many different uses. They first use the skim shovel to remove layers of dirt easily, and then they use trowels and the whisk and dustpan to carefully remove the artifacts.         It takes a lot of hard work and teamwork to uncover such big sites. Archeologists are very important in finding out the history of things. Without them, we probably wouldn't know that much about what the Indians made or ancient settling locations.

Item_Response: In 1994, a group of people interested in studing the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeologcal Project.The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James fort in Jamestown,Virginia.for over 200 years ,people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around. Item_Response: Digging it Up                      Some people think that a job of a archeologist is just digging up dirt and find important stuff, like you could do it in your very own backyard.  But it's not as simple as it looks! In this essay you will read about the process of a job of a archeologist, it will include tools, artifacts, and locations where they found our first president's house!          There are many teams of archeologists.  The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track whatever is underground.  The information is recorded so that other people can use the information to locate where to dig.  The second team focuses on digging, that place where they would be digging is called a dig.  After they dig up all the artifacts such as pottery, clay, metal toys, even gold! The third team would take them to the lab and examine them.  It is a very big process.           But how would you do all this? Well the archeologists have special help by their tools.  Here in this paragraph you will get to read about these tools.  When they dig up all the artifacts, they use a trowel which is most likely to be the most common tool in archeology, it is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.  They also use a skim shovel which has a flat edge used to remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.  If you find dirt on a artifact you would use whisk and dustpan or a knife to scrape dirt around the artifacts.  To carry the artifacts to the lab you could use a wheelbarrow.          That is a job of a archeologist, you could be a archeologist someday.  You could start in your own backyard.  Just follow these steps and use the proper tools!

Item_Response: Archeologists                    Archeologists are people who study things from the past. Archeologists uncover dinosaur    fossils, plant fossils, old colonies, old houses and the items inside of it, sometimes human bones, and much, much more.  They have many tool they use to uncover these artifacts. They use picks and shovels to dig. They also use whisks and dustpans to brush dirt off of the artifacts, they use knifes for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. They also use wheelbarrows to move items from one place to another. They use much, Much, MUCH, more tools than this.             Some interesting artifacts the archeologists have found is Fort James. In fort James in 1861 archeologists found armor and weapons buried under the ground.  A hundred years or so later a group effort to find the spot where the fort was built. They studied the area for 5 years. Eventually they found fort James.           The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where the fort's wall used to be. With all the stories they heard and pictures they had seen they knew that the fort was shaped like a triangle. The fort went all the way to the river. There they found small ledges over the water. They soon found out they were cannons. Now the archeologist group finds about a million items a year. They find things like pottery,tools, coins, and children's toys.           Archeologists are very important. With out them we would not know about the past. You would not know what dinosaurs may have looked like because they would not have uncovered all of their bones. You wouldn't know what kind of tools the old colonists once used because they never would have found them. Archeologists are very important.                                                                                THE END!

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist              The archeologist's main job is to uncover artifacts. They help know what was here on Earth hundreds of years ago. We know what we know about Earth because of them.           What does archeologists study? Why, anything you can dig up from the ground, they study. Fossils were found by them. We know that dinosaurs once roamed Earth because they discovered them.            Don't think this is an easy job, because it isn't. It involves hours and hours of digging, sometimes just to find a pile of dirt. But don't think it isn't a fun job, because it is. You might discover a new species that was extinct! The possibilities are endless!            Here are some things you probably need to know if you want to become an archeologist:   Patience-You won't find something in a day. Teamwork- You can't dig, take pictures, and wheel artifacts all at the same time! Science-after all, an archeologist is a type of scientist! Math-measuring bones, finding area, all of this plus more is what you will need to do math-wise.           Some tools an archeologist uses are:   Shovel (we all know what that is) Picks (much bigger than toothpicks) Knife (not the kitchen ones your mom uses) Wheelbarrow (not to ride in) Skim Shovel (Not skim milk. Skim meaning 'to remove small surface') Trowel (midget shovel you probably used when you were gardening as a kid)            Did you always enjoy playing in the garden or sandbox, hiding objects and digging them up again? Well, it sounds like the archeologist job is good for you!

Item_Response: An archeologists job is to study objects from the past.  Most archeologists are interested in the study of history.  Archeologists once discovered James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia.  Their job was to dig up and discover objects from the past.  Once they do that they study the objects.  Today the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year.                  Archeologists have helped historians know more about Washington as a boy because of recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home.  They have found lots of Washington's house by digging them up.  They know it's his house because they found clay pipes that he smoked.  Also they found burnt pottery and records say that Washington had a fireplace.  That means that there had been a fire that occured.                  Archeologists used many tools during their digs.  They helped them with many things.  They start digs using apick and shovel.  They help archeologists dig into the earth close to the artifacts.  A skim shovel is used for removing thin layers of soil.  When you are done using the skim shovel, you can use a whisk and dustpan to brush off the extra dirt.  If you find objects you can use a wheelbarrow to move the objects from place to place.  A trowel is the most common tool.  it scrapes and cuts to view the different layers of soil.  As you can see an archeologist's job isn't allways fun.

Item_Response: Sweat runs down my face as I dig my shovel into the Earth once again. Today is a very hot day and I am sweating like crazy, but i work through it. I am digging at Ferry Farm trying to find some information about George Washington's past. I am about 30 feet deep into the Earth and my shovel hits something.        I yell for my boss Logan, 'Logan, come here! I think i found something! Come quick and bring the whisk!'. Logan comes a few seconds later and he brought me the whisk. 'What did you find?', he asked. 'I... I don't know exactly', I said. I brush some dirt out of my way with my whisk and I tell Logan, ' I think it might be a piece of burnt pottery. Can you go get me the trowel please?'. 'Sure. i will be right back.', he reply's.         When Logan returns with the trowel he also brings me a water. ' Here is the trowel. I brought you a water also.', he says.   I reply back, ' Thanks.'. I take a sip of water and grab my trowel. I find where the two sides of the pottery is and start digging under it on the right side of the piece.          After about 5 minuets i get the burnt pottery out of the dirt. I scrape some dirt off with my whisk. I can now see what was on he pot. It looked like it was a family standing in the middle of a huge empty field filled with growing flowers. Logan snatched it out of my hand and said ' Great work Riley. After 3 weeks of digging you are the first person that found something. Go ahead and take the rest of the week off. You need it.'. I grin and say 'Thank you'. Logan nods and walks away with the pottery in his pocket. I climb up and out of my hole and walk home.           I take a drink of my water and turn he corner, climb up the wooden steps into my cool house. I lay down on my couch and fall asleep.

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist               An archeologist has a very important job. Their job is to dig up artifacts from the past, so we can learn about history. A lot of archeologists dig to solve mysteries, like when a group of archeologists found Fort James.       Archeologists wanted to see if they could uncover anything from Fort James. In 1861, the first artifacts were found. They discovered armor and weapons. They also uncovered the floors of buildings. After about 100 years a group effort tried to find the exact spot where Fort James was built. After that, The National Park Service led a 5 year study of the area. They wanted to figure out how the land was used. People used computer mapping software, to create an image of the area. Then they finally found James Fort! A set of marks on the ground was the first thing that they found. The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. Because of all the stories they had heard and the drawings they had made, archeologists knew that the fort was shaped like a triangle.       Other times, archeologists dig to find out how people lived a long time ago. Many archeologists wanted to find out more about George Washington. So, they decided to figure out where he lived, and dig up some things from his past.       On Ferry Farm, people have been living there for over 12,000 years. It's a perfect place to build a home. It's not surprising that George Washington's father moved his family there, when George was only 6 years old. George's house was long gone, so no one knew where his actual house was loacated. But archeologists belived that the stone base under the house was still there. In 2003 they started digging. They finally found it, but it took over a year. The kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses, were the first things they found. A few years later, they found the main farmhouse. On the Ferry Farm land, at least 4 other houses, have been built. They needed to find proof that this was George Washington's farmhouse. Records show that in George Washington's house, there was a fire. Burnt pottery was found by the diggers. That probably means that a fire occured there. A clay pipe was also found there. George Washington smoked clay pipes, so there was more proof.       For archeologists to find all of that stuff, they need the right tools. Here are some of the tools that archeolgists use.       Pick and Shovel: They are used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts.       Whisk and Dustpan: They are used to brush dirt off of the artifacts, and clear away dirt from the excavation site.       Knife: It is used for careful digging, and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.       Wheelbarrow: It is used to move items form one place to another, or to carry dirt away from the excavation site.       Skim Shovel: It is a shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.       Trowel: It is probaby the most common tool used in archeology. It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.       Now you know more about the job of an archeologist. It is much more than just digging in the dirt. They uncover articfacts so we can learn about history.

Item_Response: Archeologists       Archeologists use their knowledge to find interesting artifacts that belonged to people long ago. Such as Fort James, and George Washington. Archeologists use tools such as pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, a knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel.       They discover artifacts everyday. Some belonged to famous artists, and some belonged to average people. Some common artifacts archeologists find are coins, bullets, old toys, or even pieces of jewelry. Some artifacts might be worth millions, others might be worth nothing, but they are all connected to ancient history.       The tools that the archeologists use are very helpful because if they didn't have the tools, and they would have to do it by hand then it would take them double the time it took them with the tools. Using some of the tools isn't always easy and fast to do, but it certainly is cautious. Perhaps the land is unstable and it is an ancient burial site, they would want to disturb them. Though some tools do work fast and is worth digging. The pick and shovel would probably need upper body strength, but it would get the job done. The whisk and dustpan would maybe take a long time to accomplish a find, but once again it would get the job done safely. The knife would get the dirt off around the artifact. The wheelbarrow might be unnecessary to use unless the artifact was to be big for someone to be unable to carry it. They skim shovel would be cautious not to hit something that was not supposed to be hit, because the shovel would be too thin, it can take a thin layer of soil. The trowel would be the most useful tool that the archeologists could use for most parts of their dig.       Artifacts that are buried in most occasions are either rare, valuable or even a collectable. Archeologists usually find more than one item in one dig session, so the more items they find the more valuable or collectable. Usually people who are more elder have more artifacts, they will usually keep them from their childhood. There are two shows called Pawn Stars, and another on called American Pickers. Item_Response: The Job of An Archeologist        The job of an archeologist can be tiresome and time consuming but it can also be fun and exciting.An Archeologists job is very important when uncovering some of histories darkest or lightest secrets.Archeologists can't work alone there can be up to thirty five people in one team!The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track down what is underground. The information is recorded so people know what it looked like before they started digging.Then their is another team that starts the digging the place where they dig at is called a dig.Those archeologists start digging with what are called skim shovels these shovels are flat, small, and sharp so they can remove thin layers of soil one at a time.That soil is placed in a box with a half screen at the bottom that let's the artifacts stay in.       Tools used by Archeologists    Archeologists use many tools during their work time.One the most common tools they use is the trowel it is used to scrape and cut to view different layers of soil.The pick and the shovel is used to start most digs and to dig into the earth close to artifacts.The whisk and the dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.Then their is the knife it is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.The other type of shovel is called the skim shovel mentioned earlier. The skim shovel is a shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.Last but not least is the wheelbarrow used to move items from one place to another or to carry away dirt away from the excavation site.        Archeologists have a important job that comes with pros and cons one of the pros is finding a new artifact one of the cons is that all the digging can be very tiresome and time consuming.Many objects that archeologists find are sometimes put in museums.The job of an archeologists is easy and sometimes can be hard.With all the tools that archeologists use they are most likely to find at least one artifact each day of their time with a new excavation site.

Item_Response: The Job Of An Archeologist                    The job of an archeologist is to dig up fossils or valuables from the past time. This may be a tricky job,? but some things you might need to know before if you want to an archeologist if you have to have the patience to work and examine little art fossils or valuable thing that are very rare; you might also need to know a lot about fossils, another thing you will need to know or be if you would like to be an archeologist is you cant be afraid of dirt and mud or dislike it because you will be working with it a lot. Archeologist also have to work with all different types of tools which include picks and shovels, whisks and dust pans, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim shovel, and a trowel.               The reason you will be working with dirt and mud a lot is when you find fossils you mainly find them in mud or dirt or dust right? They aren't always clean, so when your assignment is to find a fossil your not just gonna walk around and find a fossil you actually have to the work; that involves you have to get you fingers into mud and start digging and trying to find fossils or objects.               The tools that you are going to need if your an archeologist are a pick and a shovel, a whisk and a dustpan, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim shovel, and a trowel. The pick and shovel are used for digging far in to find the fossil because they are so sharp. The whisk and dustpan is used for if the artifact or fossil has dust or mud on it the whisk and dustpan takes it all off so the fossil/artifact is not dirty anymore. The knife is used for cutting around the artifact and getting all the excess mud/dirt off of the artifact. The wheelbarrow is used to carry the fossils from place to place, or to carry the dirt that the archeologists dug through. Because the skim shovel is so thin it is used to take layer by layer off without breaking the mud/dirt so if there is a fossil it doesn't break because the archeologists don't know what layer it can we on.  Lastly, the trowel is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of mud/soil to check if they have any fossils or objects in them.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist                    An archeologist is someone who has the desire to learn about the past by, discovering new artifacts, classifying them and, every archeologist must have perseverance.  When you are in a search team you are split up in to separate groups that work together. One group does the the digging, they use many tools to accomplish this task without breaking anything. Another group classify the objects.  The last group maps the excavation site.  Being an archeologist takes lots of team work.                    To begin a search for answers from the past, researchers must use evidence from today to find a reasonable place to dig.  They do this by taking what they know and putting the knowledge together and getting the approximate location where the artifact is.  For example if you are trying to find your favorite toy because you lost it, you would use the information you know to find it.  Lets say you know the your little brother really likes your toy, but you never let him play with it, so based on this information you could see if your little brother has it.  archeologists also use 3D computers to map what is under them.  This is how archeologists find the approximate location of where the artifact they are trying to find is.                                                                                                                                                                              Digging for the artifact is hard work because you can not use a big excavator to dig the hole because it might break what you are looking for.  Instead you must use tools like the pick and shovel to start your dig, a knife to scrap dirt away from your artifact, a wheelbarrow to carry items and dirt away from the excavation site, you will also use a whisk and dust pan to clean artifacts, a skim shovel is also very handy for removing thin layers of dirt, and finally the trowel which is very important because it can scrape and cut different layers of soil.  This process can take weeks, months or even years to find an object that is not fake, and is valuable.                      Being an archeologist takes much perseverance, because if you do not find any thing important in your career, you will become very frustrated and you may rage quit.  All in all if you are an archeologist it is very rewarding, if you find something important, and it is a great job if you like exploring history.  This is what an archeologist does.

What they do is that they go to an old place that has been old for thousands and thousands of years like George Washington's old home. That's why when it comes to an archeologist, all of us count on him/her to do a very important job.There are also people who research the old place and tell the workers where the stuff is.       When the archeologist comes to an old place, the people that are back at the place have to tell the workers what they are digging for and where the things are. Lastly, you need a knife to cut off very hard and tiny substances stuck to a valuable thing.The job of an archeologist needs a lot of tools to help get the things they want.       Lastly, an archeologist needs to find a location to find where the valuable source is. That job isn't really for an archeologists. Its other workers that stay at the building to find things that are below or in a building or ground. An archeologist really relies on the workers at the building because without them, then they wouldn't ever find the substance. Item_Response: Being an Archeologist       Have you ever wondered about how it would be like to find and discover new artifacts everyday? Exciting, would it be? That's exactly what an archeologist does as a job. Archaeologists find new and unique artifact in different places, send them to the study labs,  and research more about that object. If you want to know more about these amazing world-traveled artifact hunters, read on!  Archeologists are very detailed and specific in whatever they do. They can sometimes use objects as big as wheelbarrows to dig soil to tiny wood picks for chipping of soil of very fragile objects. There are a lot of steps in digging up fossils and artifacts of the past. They first have to get together and entire team, which can take up to thirty-five people!         First of all, the first team maps the area using 3D that can track what is underground. The information is recorded on a piece of paper so everyone one can get a visual look about how the place was before they started to dig up the ground. Archeologists find many artifacts and materials that will show the past of the specific place. In this year, we have learned about a famous historical person named George Washington. There wasn't much information about where he lived and things about it. We wondered about what stuff and information was lying behind this historical man's childhood home. Coincidentally, we figured out that archeologists also had the same exact question! Some archeologists were digging at the dig to see if anything that was left behind was still right underneath the soil. One archeologist was digging and met a clay tube in the way. He thought about George Washington and remembered that he used clay tubes to smoke. This evidence proves that he was searching the correct place!         Furthermore, archaeologists have gone all around the world studying about its history and artifacts. They gone to Egypt to study tombs, pharaohs, and much more. They go into tobs and try to find as much as they can. They sometimes will also remove the tombs and study the precious wealth the body has been kept with. If lucky, they are allowed to unwrap the body to get a more detailed view of what the past was like when they were alive. They have also visited King's Valley to discover the dinosaur fossils. Using fine and detailed marterial, they easily find the truth and information of the life before us.         Being an archeologist can be hard work, but worth it. Item_Response: Archeologists                    Archeologists are so interesting, they get to discover the past of so many famous people . They get to use cool equipment to find things underground. To be an archeologist is a very hard but fun job. Your in charge of finding the history of so many magnificent things , which can be a big responsibility at sometimes. Archeologists will travel to places around the world to figure out its history. To get history you usually spit up in groups one for digging and the other one for actual digging. Archeologists have an important jobs.                  In 1994 a group of people interested in history started an archaeological project called the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was made to find out the secrets of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. Over 200 years ago people assumed that it had been flooded or washed away by a river, but some discovery's made proof it might still be around. The fort was built in 1607 when the settler came from England to have a better life. It was a good hide out from enemy and the boats are so close, so they docked them right there.                In 1861 the first object was found, they were armor, weapons and the floor of buildings. 100 years later they were on a mission to find the spot where the fort was built started. A National Park lead a study to figure out how the land was used. They started the computer to map out everything. That's when they finally found James Fort. From mark to mark the secret unraveled. So it turned out that after a couple hundred years it is possible to find interesting artifacts from way back.                George Washington is so interesting, but facts we know about him now are mostly about his time as the president and as a soldier. So some Archaeologists have set out to find more information on George Washington and about his childhood. When George Washington was six his father moved their family to Ferry Farm. It took the Archeologists over a year but they found the main base of the house. The Archeologists found some burnt pottery and part of a clay pipe the Archeologists knew that George Washington smoked clay pipes. So they had proof it was his house.           Archeologists have very hard jobs, but it also must be very interesting to be an Archeologist. They get to explore things no one has explored before and find out secrets about people and landmarks. Even though it takes a little while to find out those secrets and discoveries, it must be really worth it  It really must be amazing to be an Archeologist.

Item_Response: In this report I'm going to tell you what an archeologist does for a living. What an  archeologist does is that they look for things from the past, like acient tools and dinosaur bones.The diggers found pieces of burnt pottery. They suggested that a fire occured.They also found part of a clay pipe, Washington smoked a clay pipe.Archeologist can have up to 35 people on thier team.The first team mps out the area using a 3D computer, that can track what is underground. The next teamjust focuses on the digging.Those archeologist start the dig with what is called a skim shovel. These shovels are so small, flat, and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil, at one time. The dirt is placed in a box with a half-inch screem at the bottom.This lets the dirt fall out, but the artifacts to stay in.Also, the diggers use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologist use small shovels, pait brushes, and wooded picks to remove dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studing the objects that are found. Ferry Farms offers many opportunities for kids to get involved. Kids can expore the site, experience colonial life, and becaome aa junior archeologist.Digging around in dirt can give you more than just dusty jeans. The folks at Ferry Farms are bringing to life the county's first president in ways we have never seen. This is what an archeologist does.

Item_Response: Archeologists are people who are interested in studying the past.  They study things and people from long ago.  These archeologists find artifacts that can explain the life of people who lived long ago and can reveal secrets that none of us heard about.                                                                                                The archeologists find artifacts with the help of their tools.  Two of the tools are a pick and a shovel.  They are used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts.  Two more tools are a whisk and a dustpan, which are used to brush off dirt from the artifacts and clear dirt away from the excavation site.  The knife is used for careful digging and for scraping dirt around the artifacts.  Another tool is a trowel, which is probably the most common tool.  Archeologists use it to scrape and cut to veiw the different layers of the soil.  The skim shovel is also an important tool, and is made to remove thin layers of soil with each scoop.  The last tool is a wheelbarrow which is used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away.           The work of an archeologist is not that easy.  One job might take a very long time to acomplish.  The archeologists have to take their time if they want  to do everything the right way.  They divide the jobs into groups.  For example: one group maps an area, while another group, called a dig, starts digging.  The whole, thing can be slow and tiresome, but at least its worth it.           Sometimes, people have different opinions about what  happened to old things.  People might say that the object does not exist anymore.  Archeologists have found many things that people beleived did not exist.  Once, archeologists were searching for Fort James.  For over 200 years, people beleived that the river washed the fort away. When you become an archeologist, you form a group of usually about 35 people. The knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.  Another tool called the skim shovel is used carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.  Also, the trowel is used to scrape and cut to view different layers of soil, and is also the most common tool in archeology.  The wheelbarrow is ued to move items from one place to another or carry dirt away from the excavation site.  One of the other tools called the whisk and dustpan, are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site.  Finally, the pick and shovel are used to dig into the earth, which is close to the artifcts.  Archeologists use those tools for the meanings above.  To discover historical places, like the Ferry Farm and James Fort, archeologists must search around an area for a long time.  That may take from 1-5 years.  Once they find the place, they call it an excavation site.  After they discover the area, they search for historicaal remains or leftover things.  Each time archeologists find a item, they put it in a 3D computer, where it shows what the place might hve looked like when it was built new.  If you would like to be an archeologist, why not?  It is an amazing job that brings back the past!  Also, it's like an adventure........an adventure of excitement!

Item_Response: In 1994,a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project.It was designed to dicover the secrets of James Fort of Jamestown,Virginia.for over 200 years,people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.Some dicoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.                        The fort was built in 1607 when settlers from England came to start a new life.Most believed James Fort was by a river.It was easier to dock ships there,so it made sense that the settlers would choose  that spot.The first object were found in 1861 by Arecheologists. they found there armor and weapons and the floors of the building.Over 100 years later,a group had effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built.                           The National Park Service led a five-year study of th area to figure out how the land was used.they knew that this would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort.The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.That's when they finally found James Fort!The first thing they found  was a set of marks on the ground .The marks showed where the fort's  wall used to be.Between all the stories they heard and read, and drawings they made,the archeologists knew that the fort be the shape of a tiangle.They made maps They made maps and found out the fort stretched all the way out to the river.                                  Today,the groups finds nearly 1 million objects each year.The objects include pottery,tools,coins,and even metal toys for children.In the 1600s, people used to throw  their  trash down an unused well or into a pit.While digging in the the area,the archeologists found trash the settlers threw away,including the bones of animals they ate.The information learned from the objects helps us understand how the people in the James Fort lived.

Item_Response: Archeologists are people who dig up artifacts... and pretty cool ones too! First lets talk about James fort, Virginia. James fort was found in 1607, for over 200 years ( in the resent past PROBABLY about 2004 ) people have thought that Fort James was washed up by river.         The archeologists found their first artifact in 1861, it was armor and weapons. 100 years later they found where the fort was built. A national park service did a five year study of the area. BUT THEY FOUND JAMES FORT!!!                  First they found a few markings on the ground, that's how they knew where the walls used to be. the archeologists knew that the fort was shaped like a triangle, then they realized that the fort stretched all the way out to the river, and there was stone ledges built over the the river and they were meant to hold cannons.         Today, the same archeologists have found almost 1 million objects every year!! ( coins, pottery, tools and metal toys for children ) It is exciting to discover things from a long period of time in the past.          So now we have gotten to learn about what Archeologists actually do, and what amazing things they can find, so now lets talk about George Washington.              George Washington was the commander and chief of the continental soldiers in the Revolutionary War in the 17 hundreds. After the war George Washington refused to be crowned king so they made him the 1st president of the United States Of America, But does anyone know his real childhood?                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                In a place called Ferry Farm people have been living there for over 12,000 years! It is a perfect place to build a home so, of cores George's father Augustine moved there as well. George Washington was only six years old. The house was gone of cores but archeologists believe that the stone base under the house was still around. It took over one year to find the house. First they found the kitchen, slave quarters and storage houses. They found the farmhouse a few years later though. At least four other houses were built on Ferry Farm so they have to prove that this was George Washington's house/farm. They found part of a clay pipe, because we would smoke clay pipes.        For the diggers it took about two weeks to make a twenty five square foot section! The discoveries of Washington's home is important in many ways, like it give the people A better understanding of his past.         So we just looked at two major things including George Washington and James Fort but you actually know what tools archeologists use? first they will usually use a pick and shovel to dig into the earth. They will also use a whisk and a dustpan to clean off the artifacts, or a knife to dig carefully around the artifact. The leftover dirt is placed in a wheelbarrow and is taken away from the excavation site. To also dig they use a skim shovel or a trowel one removes a thin layer of dirt and another scrapes and cuts the dirt to view the different layers of soil.             So now you know about what archeologists do and how they do it.

Item_Response: Life as an Archeologist         Have you ever wondered what it's like to be an archeologist? Well if you're not up for tedious work, it might not be the job for you.       Many teams can work on a site, and there can be up to 35 people on a single team. That means if there were only three teams, there could already be more than a hundred people! However, before the digging even starts, the first team has to map out the area with 3D computers so that people after them will know what the site looked like before the digging started.        The actual process of digging is long and back-breaking. The dig is started with small shovels that are called skim shovels. Skim shovels are extremely sharp and flat, so they are able to remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. That soil is then screened - the soil is put in a box with a screen so that the dirt falls out and the artifacts stay in .        Another process that diggers use is troweling. Troweling archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to get rid of dirt. Troweling is extremely slow, however. It can take up to two weeks to dig a small 25-square-foot area!        A final team spends days in the lab studying the artifacts that are found to find out what they mean and how they are important to our history.

Item_Response: Have you ever wondered what it's like to be an archeologist? An archeologist must be very careful when doing his or her job. There are many tools that archeologists use in their work to get the job done, and archeologists find more artifacts each day.          The tools that an archeologist uses are very important. One of the most common tools used is a trowel. Trowels are used to scrape, cut, and view the layers of soil. Another tool used is a knife. Knives are used to cut dirt from around an artifact. A pick and shovel is also a tool that archeologists use. Most archeologists start digging with these.         There are more tools archeologists use, also. For instance, they use whisks and dustpans. Whisks and dustpans are to brush off dirt from artifacts and excavation sites. Archeologists use wheelbarrows, too. Wheelbarrowsare used to carry off items or dirt to one place to another. Another tool used is a skim shovel. They have very flat edges that can carefully scope away dirt. These tools are not the only tools that archeologists use, there are still many, many more!          There are many duties an archeologist must do, aswell. At an excavation site called Ferry Farms, groups of archeologists have been finding artifacts from George Washington's house! At Ferry Farms, there is at least thirty- five archeologists in one group. That's a lot of people! One group of archeologists will scope out an area by using 3D computers to see what's underground. Then they record the information so people will know what to expect when they start digging in that area. Another team focuses on digging, they call the place where they do the digging a dig.         The teams at Ferry Farms have found kitchens, slave quarters, and storage houses in 2004. Later, they found the main farmhouse. They also found pieces of burnt pottery and parts of clay pipes. Still today Ferry Farms is finding more and more artifacts from long ago.          In 1994, a group of archeologists that called themselves the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was made to find James Fort. People said that the fort had been washed away, but the project found clues that the fort was still around.          The National Park Service studied the area that was the exact place the fort had been built for five years. they tried to find out how the land was used. This helped them decide where to look for the fort. Soon after, James Fort was found! Marks on the ground showed where the walls had been, and there were also stone ledges that were built to hold cannons. Cellars, burial sites, and buildings were all found by the archeologists. Today, the group finds about one million artifacts a year!         Being an archeologist sounds like an amazing job! The tools seem fun to use. You can find great things if you just look hard enough and thats what archeologists do! This discovers more history than ever before!

So to find artifacts you must have the following tools used by archeologists: A pick and a shovel which most digs start with these two tools and there used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. Also a skim shovel is a shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Now this tool would be probably the most common tool an archeologist would use which is a trowel and it is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. These are the tools archeologists used while finding artifacts.          Here is a quick story of some archeologists working at George Washington's house to find artifacts about him. When they go out to find artifacts about him they go to his house from a long time ago, and they found burnt pottery, then this suggests a fire occured there. They also found a clay pipe, they found a clay pipe because Washington smoked clay pipes, so this discovery gives more proof it is the right house. So thats what archeologists do, they discover artifacts of people long ago. They want to know about there history.

Item_Response: There are many jobs to figure out what happened in history and an archeologist is a very important one.  Archeologists have a pretty complicated job, like they have many teams.  Sometimes the teams can have up to 35 people.  Being an archeologist is hard because you have many jobs to do and it will be very confusing with all the people running around.  These next few paragraphs will about the tools they use.            This first paragraph will be about a pick and a shovel and what their job is.  A pick is a very sharp tool that is used for to make a better hole to dig up.  A shovel is kinda the same but it is more round and it makes a deeper hole so its easier to find the artifact.  These are two tools that are useful to archeologists in team 1.             This second paragraph is about a whisk and a dustpan and what their job is.  A whisk is a metal brush that brushes dirt off the artifact to make the artifact easier to see.  A dustpan is a metal pan with a handle on one side and dirt can go into it so the dust doesn't go back onto the artifact.  These two tools are very important to team 2 because if dirt is still on the artifact then the scanning wont be correct.              This third paragraph is about a knife and a wheelbarrow and what their job is.  A knife is a very sharp tool that is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt away from around the artifacts.  A wheelbarrow is like a big bucket on wheels and is used to move items from one place to anther or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. These tools are very important tools.               This fourth paragraph is about a skim shovel and a trowel and what they do.  A skim shovel is a shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.  A trowel is a sharp hand held shovel that is probably the most common tool in archeology. It's used for scraping and cutting to view the different layers of soil. These to tools are most common and most used while an archeologist is working.                 There are many jobs in order to be an archeologist so that's why there are so many tools to help dig up artifacts so that people who want to know about people they can. Archeologist finds a lot about the past. Archeologist sometimes takes weeks to find something. They have to use devices to put tiny pieces of information together.They use a lot of tools too, such as :   pick and shovel- used to dig into the earth for artifacts whisk and dustpan- to brush off the artifacts and clear away the dirt knife- used to carefully dig wheelbarrow- used to move items to one place to the other skim shovel-used to carefully scrap thin layers of dirt and a trowel- to scrap or cut different layers of soil      Archeologist have even found Fort James. People thought that Fort James was washed away by a river but discoveries show that it might still be there.  Archeologist even learned about George Washington past. Even as a boy!           One thing Archeologist found was Fort James.  Fort James was in Jamestown, Virginia. For 200 years people thought that Fort James was washes away by a river. Archeologist found out that in 1607 England settlers came to start a new life. They did a 5 year study to make sure that it was Fort James.To today archeologist are finding 1 million objects a year!          Another thing Archeologist discovered was George Washington's home as a boy and older.  Nobody exactly knew where George Washington lived since the building was gone.  Archeologist have discovered that the stone based of the house should still be there.  In the year of 2003 archeologist started to dig in the land known as Ferry Farm. Item_Response: Archeology       Archeology is a difficult job. You need many different tools to go digging for artifacts. Also, you can't dig up an artifact overnight. It takes a lot of work. Archeologists have to map out the area that they want to dig and use 3D computers to track what's underground. Being an archeologist is no piece of cake, but you can benefit in many ways.       Once on the digging site, archeologists use many different kinds of tools to find what they are looking for. Skim shovels are used to take off a very small layer of dirt with each dig. Picks and shovels are used to dig deep to find artifacts. Knives are used to scrape dirt off artifacts and to do careful digging.Trowels are used to view the different layers of soil at a digging site. Whisks are used to brush away extra dirt, and wheelbarrows are used to move artifacts from one place to another.       Archeology isn't a walk in the park, but without it we would not know a lot about the past and the hardships that people went through. Not much would be known about anything! Without archeology, we would know nothing about our ancestors, so get out there and start digging!

Item_Response: My Report                  In 1994 a group interested in studying the past started to study Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was to uncover secrets of James Fort located in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 year, people thought that the fort had been washed away by river. Some discoveries hinted that it might still exist.                  The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how and when the land was used. The people studying used computer mapping software to make an image of the historical area, so they could picture where this all happened.                      That's when they finally found James Fort! It was amazing! First, they found a set of marks on the ground.those marks showed were the fort's walls used to be. Archeologists knew that the fort would be a triangle due to all the stories they heard, all the drawings they had seen, all the paintings and many more.                  Today, groups find nearly 1 million objects every year! Those objects include pottery, tools, coins and even toys made of metal for children. In the 1600's people used to throw their trash in a unused well or a big pit.                  It is so exciting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago. It gives us a piece of the past, how our ancestors lived and how America started as a very young country.

Item_Response: Digging up George Washington               You might think George Washington is boring ,but here are some things archeologists found out about George Washington's house and about him self. Most persons knew George when he was a soldier and a president. George's  father Augustine Washington, wanted to build their house in a land. So people wanted to find out were they used to live. How do archeologists find all of these things that were in George Washington's house all those yeears ago??           Teams work on a site. The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what's underground.  So the persons know what's actually underground. Another team works on what's really in the underground. Archeologists use skim shovels to remove thin layers of soil. It can take 2 weeks to dig a 25-square-foot. Another group spends timein the lab studiyng objects that are found. It helps historians learn about the type of life Colonial Americans lived.

Item_Response: The Job of an                       Archeologist   by: Adam Sellers                        I think the job of an archeologist is a hardworking, intersesting and useful job.       The job of an archeologist is an extremely hardworking job.  For example some people, all day long, dig, and dig, and dig using tools like a pickaxe, shovel, and a trowel, but it must be very exciting when you find something like a letter from the signers of the declaraition of independence to the King George III. If you are a lucky archeologist you may find interesting items. For example Colubus's map when he landed in America, or a piece of Indian pottery.       Sometimes, the really hardwork pays off when something interseting you find goes into a musiem and people can learn from the artifacts you dug up from the dirt.  If you find something like Leonardo da Vinci's plans for a submarine it could benifit mankind for years to come. Item_Response: Archeologist              have you ever wonder how it would feel like being an archeologist? I never did, but when I read about it I thought it was very interesting, and I bet you would think that to.First, lets talk about what are archeologist. Archeologist are people who travel around the world and look for unknown artifacts.When archeologist find something, it can change the past, or tell us more about history. For example, some archeologist found objects where George Washington's(our first general, and president of the United States) family lived. They taught us more about George Washington's past, and found many stuff that George Washington, him self, held. Another example, is about finding Fort James. Unlike the George Washington's story, Fort James actually toke longer. Soon many Archeologist found many valuable things at Fort James.                                               There are many types of tools you would need to be an archeologist. I'm going to tell you what the tools are by saying them in a list that will show the 6 common tools.       Pick and shovel Whisk and Dustpan Knife Wheelbarrow Skim Shovel  Towel                                  A Pick and Shovel are usually the most common   thing anyone can use. If you were an archeologist, you would use   these first if you found a spot to dig. these two tools dig into the earth to find the artifacts. If you get lucky and find an object, you'll notice that it's all dirty and dusty. This is where the whisk and dustpan come to the rescue. They are used to brush the artifact and clean away the sand and dirt. A knife isn't that important, so I'm not going to say a lot about it. The knife is only used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifact. If you have al lot of stuff, then a wheelbarrow is the perfect thing. A wheelbarrow is used for carrying stuff and taking the left over dirt to a different location. A skim shovel is used to carefully remove thin layers of soil with each scoop. Although, I said a pick and shovel are the most common thing, its actually the trowel which is the most common tool. it's used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. Now that I told you everything I could, I hope you will want learn more about being an archeologist

Item_Response: Finding Artifacts Preparation Guide                                                          by Juan Diaz                  If you are an archeologists and is going out to find historical artifacts, you'll need to prepare your trip.When you going to find artifacts you'll need to have the right tools for the job.If you bring the wrong tools, you may be in trouble.Just make sure you have food and water if your artifact finding trip will take at least a day or two.                                            The other tools you'll need are:                                        (1) A pick and a shovel                                         You'll need to dig in to find artifacts.                                          It wont just be lying on the ground.                                             (2) A whisk and dustpan.                                          Some of the most important parts of                                          the artifact may be covered with dirt or sand.                                          Use these to get the dirt and sand off.                                              (3) A knife                                           Usually used for digging a little bit of dirt or sand                                            off of an artifact.                                               (4) Wheelbarrow                                           Can be used for carrying the artifact if can't be carried                                            by hand.                                                (5) Skim Shovel                                             A shovel hat can scoop up a thin layer of dirt, sand, or soil.                                                (6) Trowel                                            This tool can scrap and cut different kind of layers of soil,                                            This tool is the most used tool by archeologists.                     Now that you have you're tools, it's time to find artifacts.But you need to make sure that you are in the right place to find the correct artifact.You'll also need a compass to help you find you're way around the area you're in.Make sure to dug deep enough if it's underground.But just be careful not to dig too deep or you'll reach the Earth's Core.                     Also, you'll need to make sure if you can get back above ground or you'll be in trouble indeed.Now you know you'll have to be prepared for the trip,what tools you need, and what to watch out for.Now if you are ready to find an artifact, just make sure you double check if you have everything you need.

Item_Response: The job of archeologist can be very hard because it can be hard having very many people with you.The first team uses 3D devices that can see under ground.The information is recorded so that people can see what it looks like before they dig it up.The archeologists start their digging with a tool called skim shovels,these shovels are so small,flat,and sharp they can remove thin layers of soil ,one at a time.That soil is then placed in a box with a half inch screen at the bottom,this lets the soil fall out and the artifacts stay in.              Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels,paint brushes,and woodenpicks to remove dirt.It can take up to two weeks to dig up a 25-square-foot section. Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it. The discovery of Washington's home is important for many reasons. First, it gives the citizens of the United States a better understanding of who George was before he became famous. We also began to know why he made the decisions he did. Another thing it does is help historians learn about the type of life Colonial Americans lived. All of these things are key parts of our past as Americans.  Most of what we know about George Washington comes from his time as a soilder and president. Biographies don't have very much information about his childhood. Item_Response: An archeologist finds artifacts in old historic buildings. Like for example Fort James when a team would find any objects an archeologist would study the item to figure out the lifestyle back then. It is fun to learn about our ancestors that lived long ago. It tells us about a piece of our past about people who lived long ago.          When they first found fort James they found marks where the walls used to be an archeologist would study the marks to learn more about fort James. With the archeologists hard work they figured out the building was shaped like a triangle. Archeologists also found stone ledges over the river to hold canons. The archeologists found many more things at fort James like cellars and buildings.            Today the archeologist group finds about 1 million objects every year. They find things like pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys. While digging they found where they threw their garbage including bones from a animal that they ate. thanks to archeologists we know how the people in fort James lived.              Most of what we know about George Washington's childhood comes from archeologists. They found out that in Georges childhood he lived on the land known as the Ferry Farm George was only six when they moved their.               At the time know one knew exactly where Georges house really was. But archeologists believed that the houses stone base was stile there underground. They started to dig in 2003 and found it in about 2004. The first buildings they found was the kitchens, slave quarters, and storage houses. They also found the main farm house a few years later.                Their were more than one house on the Ferry Farm at the time so they had to find proof that this was George Washington's house. They looked at records of George Washingtons past. They found that he had a fire in his house so they searched for burnt items. they found burnt pottery. They also found part of a clay pipe and records show that George smoked clay pipes. This discovery gives us proof that George Washington did live there.                If all these discoveries weren't made we wouldn't know as much about the past as we know today. Archeologists are very important they take their time to teach us more about are world.

Item_Response: Archeologists are very important people. They uncover things from our past and are a big part of finding out more about history. They have helped us learn about the Jamestown Colony and George Washington's life. Here are some examples of what archeologists do.        Archeologists go to areas such as the location of Jamestown to find information about the colony. Such as in Source #1, archeologists must first predict where James Fort was located to find proof it still exsisted. Once they used the appropriate software, they eventually found the fort and set off to work.       They learned the fort stretched to the river, found burial sites, cellars, and a few buildings, and also found objects the colony used. Archeologists discovered things such as pottery, tools, and metal toys for the childen. Archeologists found out that colonists threw their trash in a well or pit; they found things such as bones of animals they had eaten. They found many discoveries in the fort.       Another example of how archeologists are important is the discovery of where George Washington lived. As it says in Source #2,it took over a year to find proof of where he lived. Archeologists found the kitchen, slave quarters, storage houses, and eventually the main farmhouse. There was one problem though, about 4 other houses were on Ferry Farm land and the archeologists needed proof that this was Washington's farmhouse. It was said there had been a fire in the house, so archeologists looked in the farmhouse and found part of a clay pipe. Archeologists knew that Washington smoked clay pipes, so they knew had more proof this was the right house.       These are 2 reasons archeologists are important, they discover many things are past and find locations for them to study and find more information about. They help us learn about the past and they deserve a thumbs up.
