Item_Response: For History Day, I am doing my report on archeologist.  Archeologist are people who study things from the past, they might dig holes and look for valuable objects, for example a dinosaur bone.        Some of the archeologist that I researched were studying James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia.  The fort was built in 1607 when the settlers came from England to start a new life in the new Americas.  Some people thought that the fort was built near the river but the archeologist found weapons and armour farther away.        Finally the archeologist found the fort.  The fort had triangle walls that stretched all the way to the river.  There were ten different buildings, lots of burial sites, and cellars.        Today the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year. The objects are pottery tools, metal tools. Because of the archeologist we know that the settlers attacked the Powhatan Indians.  It was exciting for the archeologist to find all the things that the Indians and the settlers used.       Another group of archeologist that I studied researched George Washington's house and looked for valuable things that George Washington used.  They knew it was George's house because the house had a clay pipe in it and he smoked clay pipes.        The different tools that the archeologist use to find objects in George Washington's house are a skim shovel, a throwel, 3D computer, and a half inch screen box. The skim shovel is used for the actual digging.  A throwel is used for digging 25 square foot holes, which can take up to two weeks to finish.  The 3D computer is used for tracking whats underground.  The half inch screen box is used to hold the soil.       Archeologist are important to find important things from our past.

Item_Response: Have you ever seen the movies of Indiana Jones? Well, those movies are about a college professor who also happens to be an archeologist. He goes on crazy missions looking for lost riches. But no, an archeologist is not someone who goes to exotic places and find secret rooms and burial chambers.          The definition of an archeologist a scientist who studies the past. It's kind of like a historian, except historians read the books about life in the past. As for archeologists, they are there to get dirty. All they want is information about the past. And, to make a difference, people don't sit down. No sir, they get up and make a difference. They do travel to interesting places, but not to relax. Oh no, they are there to discover the past, comparing life now and then.          Some of the things they want to figure out is how people lived back in time, what were some of the daily materials and items they used, their techniques for building, farming, cooking, and other stuff like that. The first step in archeology is not to know who the people they are studying are, but where they lived. For example, the archeologists who wanted to study Jamestown, thought that the area where the colonists from Jamestown lived, had been washed away by a river. But that rumor didn't stop them from investigating. Only a true archeologist would prove it to themselves.          And lucky they decided to prove it to themselves, or archeologists wouldn't have found all the amazing artifacts in the area where people believed Jamestown had once stood. Some of the things they  dug out of the ground include uncovered armor, weapons, floors of buildings, eleven cellars, tons of burial grounds, ten crumbled buildings, pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children! As for George Washington's land where he lived, it did take some time to do, but they did find the Washington's land. They found the kitchen, slave quarters, storage houses, and later on the main farmhouse. Archeologists also have to do research, like when they needed to know if the buildings they found on Washingtons land was their house. So, they found records that showed that the Washingtons had a fire in the house, which mached the burnt pottery they found, and that was proof enough.         Archeologists have to use may different tools to do their job, like a pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarow, skim shovel and trowels. It is a slow process, and you must have patience, but in the end of a discovery, you are a hero to be an american, by knowing so much about our countries past. And that, my friend, is the life of a true archeologist.

Item_Response: A Job as an Archeologist       By Maddy Roelofs             Have you ever wondered how we know so much about well-known people's pasts? Well, if you want to know, I'll tell you a little bit about working as an archeologist. First things first. What is an archeologist?         An archeologist is a person who tries to find artifacts that famous people from the past, like George Washington, used. Then, they study the artifacts to find more information about that person and their life as a child. Archeologists don't work by themselves, they work in groups.These groups are called teams. There are many teams working on one site and can be up to 35 people on a team. Each team works on something different. One team uses 3D computers that can track things underground to map out the area. This way, people know where to start digging. The second group does the actual digging. They use special tools to help them. For example, the skim shovel is a small, flat, sharp shovel which they use to remove thin layers of soil. After, the soil is put in a box with a screen at the bottom so the soil will fall through and the artifacts will stay in. The last team studies the artifacts in a lab for days. It takes a long time to complete the process of digging and studing the objects but helps us understand more about well-known people!         Overall, a job as an archeologist would be tiring but you would also find some cool artifacts from history and learn more about famous people from the past!

Item_Response: Archeologists!           Have you ever wondered what it was like to live long ago? If so you might want to consider a job as an archeologist. This job presents an opportunity to learn all sorts of things about famous people who came before you.              An archeologist's job is very important. They devote their time to finding out more about the lives and families of famous people that we don't know much about. For example, we knew little about where Gorge Washington grew up, until archeologists excavated the Ferry Farm site. While we knew much about his time as a soldier and president, as well as his life at his family home at Mount Vernon archeologists made it possible to know what he experienced as a child. this is important because his child life influenced many of the important decisions he made.               Another example is the dig site at Fort James. a lot of people thought that it was swept away by the river, but recent discoveries suggest otherwise. A group of devoted archeologists spent many weeks excavating a huge amount of land that led to recent discoveries at the site of Fort James.                     While many people thought that the inner buildings of the fort were close to the river, so it would be easier to dock ships archeologists have discovered that they were located further away for protection from enemy ships. they have also discovered what remains of a stone wall that would have held cannons to ward off intruders.                 These discoveries have made it possible to learn many things about the Fort and the people who lived in it. They couldn't have done it without their tools, though. To give you a better idea of what the archeologists would have used to ,make these important discoveries here is a run down of the tools for you.                  They would start with a skim shovel to take off the thin levels of to soil, and to locate the artifacts that were left close to the surface. Then they would use regular shovels to pick up dirt to drop into a half inch screen, that let the dirt fall out, but left the artifacts in. Next they would load the dirt into a wheelbarrow to be moved to a different site to be examined for any small artifacts that slipped through holes in the screen.  someone will then bring the artifacts to a lab where groups of scientists will spend weeks looking over them, and figuring out what they mean. They then use trowels to cut soil samples to be examined by soil scientists. There are many other tools, but these are the main ones. They have to be so careful digging that it can take over two weeks to clear a twenty-five foot section!                  Now that you know about the many trials and rewards that make up the job of an archeologist, think about it. We should really be thankful that there are people out there that are devoted enough to take time away from their families to make the important discoveries that they do. Do you think that you have the diligence to become one?

Item_Response: The Life Of An Archeologist   By: Lily Marie Murray            Have you ever wondered what the life of an archeologist would be? The life of an archeologist is hard and interesting too! Long hours, lots of digging and searching for where these places are.  Sometimes it takes more than a year or two to find the place, such as Fort James. They had to dig underground to find where it was! Usually, it is totally worth it. Finding new things about different people and places. Like their childhood, history, lives, learn how they became famous, what decisions they made, what type of life they had, and much, much more.            One of there projects was Finding Fort James. For more than 200 years, everyone thought that it had been washed away by some river near by. Some say, there are some discoveries in the area said it might still be around. The fort was built in 1607. That was when English settlers came to start a new life. The first objects that were found was in 1861. They uncovered armor and weapons. Then, they found what they were looking for.......the floors of the buildings. Over about 100 years later, a group was trying to find the exact spot where the fort was first built and where it began!                The National Park Service helped construct a five year study of the area to find how all of the land was used and what could be built on it. They did this because they wanted proof that the fort was still here. People who helped with the study used special computer mapping software to make images of the area, maybe sort of like an X-ray. They finally found it! They found cellars to burial sites to buildings and much, much, more! Today, the group has found and dug up more than 1 million objects each year! They found pottery, tools, coins, and metal toys for kids!            One of the other projects they did was the past on Ferry Farm. Ferry Farm has been known for over 12,000 years. People have lived on Ferry Farm but do you know the most famous person that lived there?  Well, it was George Washington himself. He moved there with his family when he was six years old. No one knows exactly where they lived because the house is long gone. Archeologists think it is still there. They started digging in 2003. It took over a year , but of course they found it. They first found kitchens, slave quarters, and storage houses. Then, they finally found the main farmhouse a couple years later.            There were at least four other houses that were built on that land, so they needed to find the proof that this was George Washington's House for sure. The records showed that they had a fire in that house. What did they find? Burnt pottery! They also found a part of a clay pipe! Washington smoked clay pipes. After that, they knew that this was their house and there was a fire in the house.            How do you think the archeologists find this stuff in Washington's house? Well, it was a careful one. you could tell they were a pretty rich family from all the pottery and expensive stuff. They had several groups. The groups consists of 35 people at least on every team. One team maps the area using 3D computers that tracks what is underground. This is helpful so that the diggers know where to dig for the object and what it looks like.            Another team does the digging part. They are called the dig. They use a lot of tools. Let me describe them for you.   Pick and Shovel-Most digs start with these two tools. Used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. Whisk and Dustpan-Used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. Knife-Used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. Wheelbarrow-Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. Skim Shovel-A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Trowel-Probable the most common tool in archeology. Used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. Citation: Information from passage Tools Used by Archeologists                This helps us learn about our founding fathers and just pain old famous people and things. These are all part of Americas Past. We learn more about our history as a nation.            I would like and not like to be an archeologist.       Yes-I would like to because it would be fun to learn about our past and how it came to be the United States of America. To learn more about the people who helped the America be America, to be one Union not two. It would help to teach and learn more about our past, America's Past. No-I wouldn't like to be an archeologist because I can't stand to be somewhere at one time the whole time I need to move around. I like to be active and have that would be fun but it is too long to be there everday. It would also be a huge commitment, long hours, lots of digging, and searching. I guess just too much for me.            My conclusion is that an archeologists work is hard work, lots of digging, long hours, and searching too. All hard work but still it is fun and usually worth it! You find amazing things to learn about. Childhoods, family members, how wealthy they were, where they lived, history and much, much more. You will also find more artifacts, life, and history than you would in a book! Everything you find tells a story a house, pottery, clay pipes, are all artifacts that will tell a story about that person or place. It is an amazing job to have! You can also see more artifacts in museums because most artifacts are in cultural museums or history museums. You can find them anywhere!

Item_Response: Archeologists         By: Baylee West                 Archeologists are people who study objects from the past. They use Picks, Shovels, Whisks, dustpans, Knives, Wheelbarrows, Skim Shovels, and a Trowel. There can be up to thirty-five people on a team.                The first team can map the area by using 3D computers that people can track whats under ground. The information is recorded so that people will know what the item looks like before the archeologists start digging.               Another team has to focus on the actual digging, and the place were the team does the digging is called a Dig. The archeologists start to dig with a skim shovel. Skim shovels are so flat, small, and sharp that they can only remove thin layers of soil. That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the soil fall out while the the artifacts stay in.                 The diggers also use a process called troweling. Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove soil. It can take up to, two weeks to dig a twenty-five square foot section! The next team spends days and days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome.                     And that's the job of an Archeologist.   Hope you liked my biography (:   Sincerely, Baylee West

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is a carefully planned out job that requires patients, skill, and precision.  I shall explain what the job of an archeologist is like.  This will include how they find an area and what they find in the area that they plan to dig up.  It will also explain how they dig up an area and tools that they use.           Before the archeologists start excavating, they need to plan out and map the area they plan to dig up.  Using 3D computers, they can track what is underground.  This helps them see what the area was like before they started digging.  They try to make sure what they're going to excavate is still there by researching the area, but they still may not find what they wanted to find.  After this is done, they have to fly, drive, or sail to that area to begin the excavating process.           Once they are at the site, they begin to remove dirt by the process of troweling or using skim shovels to remove small pieces of dirt.  The work is very slow.  Once some objects are found they  brush dirt off them by using a whisk and dustbin.  Then, workers place them in a wheelbarrow to move them to another place. When the objects arrive, they are carefully studied for days.           Some things archeologists find may not mean much, such as a pair of broken scissors.  Some objects could help us learn more about someone or something.  If the object is a dinosaur bone it could help us discover a new species of dinosaur.   If they uncovered a brick in the desert, it could have been the brick from a pyramid.  Objects found from a famous person could change they way we look at him/her.           The job of an archeologist is a job in which you will sometimes not find what you are looking for.  You cannot let your hopes get too high, or you may be disappointed when you do not find want you wanted to.  It is also a rewarding job, considering what you find is an important object in history.  It is a job that can go either way, and can be disappointing and rewarding.  Overall, the job requires lots of patience, accuracy, and skill.

Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England   to start anew life.   Most believed that James Fort was built near a river. It was easier to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would   choose that spot. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was further away. The new spot probably gave the settlers   more protection from enemy ships. The first objects were found in 1861. Archeoligists, the name for scientist who study objects   frome the past, uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group effort   to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.       The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew that this would   help them decide where to look for proof of the fort.The people doingthe study used computer mapping software to make   an image of the area.Thats when they finally found James Fort!

Item_Response: Archeologists are very important people who help us discover the ways of living in the past, events that might've happened in the past, and to give people a better understanding of our world's history. What exactly is an archeologist? Well an archeologist is a person who spends there time in search of digging up artifacts from the past whether it is old pottery pieces, armor, weapons, tools, coins, or metal toys for children.                                                                                                                 You can't expect pottery from thousands of years ago to be in one whole piece, so if an archeologist is lucky enough to find all the pieces from pottery they most likely will spend their time gluing all the pieces together to discover more of what type of pottery people in the past made. Being an archeologist requires a lot of time and patience because you might not always find what you are looking for right away.                 How do archeologists find artifacts from the past? Well, each year many teams will work on a site where they're trying to find information. There can be up to 35 people on a team! One of the teams maps out the site using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The team that is digging can use the map that the 3D computers show so that they can know what it looks like underground before they start digging. The area the digging team does the digging is called a dig. The archeologists in this group start their dig by using Skim Shovels. That soil that they scoop up is then placed in a box with a half screen at the bottom. The half screen lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling which is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. Another team spends days in the lab studying the artifacts that were found. It takes a lot of people working together to discover our worlds past.                Archeologists use many tools to discover all these artifacts. As I mentioned earlier the group that does the digging uses a skim shovel. A skim shovel has a flat edge that is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soilwith each scoop. Another tool that the archeologists use is a pick and shovel which is a tool that most digs start with. The pick and shovel is used to dig into the earth, close to the objects. There are many tools that are used to brush away the dirt off of an artifact. One of those tools is a whisk and a dustpan. A whisk and a dustpan can also be used to clear away dirt from the excavation center. A knife also can be used to scrape away the dirt around an artifact. A knife can also be used for careful digging. A wheelbarrow is used to move items from one place to another, but can also be used like the whisk and dustpan to carry dirt away from the excavation site. The most common tool and archeologist uses is a trowel. A trowel is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of the soil. Archeologists use many tools to make their job a whole lot easier and accurate.                  Archeologists jobs are long, tiresome, and hard. It can take up to 2 weeks to dig a 25 square foot section. All those weeks add up when you are digging up a large space. It's definitely true that it takes time to actual dig up and discover the objects but to add on top of that, the time that it will take to study the objects, find out what they mean, and use other bits of information to tie in to the object that they had found. Archeologists must take their time and have patience to truly discover, enjoy, and appreciate what they have found.                 It is important, meaningful, and exciting for us to discover about our worlds past, and it's hard to do that without any kind of proof. These artifacts that our archeologists find show us the objects that were regularly used by people many years ago. All the artifacts in museums had to be discovered one way or another and they were dug up by archeologists! These artifacts give us a piece of our past and ties us to the the people who lived back then. These artifacts give us a better understanding of the United States past. The job of an archeologist is super important! We get to learn why a certain person made a certain decision from the objects they left behind. Without archeologists we wouldn't know any of this information and would be clueless. I hope you now understand why an archeologist's job is so significant! What would we do without our archeologists?

Item_Response: Finding Fort James    In 1994, a group of people interested in studying in the past .They wanted to do this because they wanted to discover the secrets of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years, people thought the he had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that he might be still around. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life . Most people thought James fort was built near the river. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The first objects were found in 1861.Archeologists who study objects from the past, uncovered armor and weapons. They discovered floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group of effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.   The National Park Service led 5yrs stjudy of the area to figure out how land was used. The people doing the study used computer mmapping software to make an image of the area. Thats when they finally found James fort. The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. the marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. Today, the group  finds nearly 1million objects include pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children.

Item_Response: Digging for History                 Have you ever wondered what archeologists do for their job? Well archeologists do mostly history. Archeologists started in 1944. They keep it on what they are looking for so the miners get an idea where the item there looking for is. To conclude, this team of archeologists starts the work by showing the miners where the piece of american history is..             Next, comes the second team of archeologists the miners. They do the mining by looking at the 3D computer to find out what they are searching and where it is. Then, they go looking for it and when they find it the just mine it out. They start mining by using a skim shovel. The skim shovels are small, flat, and sharp so they can remove the thin layers of soil one at a time. Then the archeologists use a process called trowling where they they will use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove the last layer of dirt. To conclude, these archeologists minewith different tools and find the american history pieces.              Last, the third or last team comes in to see what the miners found. They study the objects and try to find out what the miners have found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it. These type of miners must be patient for it's a long process.To conclude, these miners must have studied lots of hisory to find what the miners could have found.              Those are the three hardworking and tiresome archeologists job. To conclude, all teams of archeologists work really hard to discover new american history for us to learn about.

To use a wheelbarrow in a excavate you put the artifacts or excess dirt inside of it. Skim shovels are used to carefully remove a very thin layer of dirt with every scoop. Finally a trowel, probably the most frequently used tool, is used to  scrape/cut different layers of soil than the argeoligist studies the soil. The National Park Service led a 5 year study to find out how the land was used.The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.             Thats when they finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of markes on the ground the marks showed where the walls used to be they knew that the fort was shaped like a tringal. First, of all you have to dig , dig, and dig.With this job you either stay outside and dig or you stay outstide and study some things. I am here to talk about the diging part. These are the steps:first you find the perfect spot to dig. second you use a shovel thats really thin and sharp to just get up thin layers of dirt so you don't mess up any artifacts. third you carefully carry the extra dirt off the site with a wheelbarrow.fourth you bring the artifacts back to the lab for the other workers to study them. Archeologists recently did a search for things from George Washingtons childhood. Last,you get to work with some cool tools.Some of those cool tools are a wheelbarrow,knife,trowel, and a pick.The wheelbarrow is used to carry extra dirt off the site.The knife is used for careful digging and to remove some of the dried dirt of the artifacts.The trowel is the most common tool it is used to scrape or cut to see the different layers of soil.Last the pick is used to dig in close to artifacts in the earth.          As you can see being a Archeologist is a pretty amazing job. You get to dig all day long. Discover artifacts from famous peoples life.Last you get to work with really cool tools.So go be a Archeologist when you grow up!

Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                                                                     The job of an archeologist is to find ancient artifacts and valuables. They use many different tools such as,Pick and shovel, Whisk and Dustpan, A knife, Wheelbarrows, Skim shovels, And Trowels. But to get to work an arheologist needs to know what their looking for. Like, facts about Abraham Lincoln, Elvis Presley's guitar, or anything else that can tell us about the past.                First,(after they know what they want to find)they have to find a place to look for the item.To do this they use computer mapping software to make an image of the area. From that image archeologists can find clues such as marks,debris etc. After they find the area, they send in teams of 10-35 people. to use computers to find artifacts underground, and to dig out the area to find the mapped items. Finally, they use the artifact to tell them more about history.

Item_Response: In this report you will be learning about the job of an archeologist. Archeologists find information about people in the past who are not living now. Some people might think their job is easy and some people think it is hard. It is just your opinion but i think their job is hard because sometimes it takes you a long time to really find any artifacts. In these paragraphs you will learn about what tools they use, how they use them, and what they do.        The tools that archeologists use are picks and shovels, a whisk and dustpan, a knife, wheelbarrows, skim shovels, and a trowel. Most digs start with picks and shovels. They are used to dig into the ground and find the artifacts they are looking for. A whisk and a dustpan are used to brush the dirt off of artifacts. A knife is used to dig carefully and scrape dirt off of the artifacts. A wheelbarrow is used to move artifacts from one place to another. Skim shovels are shovels with a flat edge used to remove a very thin layer of dirt carefully. The last tool that an archeologist uses is a trowel. Trowels are used to scrape and cut the dirt to view the different layers of dirt.        Archeologists find artifacts by digging for long periods of time. They have to plan how to and where to dig before they start digging for real. Sometimes they use a 3D computer to track and map what is underground. Some archeologists just start digging in the first place and see what they find. If they use a 3D computer to map the area out they have to record the information of where to dig so they know what the artifact looks like before they start digging. If they are focusing on the actual digging, they start with skim shovels. Archeologist then put the little layers of soil dug up in boxes with half-inched screens on the bottoms. This lets soil go through the screen and leaves back artifacts.        This report was about the job of an archeologist. Now you know what type of tools they use and how they use them. It takes a few years sometimes to finish an area.If I wrote this report again I would write it about how archeologists earn their job. Since I learned more about being an archeologists I believe it would be fun to have this job.

Item_Response: The Job of an archeologist!!!                                                 By:Rebecca Karel        My name is Rebecca Karel. I am 11 years old. I go to Woodfeilds Elementry. In this report I will teach you about the job of an archeologist. I decided to pick ( I did not really pick it.) this topic because I did not know much about them. In the report you will learn about how archeologists found Fort James, how archeologists learned more about George Washington's child hood, and about the tools used by archeologists. I hope you enjoy my report.        First in 1994 a group of people got together so they could study the past of  James Fort in Jamestown. They wanted to set up an archaeological project. For over two huundred years people thought the town had been detroyed, but some discoveries were found that revealed that it might still be there.When the archeologists finnally found the area where the fort was they started digging.The first objects were found in 1861, when   archeologists found weapons, and armor.One hundred years after that they found some more. Now we have found over 1 millon things, including pots, coins, toys, and tools.        Now that we have talked about Fort James, let us discuss how archeologists helped us find more about George Washington. Archeologists found where Washington lived as a child, it took them a couple years but they did it. A few houses had been discovered so they looked for more. They found burnt pottery and a clay pipe so they confirmed that that location was were Washington lived. Archeologists work on a team to find artifacts, so thirty-five people can be on a team.It takes sevearl  teams to find an artifact.For example it can take up to two weeks or more to dig an twenty-five square foot area.thats why it is a big deal if, say you found one tiny bit of burnt pottery, scientists cound scan that pottery and find out a lot about where that pottery has been. That is how we found out about George Washington's childhood.        Archeologists have to have tools when they find artifacts. One of their tools are the pick and shovel. Archeologists use the pick and shovel to dig into the the Earth to find artifacts.Archeologists also use the Wisk and dustpan. They use these items to brush of dirt  from the artifacts. Archeologists use the knife as one of their tools too. The knife helps them scrape dirt away from the artifact. A lot of archeologists use the wheelbarow to help them carry dirt away from where they are digging, it also helps them carry the artifacts away from the excavation site. Most archeologists use the Skim shovel to dig into the soil to take a slim layer of soil off, they are able to do this bacause the skim shovel has a flat edge. The most common tool that archeologists use is the Trowel. The Trowel is used to cut the different layers of soil off so you can see them. Those are some of the tools that archeologists use.        This report was about the job of an archeologist. Item_Response: The Job of an Archeologist                                                                       by Isabella Yu             Have you ever heard of an archeologist? An archeologist is a person who discovers and digs up artifacts, items of the past, and fossils. Archeologists can use special tools to help them discover artifacts and fossils. They also have a procedure and they can dig up certain items.         Some tools that archeologists use are picks, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovels, and trowels. The pick and shovel are used to dig up the soil above where something might be. The whisk and dustpan are used to brush off dust and dirt. Wheelbarrows were used to move dirt or items to another place. A skim shovel is used to remove very thin layers of soil. The trowel scrapes and cuts layers of soil.         To dig up artifacts in a certain area, a team of archeologists first map out a place to find out what is underground. Then, another group of archeologists do the actual digging for items in the area that is mapped out. They use the skim shovel to remove layers of soil to find items. Archeolgists use another method called troweling too. troweling uses shovels, brushes, and picks to remove dirt. After the artifacts are found, another team of archeologists studies the objects that the second team found.         Most things archeologists will find are artifacts and the fossilized bones of animals. Archeologists can find ancient pottery, paintings, metal items, tombs, and toys. If archeologists are searching for fossils, they can find the remains of dinosaurs and long-ago plants and animals. There are some places that are good sources of fossils and artifacts, such as the La Brea Tar Pits in Southern California, or the Egyptian pyramids.         Being an archeologist can be fun, but it can also be dull and tiring, especially if you can not find anything. But if an archeologist finds something fascinating, like King Tut's coffin, he/she could become world renowned. Archeology is an interesting subject.

Item_Response: What are Archeologists?  Well, and archeologist is a person who has a thrilling job of digging up artifacts.  So you might also be asking, what are artifacts?  Well, artifacts are old, or historic items, used or cherished a long time ago.  It doesn't nessasarly have to be from someone who passed away, but artifacts, is similar to the word, 'ancient.' So archeologists are usually sent to homes or old buildings but to be honest, you could find them anywhere trying to dig up useful artifacts.  So when they arrive at the location, they bring in the equipment they need such as, a pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knives, a wheelbarrow, and a trowel.  These are all tools they use to dig up the artifacts.  Digging meaning, 'recovering, or surfacing.'  So of course you need to dig up dirt, or gravel to get the the artifact.  So, they would use the Pick, shovel, and skim shovel to start their process.  The knife comes in handy for careful digging. I think these are the tools yo find or discover or buid or breakdown, and those tools are Pickovel, Whiskustpan, Knife, Wheelbarrow, Skim Shovel,and a Trowel. It semms like alot doesn't it , but it   really isn't that much.       There are many Sources like Source#1, Source#2, and Source#3. But back to those tools im going give definitions. OK so umm.... Pick & Shovel: Most digs start  with these two tools.Used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. Whisk & Dustpan: Used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away form the dirt from the excavation site. Knife: Used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. Wheelbarrow: Used to move items from one place to another or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. Skim Shovel: A shovel with a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer soil with each scoop. Trowel: Probably the most common tool in archeology. Used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.       Source#1       This article about how archeologists find artifacts at Jamestown Island is a based on information. Item_Response: Being An Archeologist      Being an archeologist can be a tough job. Spending weeks on end digging. But, it can also be a fun job. Like when you find ancient burrial grouds or maybe a tomb with an egytian phero in it. That's always exciting. Well, here are some other amazing digs that made the job worth-while.           In 1994, some people interested in the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project. They wanted to find the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For 200 years, everyone thought the fort had been taken by the river. But some things found in the area hinted that it might still be there. The fort was made in 1607, at the same time the English Settlers came. The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists discovered armor and weapons. They also found the floors of buildings.          About 100 years later, a group set out to find the exact spot where the fort had been built. The people diong the study used computer mapping to create a picture of the area. And that's when they found James Fort! The first thing they found were marks on the ground. They showed where the walls used to be. From everything they had researched, they knew the fort would be triangle shaped. They also found that it streched to the river. Today the archeologists find about 1 million objects every year!          Now you can see why being an archeologist is so fun. I mean, they found a whole forrt! Well, I hope you enjoyed.

Item_Response: An Archeologist's Job                The job of an archeologist is an intresting job. They get to see all the artifacts that they get,but its a lot of work to find the artifacts,too. Let me explain what I mean.      First of all,they have to get all the research and then get the tools. They have to get things from 3D computers to dust pans. They also have teams to make it easier. The teams can be up to thirty five people! They also have to find out about other things that were found in the area to see if what their trying to find is still there. Then they start the hunt.              They find the spot where they need to start first. They use those 3D computers to try and find things under the ground. They may only dig 25 square feet in 2 weeks! The whole thing is very slow, but in the end its worth it. Once they find the artifact,it has to be cleaned. It is a great job, but it is very important. In the end it all comes together,the artifact goes where it belongs,and they wait for their next trip.

Item_Response: Archeologists           Archeologists have very hard jobs. They also have very dangerous jobs! They have to go to different places to try to find undiscovered   artifacts about one person. Say they're trying to find artifacts of Cleopatra, they'd go to were she came from ( Egypt ) and try to find artifacts. That's were the name artifacts came from ( Archeologists ). Although there job sounds easy, it's very dangerous and hard! When they're in caves trying to find artifacts, the cave could cave-in.           Archeologists can have the hardest jobs on earth! Going to find artifacts about just ONE person is super hard! Man, sometimes I can't even find facts about people in books, let alone finding their past?! I think not. First off, you have to go to where their old house was and search it. Second off, you need to find a lot of their pictures to tell who they were. Third off, you have to know a lot about that person! You also have to know a lot about how they lived, who they lived with, how many family members they had, and what they did for a living.            If you want to be an archeologist when you're older, I suggest you start studying some people right now! Finding artifacts is like finding something when it's lost, lost history! When you lose something, it's very hard to find right? If you answered yes, then imagine trying to find something that's been lost for hundreds even sometimes thousands of years! If you answered no, then man you're crazy! People who live in the same place for their whole life make it easier to find artifacts, but people who have moved around the world a lot, make it VERY hard!           As you can see finding artifacts is not all so easy. You must go through a lot of steps before you start looking for artifacts. You have to have all the right tools, the right gear, and especially the right type of people to help you!   If you want to be an archeologists when you're, just remember I warned you! I warned you that it is a very hard job!

Also they use a whisk and dustpan to also take dirt off of an artifact.  Now for the skim shovel, it is flat to remove one layer of dirt at a time.  Then,  last but not least, the trowel.  It lets an archeologist look at one layer of dirt at a time.       You cant just dig up a house and say it belongs to a famous person in history,  you need to find clews that it is theirs.  Like in Digging up George Washington's Past.  They found different clews it was his.  One was that they found one of his clay pipes.  Also it gives more information about their childhood, their adulthood,  when they where born, and much more probably.           Without archeologists we would know almost nothing about the past.  Maybe not even basic maps.  Luckily we have them to tell us the mysterys of the past.

Item_Response: Digging For History             Finding Fort James                      Archeologists have been studying Jamestown in 1994.               They have been discovering the secrets of James Fort in             Jamestown, Virginia. People thought that the fort had been             washed away by a river. Some discoveries found in the area               hinted that it might still be around there.                                         James Fort was built  in 1607, that's when the settlers                      came from England. It was easier for people to dock ships                  there. The settlers found objects that meant the fort was                        further away from where they were. So they moved away,                   and the new spot gave more protection to the settlers from                   enemy ships.                             The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists                       uncovered armor and weapons from the past. They found                     other objects, such as, floors of buildings. Over 100 years                   later, a group of archeologists, found the exact spot where the             fort was built.                                         The National Park Service led a 5-year study of the area                to figure out how the area was used. They decided that this                 solution would help them look for evidence of the fort. Some               of the group did the computer mapping software of the area to              make an image of the  area.                             They finally found James Fort! They found a set of marks                on the ground, they showed where the walls used to be. They              heared different stories, read books, and made drawings, the             archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a                       triangle. They found different objects such as:11 cellars,                     ledges, burial sites, and ten buildings.                          So, do you want to be an archeologist?

Item_Response: Archeologists        Archeolgists have a vary inportant job. There job is to find artifacts from inportant times in history. Things from George Washingtons childhood and finding Fort James. Archeoligists are our link to the past.             One of the vary inprtant jobs that they had to do was find George Washingtons home. They needed to find his familys house because we did not know much about his childhood. The Archeolgists task was to find were his home was lokated on Ferry Farms. Using 3.D maps and tools they were abel to find it.            Another inportant dig they dug was finding Fort James in James town from one of the first colenies. Some peopole thought that it had been washed away by the river. But the archeolgists pruved them rong. They aculy found the exact spot were it had been built.Its pretty cool to know what archeologists can find.            Archeologists have lots of special tools for on the dig sites. (1) They have a pick and a shovel, they use these tools to start the dig by clearing away the top layer(s) of dirt. (2) they have something called a whisk and a dustpan, the whisk is used to brush dirt off of artifacts or off the exevation site, they use the dust pan with the whisk. (3) They use a knife for careful digging and to scrape hard dirt off of the artifacts.(4) They use a wheelbarrow for obviuse reasons(like caring dirt away from the dig site). (5) They use a specail tool called a skim shovel, that has flat edges, to remove a thin layer of soil with every scoop. (6) The last tool they use is a trowel, this is probebly the most comen tool, and they use it to scrape, and cut to veiw the soil from different angels. Now you know all the tools that they need, and how they use them.            Archeologists are like detectives with with tools and an inportat job to solve the mysterys past.

Item_Response: What is it like to be a archeologist? your about to find out. A archeologist is a person that uses many tools to dig up different artifacts from many different locations. Those artifacts help us learn more about history. It is exiting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago.              The process of digging is a careful one. It takes patience, and many hard workers. The many people who dig are on a 'team.' There can be up to thirty-five people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground.All the information is used to show where the workers need to start and what to use.             Another type of team works on the actual digging. Where they dig, is called a 'dig.' they start with a tool called a 'Skim shovel.' The skim shovel is used to get the first few layers of dirt off. It can do this because of its shape. The skim shovel is is small, flat, and sharp.               A technique called troweling is also a way to dig up artifacts. They archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes and wooden picks to remove the dirt off of the artifacts. Sometimes, it takes up to two weeks to dig a twenty-five square foot section. A different team from the two you have already learned about, spends a whole day examining artifacts in a lab.                  So, do you think your going to be a archeologist? Your going to have to be a patient and hard worker!

They uncovered armor and weapons.  Over 100 years later, a group tried to find the exact spot where the fort began.  They led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used.  They knew that this would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort.            That is where they finally found James Fort!  The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground.  The marks showed where the fort's walls used to be.  between all the stories they heard, read, and drawings they made , the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle.             Today, the group finds nearly 1,000,000,000 objects each year.  The objects include pottery, tools, coins, and even metal toys for children.  In the 1600's, people used to throw there trash down an unused well or into a big pit.              It is exiting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago!  In my opinion archeologists are pretty cool people!

Item_Response: So archeologists work on digging sites and find find artifacts. There is more to them then you think. This essay tells you how they work on digging sites, why they must be careful and patient while digging, and what benefits their digging. Remember there is more to archeologists then you think.       Archeologists are split up into teams. The first one of these teams map the area with three-dimensional computers. Those computers track what is underground so that the archeologists will know what the site looks like before they start digging. The second team does the actual digging. They start digging with a special shovel called a skim shovel which can remove a thin layer of dirt with each single scoop. Then the soil is put in a special container that has a 1/2 inch screen at the bottom that lets all of the dirt out at the bottom while the artifacts stay in. Then the archeologists use paint brushes, small shovels, and wooden toothpicks to remove dirt in a process called troweling. The final team studies the objects that were found on the site in a lab.       This whole process takes a long time, and you might want it to be over with. But you must be patient with your work! The people who dug up the site and found George Washington's house said that it took a year to find the slave quarters, kitchen, and storage houses. It took even longer to find the farmhouse. Plus, if you were not careful, you would dig right past the thing or place that you were trying to find.       But, something benefits all this hard work. When you do find what you were looking for it will teach you a little about world history. There is that and the fact that you discovered something that was lost in history for so many years. On top of that there is the joy of doing all that labor and it really pays off.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is to study and learn about things that happend in the past or to study famous people like Goerge Washington.Also,their job is to study objects from the past.          In 1994,a group of people interested in studying the past started in Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project.The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia.For over 200 years.people thought that the fort had been washed away by   a river.Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.                                          The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life.Most believed that James Fort was built near the river.It was easier to dock ships there,so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot.However,objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.The new spot probably gave the settlers more protectio from enemy ships.                                                                                                                                                   The first objects were found in 1861.Archeologist,the name for scientist who study objects from the past ,uncovered armor and weapons.They also discovered the floors of buildings.Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.                                                                                                                                                     The National Park Service led a five year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew that this would help then decide where to look for proof of the fort.The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.                           Thats when they finally found James Fort!The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground.The marks showed where the forts walls used to be.Between all the stories they heard and read,and drawings they made,the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle.They  made maps and found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river.The ledges were designed to hold canons.The archeologists also found eleven cellars,dozens of burial sites ,and 10 buildings all within the border of the fort.                                                                Today,the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year.The objects include pottery,tools,coins,and even metal toys for children.In the 1600s,people used to throw their trash down n unused well or into a big pit.While digging in the area,the archaeologists found the trash the settlers threw away,including the bones of animals they ate.The imformation learned from these objects helps us understand how the people in James Fort lived.We now know how the settlers fought the Powhatan tribe that often attacked them.We also know what the settler did to survive the difficult years when they had little food.                                                       It is exciting to discover objects that were regularly used by people who lived hundreds of years ago.It gives us a piece of our past and ties us to people who fist started the American colonies.                                                                                                                                                     Most of what we know about George Washington comes from his time as a soldier and president.Biographies dont have very much imformation about hs childhood.Thats changing,however.Recent discoveries at Washingtons childhood home had helped historians know more about Goerge Washington as a boy.                                                                                       People have lived on the land known as Ferry Farm for over 12,000 years.Its location makes it a perfect place to build a home.There for,its not surprising that George Washingtons father,Augustine Washington,moved his family there.Goerge Washington was just 6 years old at the time.                                                                                                                                                 No one knew exactly where the Washington home was located since the actual building was long gone.Howevr,archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there.They started digging in 2003.It took over a year,but they finally found it.The first buildings they found were the kitchen,slave quarters,and storage houses.They found the main farmhouse a few yeats later.                                                                                                                   At least four other houses have been built on the Ferry Farm land,so the diggers needed to find proof that this was George Washingtons farmhouse.Records show that the Washingtons had a fire in their house.The diggers found pieces of burnt pottery.The suggests a fire occurred there.They also found part of a clay pipe.We know that Washington smoked clay pipes,so this discovery gives more proof it is the right house.              The process of digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one.Each year,many teams will work on the site.The can be up to 35 people on a team!The first team maps the area using 3d computers that can track what is underground.The imformation is recorded so that the people will know what it looked like before people started digging.Another team focuses on the actual digging,and the place the team does the digging is called a dig.Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels.These shovels are so small,flat,and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil,one at a time.That soil is then placed in a box with a half inch screen at the bottom.This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in.The diggers also use a process called troweling.Troweling is when archeologists use small shovels,paint brushes,and wooden picks to remove dirt.It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section!Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found.The whole process is slow and tiresome,but its worth it.               The discovery of Washingtons home is important for many reasons.First,it give the citizens of the United States a better understanding of who George Washington was before he became famouse.We also begin to know why he made the decisions he did.Another thing it does is help historians learn the type of life Colonial Americans lived.All of these things are key parts of our past as Americans.                                                                                   Ferry Farm offers many opportunities for kids to get involved.The George Washington society runs summer workshops with both clasroom and outdoor activities.Kids can explore the site,experience colonial life,and become junior archeologists.Kids can sign up for classes,games,and crafts.The is even an interactive website!It challenges kids to solve puzzles about the work being done at the Ferry Farm.                                                                      Digging around in the dirt can give you more than just dusty jeans.The folks at Ferry Farm are bringing to life the countrys first president in ways we have never seen.

Item_Response: Being an Archeologist                     Do you know what a person is called when they look for artifacts from the past? They're called archeologists. Archeologists find things like pottery, pieces of tile, armor, weapons, and etc.To find these things it depends on where the excavation site is.                  When you're an archeologists you have to use many tools, so they can excavate the artifacts carefully. The tools they use are picks, dustpans, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, and a trowel. They start excavating by using the two tools a pick and a shovel. They use them by digging into the Earth near the artifacts. Another one of the tools they use are a whisk and dustpan they are used to brush dirt off of the artifacts and to clear away dirt from the excavation site. The other tools they use are knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovel, and trowel. They use knives by carefully digging around the artifact and to scrape dirt off of the artifact. Wheelbarrows are used to move artifacts or dirt away from the excavation site. A skim shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Last, but not least the trowel. The trowel is used to scape and cut to view different layers of soil.                    In 1994 a group of archeologists were interested in studying the past of Fort James. The project was called 'The Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project' ; it was designed for archeologists to find the secrets of Fort James in Jamestown, Virginia. When the fort was built near a river they decided to start at a river, but when they found objects somewhere else near the river the spot they found was probably safer than the place they were looking at first. They uncovered armor, weapons, and some pieces of tile floor that might have been used for the flooring of the fort.                     Now thats what I know about what projects and tools archeologists do and use.

Item_Response: A job as an archeologists is very important. Though some people might not realize it, but a lot of our history comes from an archeologists job. They find out things from the past. Now lets get into more detail about an archeologists job.               An archeologists job is to study things from he past. Archeologists do also need things to help them do their job properly and successfully. Some of these tools include,   technology such as computers and other special technology. pick and shovel whisk and dust pan knife wheelbarrow skim shovel trowel  and so much more! Of course all these tools are used at least one time in an archeologists job. Lets find out what the purposes of these tools are. Technology is used for lots of things, such as researching the mystery they want to get more background information about, and lots of other things to. Archeologists usually start off digs with these two tools, a pick and shovel. These are used to dig into the earth, close to artifacts. A whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. A knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. Archeologists also us a wheelbarrow to move items from one place to another, or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. A skim shovel has a flat edge used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Finally, a trowel is probably the most common tool in archeology. It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. Those are just some of  the tools archeologists use in their investigations.                                                                                                                                 Did you know that it takes lots of time to uncover things that archeologists are out to find. Have you ever thought about this? They can't just guess or suppose, they have to do a lot of research even before they set out to find what their looking for. they really have to be precise or accurate. They have to get background information. Like if it was a building and it wasn't there anymore, than where was it when it was still standing. Also even after they have found artifacts it might not be the whole thing so if they do find another piece they would have to find the exact spot and glue and mold,etc. All in all it's like a puzzle, ( but a one million piece puzzle!) Now you see why it takes so long for an archeologist to complete their mission.             Archeologists don't only discover the things their looking for, but sometimes they discover other things to.                                                                                                  An archeologists job isn't as easy as you think, it requires lots of things. An archeologist has a major impact on our history. Thanks to archeologists we know so much more of our history than we would have if their weren't any archeologists.

Item_Response: Archeologist               Victoria Flores                                                                              Being an Archeologist is hard work you have to dig for evidence also test chemicals or clothes.There are evidence with  James Fort and George Washington's house, that they discover.                    James Fort was built by settlers who came from England to start a new life.People believe that it was built by a river because it would be easier to ship out ships for supplies.Some people say that over 200 years ago it got washed away but the archeologist say's that it might be around because they are finding clues.Their are objects found like pottery,tools,coins,metal toys, and undercover armor and weapons.The archeologist studied it for 5 long years with maps,land, and the area .They finally found the fort by the marks on the floor where the walls use to be they knew it was the fort because they know that it is shaped like a triangle.They realized that there were stone ledges in the river and that ledge was designed to hold cannons.The archeologist found eleven cellars with dozens of burial sites.In the 1600's they use to throw there trash away in an unused well or into a big ditch.While the archeologist was digging they found trash in wells or ditches with also bones from animals.The Powhatan Indians often attacked them and stole their food so know they know that they had little food to eat.It was very exciting for the archeologist to find pieces of our history.                George Washington moved into this house with his family when he was about 6 years old.No one knew where Washington's house was really located since the home was burned down.The archeologist believe that there is a stone base still under the house.They started digging in 2003 it took over a year but they found it.The first building they found were the kitchen,slave quarters,and the storage houses.There is a land called the ''FerryFarm Land''.On the land their were at least 4 other houses,he diggers needed to find evidence if the farmhouse was Washington.The records of Washington say that his house burned down of a fire.The diggers found burnt pieces of clay so there wondering if the fire is true.There was also a piece of a clay pipe,we know that Washington smoked clay pipes.So know we know it is true about what happened at Washington's house.                 How do the Archeologist do this job?Well they do it by working together as a group which is 35 people.They have cool tools like 3D computers that can track underground things so they know were to dig and give them information.They start there dig with a skim shovel then use a wheelbarrow to take the dirt somewhere else.They use small shovel,paint brushes,and wooden picks to remove dirt.It can take 2 weeks for using those tools a 25-square-foot section!Everything goes slow but it is really worth it for finding things in the past.                       Those are things archeologist found interesting but their are many more to go.

Item_Response: FINDING FORT JAMES        In 1994 a group of people intereested in studyng the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archealogical Project the project. The project was a designed to discover the secrets of the james fort in Jamestown, virginia. The fort was built 1607 when settlers cam from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would chose the spot.       The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists the name for the scienist wh study objects from the past, uncover armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built again. The National Park Service led a five- star study of the area to figure out how was the land was used.        Thats when they finally found James Fort the first thing found was a set of marks on the ground. the marks showed the forts walls used to be. they made maps and found out that the fort streched all the way to the river. today the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year. the objects include  pottery tools coins and even metal toys for childeren.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is hard and dirty work. They have to dig most of the stuff they are looking for. Archeologists have special tools to help them dig up artifacts like picks, shovels, and wheelbarrows. It takes awhile before archeologists can do anything because they have to do a lot of research on the artifact they are looking for or something related to it.      Archeologists discover these artifacts for people to better understand the history of the artifacts. It also helps historians learn more about how people lived.      Archeologists sometimes start looking for an artifact and find tiny parts of it, but then they stop sometimes. Somebody else will sometimes lead a group and hopefully be more successful. It helps when archeologists find little bits and pieces around the area because then it gives them an idea where the site is they are looking for. Archeologists also work in teams. Each team works on a certain things like computers, where they are actually going to dig, and another team works in the labs studying the objects they found.      Archeologists use a bunch of different tools whether it's people, technology, or stuff they use to dig, archeologists have big jobs.

Item_Response: Treasure Hunters: Archeologists                        Archeologists are the treasure hunters of the world. The word archeologist means 'scientist who studys objects from the past'. Archeology is a major part in the    United States of America. Archeologists have been a part of the finding James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia and the learning of George Washington's childhood.These were very interseting escavations.           James Fort was a fort built in 1607 by English settlers. Settlers left the fort and it is said did not tell anyone of the whereabouts of the fort beacause many people believed it was built next to the river, yet the first objects found in 1861 were found farther from the river. Litte did the archeologists know that it wou take over 100 years to find the fort. The National Park Service led a five-year study in the late 1980s-early 1990s era. The people did a mapping scan of the area. They used it to make an image of the area and found the fort.           Not alot was known about George Washington's childhood because there was no known information about him. Archeologists led an escavation at Ferry Farm where it is known to be George Washington's childhood home. Of course there was no house because it was destroyed. They dug underground trying to find a room. One year later they found the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses. They found the main farm house a year later.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is about digging up some lost artifacts.   One unique find of an archeologist is Fort James.   Long ago, in 1994, a group of people were interested in long lost artifacts, buildings, among many others. This 'studying of the past' began the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was designed to discover the secrets of Fort James in Jamestown, Virginia (one of the thirteen colonies). For over 200 years, people thought that Fort James had been washed away by a torrent. Some say that it might be around if archeologist discovered the area. Now, about a hundred years later, a group of archeologists teamed up to find the long lost artifacts of the now-old-and-historical Fort James. To help find the area of the fort, they rely on the National Park Service (which led a five-year-study of the area). The group of archeologists knew this would help them decide where to look for definite proof.   When they reached Fort James, the first thing they saw where footprints on the ground. These marks showed where the fort's location used to be. But, that's the first thing they found, because today the group of archeologists had found one million of these artifacts now to be shown at a museum. These include pottery, tools, coins, and metal tools.   One other unique find is the long lost tale of George Washington, his home, and the many artifacts that he had.   A group of archeologists (different from the ones that discovered Fort James) teamed up to 'dig up' George Washington's past. The archeologists made a trip to Ferry Farm to CAREFULLY dig up the artifacts George Washington had when he was six. First, information is collected before the dig. Meanwhile, another team of archeologists focused on the dig of Washington's past.  This team started with small, flat, and sharp shovels called skim shovels. These shovels can only remove thin layers of soil, one at a time. Then, it's placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom, which lets dirt fall out while artifacts stay in. Archeologists also use troweling, another digging process. Troweling is when archeologists use wooden picks, small shovels, and paint brushes. Meanwhile, another team studies the artifacts. The dig is tiresome and torturous, but it's definitely worth the dig.   Kids can also get involved with being an archeologist. In example, Ferry Farm can offer many kids to get involved, so they open the George Washington society, which runs summer workshops with both classroom and outdoor activites. Kids can explore the site, learn about the life of a colonist, and become junior archeologists. Kids can also visit an interactive website.   How to become an archeologist is simple. You just start with a pick or a skim shovel, scoop up the earth with a dustpan, then scrape off dirt with a knife, carry it away with a wheelbarrow, and then the troweling starts. It may not be a clean and short job, but it's worth the try. Just keep digging until you will find the long lost artifacts of a historical person!

Information has to be recorded for people to know how it looked before they started to dig in the area. That is what the first team will do to search for artifacts.           Another team comes in to work on digging.The team will dig in an area called a dig.Archeologist use small, flat and sharp shovels used to dig thin layers of soil called skim shovels. The soil is put into a box with a half inch screen at the bottom for the dirt to fall out and also use a technique called troweling, which is when they use mini shovels, paint brushes, and picks made out of wood to get dirt of the artifacts. Another reason why is it tells us more about other famous people in history. One last reason is it could also tell more about other time periods. Item_Response: Archeologists Job                    Archeologists have many jobs and in this report i going to tell you the importance of this job and what they do. Archeologists are people who study objects from the past. They help people discover objects from the past and what they meant. Archeologists use many sources that help them like the internet, the internet helps them discover more information about the object. There are many reasons why does the job of archeologists are important and you are going to know.        Many times archologists work in fossils and when they do they learn many intrusting things just like us, so that means we have something in common with them. Fossils are dead things that were in the past, as time past their shape began going to form a shape on a object. Archeologists wanted to know what happen to the thing and how did it die. Archeologists were smart but sometimes they had trouble discovering the informationn of the thing that was dead, they can even lasted months or years searching about what happen to that thing.        Archeologists also use many stageties to study the object from the past. Finding Fort James was difficult, for 200 years people thought that the fort had washed away but the archeologists were going to prove them wrong. Most people believed that James Fort was built near the river, the firt object they found was in 1861 it was uncovered armor, weapons, floors, and buildings. Archeologists used mapping software to make an image of the area because they wanted to figure out how the land was used. In that time they found James Fort, the first thing they saw was a set of marks on the ground, the marks showed where the fort's walls used to be. Between the stories the heard and read they knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle with all kinds of things.        Acheologists use many hints, tools, and sources. One of the tools are the skim shovels, they used this in digging up a spot that was known as Ferry Farm, people had lived on this land over 12,000 years. Augustine Washington lived there when George Washington was just six years old. No one knew where was the Washington home wqas located since the actual building was long gone. Archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there, they started digging in 2003, it took over a year but they finally found it. The first buildings they found were the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses, they found the main farmhouse a few days later. Records show that the Washington had a fire in their house.        As you know, archeologists use many tools for many things. Pick and shovel are one of those tools, most digs start with these tools, they used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. The whisk and duskpan used to brush dirt off the asrtifact and clear away dirt fro m the excavation site. A knife is used for careful digging and to scape dirt from around the artifact. The wheelbarrow used to move items big or small from one p[lace to another. Finally a trowel is a common tool of acheology, it used to scrape and cut to view the diffrent layers of soil.        Now you know a few reasons about why the job of the acheologists is important. Archeologists do a lot of important discoveries and I thank them for helping us discover items that are from the past. Doing this report about acheologists job was important to me and I hope you like it. Acheologists are the best and smart for discoveries.
