Item_Response: This paper is about the job of an archeologist.   Being an archeologist is a wonderful job. You get to look at wonderful things, see thing that you have never seen before and use things that you've never used before. You get to see the remains of a very famous person that lived long ago. You also get to see what they ate and what they lived in and also where they lived.        You can get involved with Ferry Farm. The George Washington club runs summer workshops and outdoor activities. Kids can explore the site and discover what its like to be in the Colonial Life. You can become a junior archeologist. Kids can sign up for day classes, games and crafts.       In 1994 a group of people interested in the study of the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project.   The project was designed to descover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 yrs., people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around there.       The fort was built in 1607 when some settlers came from England to start a new life upon them. Most belived that James Fort was built near the river. It was easier to dock the ships there. So it made sense that the settlers would have chosen that spot. However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was built further up river.  The new spot probably gave thee settlers more cover from the enemy ships.        Today a group has found about 1 million items a year. Like pottery tools, old coins, and even metal toys they used for children.  In the 1600's people used a well or a big pit that was unused to throw away their trash. While digging in the area, an archeologist found the trash the settlers threw away like, bones of animals they ate. The information learned about these objects help us know how the Jamestown people lived.

If they don't find anything the first day, they'll continue the next day either in a new spot, or a little farther away from the old spot they started on.            There are several different teams to dig up these artifacts. The first team maps the area using 3D computers so they can track what is underground before they dig, so they know what they are digging for. another team focuses on the actual digging. Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skin shovels. These shovels are meant to remove thin layers of dirt at once. Then, the dirt is placed in a box with a screen at the bottom so the dirt falls and the artifacts stay in the box. Not everyone knows what an archeologist is or what they do, but they are still very significant. Archeologists are people who study history. They are significant in many different, but similar in some ways . For example, we need scientists to discover earths history and teach it to todays people so no one is confused on what happened and why it happened.       Archeologists have been known for their important studies, because of history happening since the first day of earth archeologists have been at it for decades maybe even centuries. They're known for discovering non-living things to living things and exinct things to fossels. In the past life time, scientists didn't have the technology that we have today so they couldn't find that much evidence on what happened before. However, todays technology is more advanced in many ways which provides acheologists to go deeper into their thoughts and reasons. Although, its still hard to be an archeologist because history is told through man to man and some stories are told differently which could lead to false imformation. Those tools are some of the tools you would use if your trying to find history from when exinct or dead living things or to find the history and information from a fossel.       In conclusion, archeologists are scientists that discover earths history and pass it down to people, they use many technology and tools to dig up the evidence of what happened, why it happened, and how it happened. They are very significant scientists and they help provide information to teach others of the past. Archeologists have been around for centuries telling man to man about recent and past times. Therefore, archeologist will continue gathering information and facts about history and pass stories down, there will probably be no ending to this.

Item_Response: In the article 'Finding Fort James' by Cheryl Bradley, the Jamestown Archaeological Project was created to learn even more about James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. Many people thought that it had been washed down the river it was made close by too, or destroyed and too broken to try and find. Around 200 years later there were signs that those theories were wrong and that James Fort was still there. The Jamestown Archaeological Project groups were determined to find more about this fort and prove the theories wrong.          One reason why they are so determined is in 1861 the first objects were found, armor and weapons to protect the fort, they also found they also found the floor of the fort. They didn't stop and around 100 years later, they found the exact spot where James Fort stood and stayed strong enough to find now. A 5 year study was worth it! It took computer mapping software and hard work to find the wall marks and stone ledges over the river it was built by. This showed that canons used to be there and also found cellars, burial sites, and ten buildings. They found even more things and each year even more.          Clearly this shows that the Jamestown Archaeological Project proved the theories about Fort James destroyed and washed down the river wrong! They had found the cellars, buildings, artifacts, and marks where the fort had been. Team-work and determination really helps. It took years and years to have this project come through very successful and now we all can know much more about James Fort than we did.          In conclusion, determination and believing that you are right pays through. The Jamestown Archaeological Project groups should be proud of them selves for believing and being determined in what they believe and what they have done for their country. We today know much more about the James Fort than what we did a couple hundred years ago, just because of one group determined and believing in them self ready to discover what they want.

Item_Response: Dig dig... pat pat... heave heave... sweat sweat. Archeologists have a difficult, but rewarding job in   which they find ancient artifacts. They use many different tools, and use them to find different things. They have to go through different steps in order to find what they are searching for. These are the ways archeologists dig up history.       Archeologists first map the ground where they will dig. They use 3D computers to track things in the   ground. The image that comes out is the map of the area. They then record all that information, so the diggers know what it is like in that area. The mappers have an easier job than the diggers, though.        The archeologists that dig do it in the place called the dig. They use tools such as a knife, pick, shovel,   trowel, skim shovel, whisk, dustpan, and wheelbarrow. The tools are each used for different reasons. The diggers first start digging with their skim shovels, which remove thin layers of soil at a time. The dirt scooped is put in a box with a small screen at the bottom, letting dirt fall, but keeping artifacts in. Archeologists also use their trowels in a process called troweling. That is when they use small shovels, picks, and brushes to take away soil and dirt. The digging part of archeology is undoubtedly the hardest.       The final step in archeology is studying them. Another team of archeologists spend days studying the   artifacts found. The people who study the artifacts find information about the past. They can find out how people lived, or use the artifacts to find a specific place. Studying the objects is probably fun, since you can find information about history.       As you see, archeology is a hard job that many people rely on to find historic things. The artifacts   archeologists find are useful in finding information about history. Without archeology, what would we know about history?

Item_Response: ?                                                                                     The Long Job of an Archeologist                    What is an archeologist? An archeologist is a person who goes to find some thing that is very old using all kinds of resources. For instance, if you are trying to find something that belonged to the vikings, then you would have to go to where the vikings lived Archeologists go through difficulty, hard thinking, and pride while working. Archeologists go through a lot to find these wonderful things and without them, we wouldn't know much of our history.                  To start, an archeologist's job is difficult because a lot of things that they are looking for are very fragile. They need to use special tools and be very careful because of these fragile pieces. It is also difficult because if they mess up one thing, then all the blame would be on them because they just ruined history. Lastly, it is difficult because most of the time it takes a very long time to find out what they are searching for.                 Initially, being an archeologist takes a lot of thinking because before you even start searching for what you want to find. For instance, if you wanted to find something that belonged to the vikings you would have to do a lot of research and studying before you start looking. They also have to do a lot of thinking because they need to know what they are doing. If they do the wrong thing and they mess up, then everything will get ruined.                  Most importantly, one of the most exhilarating part in an archeologist's job is feeling pride. They probably get this feeling when they finally discovered what they were searching for. For example, if you finally found where George washington lives, then you would feel it because you finally found your discovery. They would also feel pride because most of the time, it takes them a long time to find there discovery and usually, when you've been working on something for a long time and you finally finish it, you feel pride.                  To conclude, archeologists are very important to us. they put a lot of time and effort just to find history for us. Archeologists have very stressful jobs, but they always manage to get their jobs done. They are also fantastic role models on us and are a big part of our education.

Item_Response: Digging Up the Past: Archeologists                                                                                            Lauren Vuong                  Have you ever wondered what an archeologist does? Archeologists are people who 'dig up the past'. There are many archeologists all over the world, and they all do different things. For example, some dig up fossils of dinosaurs to discover about when they lived and etc. while others study artifacts that date back to 1300 B.C. The phrase 'digging up the past' was made because archeologists had been digging for facts about the past through artifacts and other. Many of the pottery pieces, statues, and pieces of statues in museums came from the work of archeologists across the globe. Archeologist's jobs are to find clues about the past.                      Now a days, some of the tools used by the archeologists are picks, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovels, and trowels. Even though we are in the 21 century, they still use these basic tools. Along with this, current day archeologists use 3 dimensional computers to scan the ground for remains and they use other technology too. We are lucky to have modern day technology to help us in many things. Archeologists can take less time, energy, and money using these tools because then they don't dig up the wrong areas. Some of the tools archeologists use have special jobs. For example, a pick and a shovel: used to dig into the earth, can cart away dirt. A whisk and dustpan can be used to: brush away dirt and uncover artifacts/ clear away dirt from search site. Knives are useful to do careful digging around artifacts and to scrape dirt away. A skim shovel is useful because you can take thin layers of dirt off. One of the more common tools throughout the world is the trowel: used to scrape and cut into the soil. There are many tools, modern and classic, used in the study of archeology.                      Throughout the years, archeologists have discovered many interesting things. For instance, some archeologists are currently on a search for an ancient Mongolian king's, Ganges Kan, tomb. Others searched for George Washington's house. All studies took at least 2 years. Early settlers lived there so after 200 years, in which people believed it was washed away by the river, the National Park Service asked some archeologists to go looking for traces of Fort James. It took 5 years, but finally they found the triangular structure stretching from the river, back into the mainland property. Many other searches have been issued to find facts about people of the past, how they lived, and etc.                       Overall, many studies have taken place throughout the years to find facts about the past and there have been many archeologists. Item_Response: Archeologists and their Work            Have you ever wondered what an archeologist does for their job? Well, hopefully this report should answer all of your mind boggling questions that you have been dying to have answered.            First off, an archeologist's job is to pretty much uncover history. And, as you probably know, digging up the past is a long, laborious process. They pick different sites such as Mr. George Washington's own childhood home! Wouldn't it be interesting to learn all about his childhood since we really don't know that much about it? Archeologists pick other interesting sites as well. If you could think of one famous person who would you pick?            Archeologists have fancy, technical, modern day tools that play a big part in discovering our American history. A few example of tools and how they are used are:       The pick and shovel. The pick and shovel usually start the digging process. Their job is to slice and cut and dig into the earth to get close enough to the artifacts. The whisk and dustpan. The whisk is used to simply brush off dirt and unwanted rubbish off the artifact and the dustpan is used to clear the dirt away. Just like a good spring cleaning! Knife. A knife is used for precise and sharp digging. Also to scrape dirt off of the artifact. The wheelbarrow. The wheelbarrow is practically used for the same purposes of yard work. It is used to clear dirt away or to transport items to another area. The Skim Shovel. The skim shovel removes one layer of dirt at a time using a flat, sharp edge.     6.The trowel. The trowel is used to dig, scrape, and cut to see different layers of dirt.       Now that you have viewed the different tools and their purposes, you can probably guess how long and frustrating at times the archeologist's job is!            The sites the archeologists when to recently are Fort James and George Washington's old house. Some of the tools they probably used in the dig at Fort James are the wheelbarrow and knife and probably whisk and dustpan. The tools they probably used at George Washington's old home was probably the wheelbarrow the pick and shovel and the skim shovel.            As you can see, the archeologist has a very long job that could take hours upon hours of their time. But they have a very important job no less and without them, we wouldn't know half of our history.

Item_Response: In 1994, a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archeological Project. For over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. The first objects were found in 1861. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began. The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area. That's when they finally found James Fort. The archeologists found eleven cellars, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the fort. Today, the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year. Item_Response: Archeologists              Archeologists are people that study objects from the past. In 1994 a bunch of people interested in the past created the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. This project was made to find old secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia. For Over 200 years, some people thought the James Fort was washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might be still there in Jamestown,Virginia. The James Fort was built in 1607 when new people came to the 13 colonies to start a new life. Many people thought that the James Fort was built near a river. It was built there so it will we easier to dock their ships there so it made sense that the people would chose that spot to dock. The objects found nearby suggested to move the fort to move farther. The new spot that the settlers found was more protected from enemy ships.In conclusion 1994 was when the start of the James Town Rediscovery Archaeological Project.                  In 1861 archeologists found the first objects. Archeologists discover armor and weapons and they also discover the floor of the James Fort. Over 100 years later people tried to find the location of the James Fort again. The National Park Service led a five year study of the area to try to find how the land was used. They new that that it would help to find the location of the James Fort. The people doing the studying used a computer mapping software to imagine how the area would look like.They finally found the location they found marks on the ground the marks where the fort's wall.The archeologists thought the shape of the fort was a triangle but it was really stretched all away a crossed the river.  In conclusion found objects that lead them to find the location of the fort.              Another thing that archeologists study was George Washington. People have lived on the land called Ferry Farm for over 12,000 .It makes a perfect location to built a a house. That's why it is not surprising that George Washington's father moved his family there.When his dad moved him to Ferry Farm George was only 6 years old!No one really knew were was his home located since the actual building was no longer there. However archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there. The archeologists started to dig in 2003.It took them over a year, but they finally found the stone base.The first thing the archeologists found was the kitchen,slave quarters, and the storage houses.After a few years later they found a farmhouse.In conclusion George Washington lived in Ferry Farm              At last the four houses have been built on Ferry Farm land, so the diggers needed to find proof why this was George Washington farmland.Records show that Washington had a fire in their house. The diggers found pieces of burnt pottery. This suggests a fire occurred in his house.They also found a part of clay pipe. We know that Washington smoked clay pipes, so this gave more proof this was George Washington's house.In conclusion the archeologists found 4 houses and they think one of them is Washingtonians

Item_Response: Archaeologists   Have you heard of Archaeologists? Maybe you've heard of people that dig up dinosaur bones?   Those people are archaeologists. Many Archaeologists dig up old artifacts or small pieces of things hundreds, and maybe thousands of years old. There are archeologists all over the world. There are archeologists in China, Canada, Australia, Russia, Kenya, France, and here in the U.S.A. There are archeologists many other places, too.   Tools they use are pickaxes, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovels,   and trowels. Everything is used for something different. I bet you were wondering what a trowel was, or the difference between a skim shovel and a regular shovel. Well, I'm about to tell you.   Pick and shovel   Pickaxes and shovels are used to break and dig up dirt near the spot where the artifacts are.   Most digs start with these two tools. Picks are used to break up dirt and make the easier for the shovel. Shovels are used to dig dirt up to make the artifacts easier to get to.   Whisk and dustpan   These tools are used to brush dirt off of artifacts. They can also be used to brush dirt away very   close to the artifact, so the archaeologist won't damage the artifact.   Knife   Knives are used to scrape dirt away from the edge of the artifact. They can be used  to scrape   dirt from the insides of artifacts.   Wheelbarrow   Wheelbarrows are used to haul dirt away from the dig site. They can also carry heavy artifacts   away from the dig site.   Skim Shovel   This tool is used to dig layer by layer of soil from the dig site, and is mostly used when close   to the artifact.   Trowel   The most common tool used. It is used to scrape away dirt to examine the layers of soil.       Now I hope you know more about archaeology and how it's done. Thank you for reading my   report about archeologists.

Item_Response: Archeologist have an interesting, hard working job. They are counted on by many people. Would you want to be an archeologist? I am going to tell you about the job of an archeologist! The tools they use, where they discover the past, and digging!                                I have you heard about those people that are discovering new things? They are archeologist! Archeologist use many tools to find interesting things. Some of the tools they use are a Pick and Shovel, Whisk and Dustpan, Knife, Wheelbarrow, Skim Shovel, and Trowel. The pick and shovel are used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. Now those two are really needed! The whisk and dustpan are used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away dirt from the excavation site. Boy, those are two  things you will miss if you forgot them at home! Careful digging and scrapping dirt from around the artifacts is easier if you have a knife. Moving items from one place to another isn't easy without a wheelbarrow! Wheelbarrows are also used to carry dirt away from the excavation site. A skim shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. The TROWEL is the most common tool in archeology. It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil. If this one is not in your back pocket, you probably won't be finding anything!                                  For archeologist to find things they have to find the spot first.   Finding the spot isn't easy, you have to search and search and search.  Another thing that you have to do is to calculate where (for example) George Washington lived and where he would go, etc.  You would have to figure all that out then go there and find it.     It doesn't sound so easy, but it is quite enjoyable!                                                           Digging is a BIG part in archeology. Digging isn't that easy, it's not supposed to be, but digging can be the best part if you think about it. The digging leads you to the end and the suprise is waiting there!  Also you have a team of up to 35 people so that makes it a lot better! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the digging is called a dig. Skim Shovels are used for when you dig. The whole digging process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.                                          You see archeology is a big job! You have a lot of work to get done and that work is very important! It is an enjoyable, good experience job too! You have to work hard and get dirty but that's where all the fun comes from! The past is always fun to find in the present to show the future! So you should try archeology as your job in the future, I might even consider it!

Item_Response: Have you ever wondered how scientists and historians know what happened in the past? Those scientists are called archeologists and they study objects from a long time ago. They collect the data, find the artifacts, and use different tools to do it.                Archeologists need a place to start so they can conduct the investigation. That's where the data comes in. They use other scientist's research to know where to find what they are looking for. After they know where to look, they have to create data of their own to help other scientists. If they want to figure something out they have to find the problem and use their knowledge to research it. Collecting data is a giant part of how they discover information.                   After collecting all their data, scientists can look for the artifacts. This is important because actually seeing the objects makes it easier to study them. Archeologists look for artifacts where they know they can find them. But why do they look in the first place? This question is very easy to answer. Archeologists look for artifacts to find out more about the lives of people who lived before us and to advance in areas where other people needed help. Scientists also look for artifacts to find how things came to be. Documents are artifacts that we couldn't do without. If we did not have a documentation of how things happened it would be much harder to study the way things worked. Artifacts play an extremely important role in the study of history.                How do scientists get these things like data and artifacts? They use tools of course! Not just any tools though. They use specific tools to do specific jobs. Some of these tools are shovels and picks which help the scientists clear out land that they need to move in order to find their artifacts. No scientist could get this job done if they did not have the right tools to do it. Archeologists use whisks to wipe the dirt off of their artifacts and to collect small samples of their discoveries. They can even use knives to do things like scraping dirt off of important objects. These are only a few things that archeologists use for their investigations. Tools are another example of something very important to discovering information.                Scientists and historians know what happened in the past for all of these reasons and some more. Archeologists certainly have to collect their data, find their artifacts, and last but not least, use all kinds of special tools.

Item_Response: Archeologists       Archeologists have really cool jobs. they get to learn about things from the past. They get to find artifacts, fossils, and other neat things. Archeologists learn new things every day and can discover old artifacts from long ago.        The first thing archeologists do is get all the supplies they need. The supplies that they need include, a pick and shovel, a whisk and dustpan, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim shovel, and a trowel. A pick and a shovel is used for digging in the earth, a whisk and dustpan is used for brushing dirt off artifacts, a knife is used for scraping dirt from around artifacts, a wheelbarrow is used to move items from one place to another, a skim shovel is used for removing a thin layer of soil in each scoop, and a trowel is used for scraping and cutting to view the different layers of soil.                                                         Next, archeologists need to find a place to work. They would need a place with a lot of artifacts or somewhere that had a village or house that isn't there anymore. Somewhere like Fort James, Virginia would work. Fort James was built in 1607 so there is lots of artifacts there. Places like this would be perfect for archeologists to dig.       Then, archeologists would start digging for artifacts. They look for parts of houses, floors of buildings, armor or weapons, cellars, or anything old. They would use a trowel, a skim shovel, and a pick and shovel to dig. Then the archeologists bring the items they find to a certain spot in a wheelbarrow.        Last, the archeologists get the whisk and dustpan, knife, and start to clean up the artifacts they found. once they do that they start studying them and find the history of  what they found.         As you can see, being an archeologist is an exciting job and one day you might decide to be one too!

Item_Response: ARCHEOLOGISTS DIGGING UP FACTS   Have you ever wondered what archeologists do for work?  Well, I'm going to tell you what they do.       First, they pick what they want to work with because there are different types of things they can dig. There are ones that work inside, at digs, on shipwrecks and so on. Archeologists dig up facts about people that lived long ago. Or on shipwrecks they try to figure out what lead up to the wreck and when it happened. Item_Response: Being an archeologists is a hard job because you can have a group up to 35 people or maybe evan more! The process of digging in places is a careful one.Each year many teams will work on a famous place.The way the archeologists dig up these atifacts is with having  groups work on different things like let's say the first group maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground.The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started digging.Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place the team does the digging is called a dig. Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small,flat and sharp that they can remove nothing but thin layers of soil,one at a time. That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch  screen at the bottom. This let's the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling. Trowling is when archeologists use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a place that is 25-square-foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it. So that's how the whole process is made and hoe the job is done and hoe thw archeologists do their job.

Item_Response: In 1994, a group of people interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. The project was designed to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. For over 200 years, people thought that fort had been washed away by a river. Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.             The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came from England to start a new life. Most believed that James Fort was built near a river. It was easier to dock ships there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot.   However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away. The new spot probably gave the settlers more protectionfrom enemy ships.              The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists,the name for scientists who study objects from the past,   uncovered armor and weapons. They also discovered the floors of buildings. Over 100 years later, a group effort to find the exact spot where the fort was built began.             The National Park Service led a five-year study of the area to figure out how the land was used. They knew that this would help them decidewhere to look for proof of the fort. The people doing the study used computer mapping software to make an image of the area.              That's when they finally found James Fort! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks showed where fort's walls used to be. Between all stories they heard and read, and drawings they made, the archeologists knew that the fort would be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and found out that the fort streched all the way to the river. Then they realized there were stone ledges built over the river. The ledges were designed to hold canons. The archeologists also found eleven cellers, dozens of burial sites, and ten buildings all within the border of the fort.

Item_Response: Archeologists         This informational report will be about archeologists. It will be talking about thier jobs, the differnt tools used, and how they do it. Archeologists are people that dig up different things and find things that have to do with the history of different things in the world. Archeologists have to have many different responsibilities to do what they do. There are 6 different tools that they use. Archeologists dont always find things every day. Somedays they might be just looking around and other days it might be very sucsessful but they should always have to have a positive attitude about it. Archeologists are very hard workers to get theur job complete for the day but the next day they should still be as positive and hard working as they were the day before.          First off, about Archaeologists jobs. Archeologists are scientists who study objects fromthe past. They have to be very patienrt otherwise they will not be able to find things. Not everything that Archeologists do is digging some of it is having to go look in old places or look in areas that are hidden but not unerground.  There can be up to 35 people on a team. The first team has to map the area and read it on a 3D computer. The information is recorded so that people know where to look to find things. Another team focuses on the actual digging and where they are digging is called a dig. Archeologists have to work together on things cause somethings that they are getting out are very big or delecate so they have to work together to get it out.          Next, is about the different tools that they use. The different tools that an Archeologists use are a pick and shovel, a whisk and dustpan, a knife, a wheelbarrow, a skim and shovel and a trowel. All these tools have a very special meaning and are used for different things. A pick and shovel are the two tools that most people in a dig start with. they are used to dig into the earth, that are close to the artifacts. A whisk and a dustpan are used to brush the dirt off the artifacts and clear away the dirt form the excavation site. A knife is used for carefully digging out the artifacts and to scrape the dirt away from around the artifacts. Skim shovels are a shovel with a flat edge used top carefully remove a thin layer of soil at a time with each scoop. The last tool is a trowel. A trowel is probably the most common tool in archeology and is used to scrape and cut to veiw the different layers of soil.         Lastly, about how they do their job. Archeologists are very determine people who walk around loking for bones or old artifacts. They do this because they want to learn more about the history of the world and they would like to share it with the rest of the world. They are not all the time digging but sometimes just looking areound to see what they can find. Archeologists have to be very careful to make sure that they dont brake any of the objects. They have to use the special tools for what they are made to do only or nothing else because if they arer used improperly theycan brake or they can brake the artifacts. They would especially have to work together when they are in a team of 35. Each team has a different role to do to get the job done. One team might be digging while another team could be mapping out the whole area to tell the other team where to look. Item_Response: A group of people who are interested in the past got together and started Jamestown Rediscovery. The project was put together to find James Fort secrets in Virginia. Over 200 years, people thought the fort has been washed away by a river. The fort was built in 1607 when settlers came to the land from England to start a new life.              A lot of people believed that the fort was built by a river. It was easier to dock ships there so it makes more sense. Objects were found nearby and people suggested the fort was farther away. The new spot gave settlers more protection in case an enemy is nearby.               Objects were found in 1861. Archeologists uncovered armor and weapons. And floors of buildings were found. More than 100 years later a group went searching in the exact same spot where the fort was built.                National Parks gave a 5-year study of how the land was used and looked for proof of the fort. They finally found it! The first thing they found was a set of marks on the ground. The marks led where the fort wall used to be. And today the group finds nearly 1 million objects a year. Including pottery, coins, tools, and metal toys!

Item_Response: History is very importaint to us. It helps us understand how we lived in the past.       Objects help us tell about the past. Even an object found in a old house can tell a story about a person, place, or thing.       In George Washingtons house, the diggers found a clay pipe and burnt pottery indicating it was his house.       There are teams of up to 35 people that dig up these relics. They are called archeologists. They dig the relics up carfully so they dont destroy or disturb the artifacts.       The archeologists use skim shovels to remove layers of dirt from the dig site. Then they put the dirt in a box with a screen at the bottom that lets dirt fall but not the artifacts.       Another way to dig is called troweling. Troweling is when you use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to dig up dirt.       It takes about two weeks to dig up a 25-sqare-foot section when you use troweling to dig. Its a long time but its worth it!

Item_Response: Archeology         Archeology is very interesting. For History Day I have chosen to write about archeology. Archeology is about helping the people of today learn about the past. There are many tools used in archeology such as the knife and wheelbarrow. People who study archeology are called archeologists. One discovery requires over one hundred archeologists. Archeologists spend years and years digging for things from the past.     There are many tools used in archeology, here are some of them, the knife, the wheelbarrow, the trowel, the skim shovel, pickaxes, shovels, whisks, and dustpans. Whisk and dustpans are used to clean artifacts. Wheelbarrows were used to move dirt and artifacts from one place to another. Most archeology digs start with picks and shovels and they are used to dig close to artifacts. The trowel is the most common tool used in archeology and it is used for scraping and cutting dirt. The skim shovel has a flat edge to help carefully remove a thin layer of soil.     Now I think archeology is very interesting. Some discoveries such as the finding James Fort and George Washington's house have been very helpful archeology discoveries. Yes you may think archeology is boring but think of all the cool things you could find. You could find dinosaur fossils, gold, a buried ancient civilization, and caves of diamonds! So really archeology isn't very boring at all and I hope you agree with me.

Item_Response: A group of people interested in studding the past are archeologists.They work hard and research the past of very historic people like George Washington.Archeologists that looked for George Washington and the Fort James past are pretty famous now.Archeologists had to discover the secrets of the James Fort in Jamestown,Virginia.For over 200 years, people thought that the fort had been washed away by a river.Some discoveries in the area hinted that it might still be around.It was easier to dock there, so it made sense that the settlers would choose that spot.However, objects found nearby suggested the fort was located further away.The new spot probably gave the settlers more protection from enemy ships.The fist objects were found in 1861.Archeologists uncovered weapons and armor.It gives us piece of our past.                                                         Most of what we know about George Washington comes from his time as a soldier and president.Archeologists don't have very much information about his childhood.Recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home have helped historians know a little more.Therefore, its not surprising that George Washington's father,Augustine Washington, moved his family to Ferry Farm, a perfect place to build a home.George was just six years old at that time.No one knew exactly where the Washington home was located since the actual building was long gone.However, archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there.They started digging in 2003.The first buildings under ground they found were the kitchen, slave quarters, and storage houses.they found the main farmhouse a few years later.This discovery gives more proof it is the right house.

Item_Response: Wow! Archeolegists are really cool! For poeple that are not aware, Archeologists are people that study ancient artifacts. They have a vast range of tools, computers, and radar that help them find the artifacts. Some tools are the Pick and Shovel, which most of the digs start with. They are used to dig into the site and find artifacts. Archeologists also use the Whisk and Dustpan, which are used to brush dirt off of artifacts and clear dirt from the dig site. Following, there is the knife, and that is used for causuos digging andmoving dirt from the artifact. Next, we have the Whellbarrow, which is used to move either dirt or items from the dig site, and the Skim Shovel, used to scrape a thin layer of earth from the dig. Finally, there's the Trowel, which is most likely the most common tool for Archeolologists, used to cut and scrape to look at different parts of the soil.         One of the digs Archeologists have done is find George Washinton's childhood home. They used the recordings from that time and matched it up with the items. All of them mached! Item_Response: Archeologists    Archeologists are people who have the job to study objects from the past. They go to abandoned historical sights to dig up artifacts. Which are objects from the past.      A group in 1994 were interested in studying the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. They were going to find and study Fort James. They were going to dig up old objects to study what people used in the old days. It took over 100 years to find the exact spot were Fort James was! The National Park Service led a study of the area to figure out how the land was used. This would help them decide where to look for proof of the fort. That's when they finally found the fort! They found a set of marks on the ground indicating where the fort's wall was. The archeologists knew the fort was a shape of a triangle from all the stories they have heard.      Today the group finds nearly 1 million objects each year. The objects include pottery, tools, coins, and even little toys for the children. They found trash the settlers threw away in a well or large pit. Including the bones of animals they ate. Archeology gives us a piece of our past and ties us to the people who lived hundreds of years ago.      Archeologists are important because if we didn't have them we would know very little about our past. Also about what life was like in the old days.

Item_Response: Archeologists are scientists that study our past. They study our past by digging up artifacts. The artifacts are useful because the archeologists use them to tell about the past.                  One group of archeologists were determined to find Fort James. While looking for the fort they found many interesting artifacts about how the people lived. By using computer software they were able to see the most accurate place of where Fort James was. Some artifacts that the archeologists found around the fort were coins, metal toys for children, and weapons.                   Another group of archeologists wanted to uncover George Washington's past at Ferry Farm. At first the team found the slave quarters, kitchen, and the storage houses. Then they found the main farmhouse.                      The tools and processes that the archeologists use are complicated. Archeologists use picks and shovels to dig into ground near artifacts. A whisk is used to brush off dirt from artifacts. Knifes are used for careful digging. Wheelbarrows carry heavy things. A skim shovel is used to remove a thin layer of soil. Trowels are used to scrape and cut to view the differing layers of soil.

Item_Response: Part two is about digging up George Washington's past. Most of what I know about George Washington is that he comes from his time a great solider and president. Boigraphies don't have very much information about his childhood. Thats changing however. Recent discoveries at George Washington's childhood home have helped all sorts of histotians know alot more information about George Washington as a little boy a long time ago.          People have lived on the land known as Ferry Farm for a very long time, over 12,000 years. It's location makes it a perfect place to build a home. Therefor, it's not suprising that George Washington's father, Augustine Washington , moved his family there. George Washington was just six years old at that time. No one knew exactly were the washington home was located ever since the actual building was long gone. However archeologists believed that the stone base under the house was still there. They started digging in 2003. It took over a year, but they finally found it.           The first buildings they found were the kitchen , slave guaters , and storage houses. They found the main farm house a few years later. At least four other houses have been built on the Ferry Farm land, so the diggers needed to find proof that this was George Washingtons farm house. Records show that this was Washingtons had a fire in their house.  they lost a lot of there stuff in the fire.             How do the archeologists find all of these things that were in Washington's house all those years ago? The process of digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one. Each year, many teams willl work on the site. There can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like before people started digging.             Another team focuses on the actual digging, and the place team does the digging is callled a dig. Those archeologists start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These are so small, flat, and sharp they take up soil.

Item_Response: ARCHEOLOGIST   A archeologist is a man or a women going across the world looking for artifacts such as diamonds, gold, reebees. A archeologist always come prepared to go across the world, A archeologist always have six things that they carry with them, these things are called tools these things are a pick and shovel, whisk and dustpan, knife, wheelbarrow, skim shovel, trowel.   The Pick and the Shovel it for to dig into the earth close to the artifact.   The Whisk and Dustpan is used to brush dirt off the artifact and clear away dirt from the excavation site.   The Knife is used for careful digging and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts.   The WheelBarrow is used to move items from one place to another or carry dirt away from the excavation site.   The Skim shovel is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop.   The Trowel is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.

Item_Response: Archeologists are people who find artifacts and ancient things from long ago. Both articles are based on how archeologists find artifacts from really famous places.One place where they went was to the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. The second place the archeologists went was to a house where they thought that George Washington lived in long ago. I am going to tell you what they did, researched, and analyzed in both places.           The group of archeologists are  interested in studying things from long ago with the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological Project. This project was formed to discover some of the deep secrets hidden in the James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia. The jobs of these archeologists is to find the hidden artifacts in James Fort. The first objects were found in 1861. The archeologists or the the scientists who study objects from the past, uncovered many weapons and armor. They found floors of buildings, too. At least 100 years later, another group came and tried to find the exact spot where the fort was built. The National Park Service led a five- year service of the area to find out how the land was used. They always knew that this would help them find proof of the fort. The people studying this used computer mapping to look at an image of the area. That's when they finally found the James Fort! A set of marks on the ground was the very first thing they saw. they showed where the fort's walls used to be. Between everything they research, heard and read about, they knew that the fort was going to be shaped like a triangle. They made maps and that showed him that is stretched out all the way to he river. The archeologists always were researching and trying to find out many new things about many ancient things and places. That is what makes their jobs so interesting and importing.               Where George Washington lived and spent his childhood was another place that the archeologists went to. The archeologists went there to find out if that was where George Washington lived as a child. There, they found proof to rediscover the place where George Washington lived. As a result, thy keep on finding many more things that lead to the conclusion that what they wanted to discover was true. The discovery of George Washington's  home was extremely important for many reasons. First of all, it makes the citizens of the United States understand George Washington's life story and give them a better understanding of where he lived and actually walked through before becoming famous and being the first president of the United States. Second of all, we would know the decisions he made and why. Lastly, it helps us learn how the Colonial Americans lived. The archeologists found many artifacts and things that belonged to George and he used.       So, now you know the things that archeologists do for a living. Their intersting job helps them and many other people understand the ways of people that lived long ago. Archeologists learn, even though they already know alot. Having that job is great for understanding the lives of famous people back then. So, now you can understand the jobs of archeologists and what they do for a living and how they do it.

Item_Response: The job of an archeologist is a hard one, but very rewarding. This paper will gude you through the job of an archeologist. Now lets get digging!       Archeologists usually work in very dusty enviornments where there is a very large chance of finding ancient artifacts, such as toys, tools, inventions, and even entire buildings or cities! The artifacts they find are their pay, so the more items found, the more money. But it is very hard to find these objects, and most archeologists are lucky to find one every week! The items are also used for reasearch on past cultures. For example, if a goblet was found in Greece, it would most likely be sent to greek mythology professors for research.       The tools of an archeologist are very simple.You have the pick and shovel, but did you know there are more than six others? The shovel is, obviously the most common tool found with archeologists. The pick is used where the shovel cannot pierce the ground. It is very heavy, and has two very sharp ends used for cracking rock. Then there is the whisk and dustpan. They may not be very big, but they are essential tools to archeologists. The whisk is used to clear dust from delicate objects, such as teacups or very old books.The duspan is used to gather up the dirt and see if it has special minerals inside. Now we come to the knife, another essential, but small, tool. The knife is used for getting most of the dirt off of artifacts so that the whisk can get the remainder, because a whisk is only a brush and can't get all of that dirt off. I could go on and on about the tools, because there are many out there, but I digress.       So, as you can see, the life of an archeologist is a very confusing and long one, but in most cases, a fun and challenging one.

Item_Response: Archeologist do lots of things. It's a dangerous job but has alot of excitement. They explore and study anything from a sercet fort to a Old Presidents house!           Archeologists use many tools while exploring and there are quite interesting. They use picks and shovels to dig into the Earth. The whisk and dust pan is used for brushing off artifacts to see more detailing in the object. Also they use knifes for scrapping dirt around artifacts not for cutting our dinner like we do. Wheelbarrows are used to get dirt away from where there are studying. The skim shovel is used to scoop a small layer of soil. A trowel is used to cut the view the different layers of soil.           Archeologists have found the James Fort that we thought we had lost for years by the river sweeping it away but we were wrong! The fort was built in 1607 and was used for surviving attacks, there were even canons! We found artifacts such as pottery, tools, coins, and much more.          Also they have found George Washington's House when he was a kid. They started digging on Ferry Farm in 2003 and it took over 1 year! What do you think they found at his old house? The diggers found burnt pottery. They knew this house was George's because his house burned down in a fire. Also because they found pipes and George was known to smoke them.          It's amazing what archeologists can do! Do you want to be one when you grow up? They make a big difference on Earth and without them we wouldn't know what we know today.

Item_Response: Who are Archeologists?         Archeologists are very interesting and important people. You might have some questions though such as, 'Who are archeologists?' or 'What do they do?' Well, archeologists are people who study artifacts or objects from the past or dig up mysterious or well known artifacts from the past. They are important because, they help us discover past artifacts such as, James Fort or George Washington's clay pipes.                                                                         Discovering James Fort        James Fort was built in 1607 when settlers wanted to start a new life. In 1994, a group of archeologists studied the past started the Jamestown Rediscovery Archaeological project. The project mission was to discover the secrets of the James Fort. But, beforethat, the first items were found in 1861. Archeologists found armor and weapons. Then, 100 years later, a group found the exact location where the fort began. The National Park Service studied for five years to discover how the land was used. They used computer mapping to make an image for that certain area. Then, they finally found James Fort! First, they found marking on the ground. The marks displayed where the fort's walls used to be. Then, they found stone ledges built over the river which, were designed to hold cannons. Also, archologists found 11 cellars, lots of burial sights, and 10 buildings! For archeoloists this was a fantastic discovery and a great acheivement that will be remembered by the forever!                                                                                        Tools     Archeologists use many different tools for all of their hard work. Most, if not all, of the tools were used for digging as you can probably imagine. One of the tools they use is a shovel. A shovel is used to dig up the dirt. Another one of the tools they use is a pick or pickaxe. A pickaxe's job is very similar to a shovel even, though they look different. A pickaxe is used to dig into the Earth. Unlike, the shovel it is used to dig stone and harder subtances than the shovel. Now, let's talk about the whisk and the dustpan. You probably used these before in your homes. A whisk is used to sweep up dirt into the dustpan. You can probably picturing yourself using this tool at home. Now, lets move on to the knife. Another tool you probably use in your everyday life. But, for archeologists it is used differently. A knife is used for carefully used for digging and to scrape dirt from the artifacts. There are more tools but, those are some main ones                          Anyway, that's all I have to share. Archeologists are very interesting people and will never be forgotten and are important in history.

Item_Response: How much do you know about archeologists? Do you know the tools they use? What about different historical facts they've discovered? Soon you will be an expert on all of these topics and more.   First you need to know the tools they used. These are some tools they use:         Pick and Shovel Whisk and Dustpan Knife Wheelbarrow Skim Shovel Trowel   These are used for scraping away layers, digging shallow and deep digs, and transporting and clearing materials such as dirt. When archeologists search for hidden mysteries buried beneath the ground, they can't just jump right in, they have to check all their equipment and determine which tool is best for the work their doing. If they were looking for small delicate artifacts right beneath the surface they night use a knife or a skim shovel and then a whisk to dust treasures off. If they were looking for the base of a building buried deep in the ground, they would probably use a pick and shovel and then a wheelbarrow to wheel away dirt.   If it weren't for groups like The National Park Service or Ferry Farm we wouldn't know very much about America's history. Ferry Farm discovered George Washington's life before he became president. It took a year just to find the stone base of his house. The National Park Service conducted a five-year investigation of James Fort. It's hard to believe, but this group finds approximately 1 million artifacts each year! They've found tools, coins, metal toys for children, pottery, etc.   Now you know all about the job of an archeologist. Could you even imagine how much effort each person puts in each day. It's hard work being an archeologist!

Item_Response: Finding Fort James       In 1994 a group of people were interested in studying the past of Jamestown  and they called it the Rediscovery Archaeological Project. This project was designed for discovering the past and secrets of James Fort in Jamestown, Virginia . For 200 years some people thought it was washed away by a river.        James Fort was built in 1607 and it was built next to a river so it was easier to dock for ships. In researches the fort was located somewhere else. The new spot was probably gave people protection from enemy ships.       The first objects were found in 1861. Archeologists study objects from the past,like uncovered armor and weapons.They also discover floors and buildings. Over 100 years later a group of people put an effort to find where the fort was first built.       The National Park Service led a 5-year study in the area to figure out what the land was really used for. They knew that this would help them decide where Fort James really was. the people used the computer to use a mapping software to make an image of the area.       That is when they finally found Fort James! the first thing they did was set marks on the ground. The marks would show where the corners of the fort wall where. from all the stories they read they new that the fort was shaped like a triangle. They made maps and they found out that the fort stretched all the way to the river. They soon realized that stone ledges were built for cannons and to hold cannons for enemies ships or troops.The archeologists also found dozens of burial sites and cellars and ten buildings within the border of the fort.       Today the group finds 1 million objects each year. The things they find includes pottery,tools,coins and even metal toys for children. in the 1600s, people used to throw their trash down in an unused well or a pit. While digging they found trash that settlers threw away. we know how the powhattan tribe attacked and how they fought back. we also know how they survived with little food.       It is exciting to discover objects from the past. It helps us know how the past was.

Item_Response: An archeologist's work is simple, but it's not easy. Archeologists go onto excavations to find abandoned places and find artifacts that are probably worth more than a mansion. They explore the world looking for places to excavate. They find many things, and the job pays well, (probably).          Archeologists do many fun things and use many different tools. They use these tools during an excavation, which is the hard part of being an archeologist. You dig in the ground carefully and once you find what you're looking for, you carefully dig around it. If it's a buried artifact, you carefully grab it with gloved hands and bring it up.         If it's a building that has been covered in dirt, then dig around until you've found the door, because most buildings have doors. Once you're in, you look around the building for artifacts, if there are any in the building.       Like I said, an archeologist's work is simple, but not easy.

Item_Response: Archeologists                  What is an archeologist? It's a person who carefully digs up artifacts. Archeologists have a very difficult job. They have to very carefully and gently clean and find artifacts. They have to have gentile hands when they work and a lot of patents. It may take them up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-foot section! That's along time!           Archeologists can find many things. Some archeologist found the remains of Fort James in Jamestown, Virginia. Others found some things from George Washington's childhood, from his childhood home. Lots of things have been found by archeologists. Lots more are waiting to be found.                   The place where archeologists do the digging, is called a dig. Archeologists have many tools:       Pick and Shovel- Lots of digs start with these tools. They are used to dig into the earth, to get closer to the artifacts. Whisk and Dustpan- This is used to brush dirt off the artifacts and clear away the dirt from the excavation site. Knife- This tool is used for careful digging, and to scrape dirt from around the artifacts. Wheelbarrow- these are used to move items from one place to another, or to carry dirt away from the excavation site. Skim Shovel- A shovel with a flat edge. This is used to carefully remove a thin layer of soil with each scoop. Trowel- This is probably the most common tool in archeology. It is used to scrape and cut to view the different layers of soil.   Archeologists have though jobs, long ones too. I think it might be cool to be an archeologist, but maybe not. It would be cool to find something. But I don't think I have the patents. I like reading about them. I hope you do too.

Item_Response: I am going to tell u about how archeologist dig up stuff from the past.the process of digging at the Ferry Farm is a careful one.Each year, many teams will work on the site. There can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that people will know what it looked like  before people stared digging. Another team focuses on the actual digging , and the  place the team does the digging is called a dig. Those archeologist  start their dig with what are called skim shovels. These are to small ,flat and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil, at a time. That soil is than placed in a box  with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets  the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called troweling is when archeologist use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt. It can take up to two weeks to dig a 25-square-feet section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but it's worth it.                                                                                                                                                             I'm going to tell you what it means.The discovery of Washington home is important for many reasons. first, it gives the citizens of the United states a better understanding of who George Washington was before he became famous. We also begin to know why he made the decision he did. Another thing it does is help historians learn about the type of life Colonial Americans lived. All of these things are key parts of our past as many lived Americans. Digging around in the dirt can give you more than just dusty jeans. The folks at Ferry Farm are bringing to life the country's first president in ways we have never seen.           I'm going to tell you about getting involved Ferry Farm offers many opportunities for kids to get involved. The George Washington society runs summer workshops with both classrooms and outdoor activities.  Kids can explore the site, experience colonial life, and became junior archeologist. Kids can sign can sign up for classes, games, and crafts. There is even an interacitve website! It challenges kids to solve puzzles about the work being done at Ferry Farm.

Item_Response: ONCE THERE WAS A MAN NAME GEORGE WASHINTON .HE WAS THE FRIST PRESENDINT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA. THERE ARE PEOPLE THAT ARE LOOKING FOR SOMETHING FROM HIS CHILD HOOD AS A KID. THE FRIST OBJECTS WERE FOUND IN 1861. ARCHOELOGISTS THE NAME FOR SCIENTISTS WHO STUDY OBJECTS FROM THE PAST, UNCOVERED AMOR AND WEAPONS. THEY ALSO DISCOVERED THE FLOORS OF BUILDINGS. OVER 100 YEARS LATER A GROUP OF EFFORT TO FIND EXACLY SPOT WHERE THERE HOME WAS. NO ONE KNEW EXACLY WHERE THE WASHINTON'S HOME WAS LOCATED SINCE THE ACTUAL BUILDING WAS LONG  GONE. HOWEVER, ARCEOLOGISTS BELIEVE THAT THE STONE BASE  UNDER THE HOUSE WAS STILL THERE. THEY STARTED DIGGING IN 2003. IT TOOK OVER A YEAR , BUT THEY FINALLY FOUND IT. THE FRIST BUILDINGS THEY FOUND  WERE THE KITCHEN, SLAVE QUARTERS, AND STORAGE HOUSES.THEY FOUND THE MAIN FARMHOUSE A FEW YEARS LATER. AT LEAST FOUR OTHER HOUSE HAVE BEEN BUILT ON FERRY FARM LAND, SO THE DIGGERS NEEDED TO FIND PROOF THAT ThIS WASWASHTINTONS FARM HOUSE.RECORDS SHOW THAT THE WASHINTONS HAD A FIRE IN THEIR HOUSE. THE DIGGERS  FOUND PIECES OF BURNT POTTERY.THIS SUGGESTS A FIRE  OCCURRED THERE.THEY ALSO FOUND PART OF A CLAY PIPE.WE KNOW THAT WASHINTON SMOKED CLAY PIPES, SO THIS DISCOVERY GIVES MORE PROOF IT IS THE RIGHT HOUSE. PEOPLE HAVE  LIVED ON THE FERRY FARM FOR OVER 12,000 YEARS.IT'S LOCATION MAKES IT A PERFECT PLACE TO BUILD A HOME. THEREFORE, IT'S NOT  SURPRISING THAT GEORGEGE WASHINTON'S FARTHER,AUGUSTINE WASHINTON, MOVED HIS FAMILY THERE. GEORGE WAS JUST SIX YEARS OLD AT THE TIME. THIS DISCOVERY OF WASHINTON'S HOME IS IMPORTANT FOR MANY REASONS. FRIST,IT GIVES THE CITIZENS OF THE UNITED STATES A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF WHO GOERGE WASHINTON WAS BEFORE HE BECAME FAMOUS. WE ALSO BEGIN TO KNOW WHY HE MADE THE DECISIONS HE DID. ANOTHER THING IT DOSE IS HELP HISTOIANS LEARN ABOUT THE TYPE OF LIFE COLONIAL AMERICANS LIVED. ALL OF  THESE THINGS  ARE KEY PARTS OF OUR PAST AS AMERICANS. FERRY FARM  OFFERS MANY OPPORTUNITIES FOR KIDS TO GET INVOLED. THE GOERGE WASHINTON SOCITEY RUNS SUMMER WORK SHOPS  WITH BOTH CLASSROOM AND OUTDOOR ACTIVITES. KIDS CAN EXPLORE THE SIT, EXPERIENCE COLONIAL LIFE, AND BECOME JUNIOR ARCHEOLOGISTS. KIDS CAN SIGN UP FOR CLASSES, GAMES, AND CRAFTS. THERE IS EVEN AN INTERACTIVE WEBSITE! IT CHALLENGES KIDS TO SOVE PUZZULES ABOUT THE WORK BEING DONE AT FERRY FARM.

Finding Fort James                                      In the early 90's a group of people got interested in studying the past started the Jamestown R.A.P. Item_Response: Archeologists           What are archeologists? They are scientists that discover and study things from the past. Some tools they use to help them find the artifacts they need are: picks, shovels, whisks, dustpans, knives, wheelbarrows, skim shovels and trowels.Archeologists use these tools to find artifacts that help people understand the mysteries of the past.   Tools And How They Use Them        Picks and shovels are basic tools that archeologists use to dig up dirt.   A whisk and dustpan brushes off dirt from the artifacts that the archeologists find.   Knives are used to scrape dirt from the edges of the artifacts.   Wheelbarrows are used to carry artifacts and dirt away from the place they are searching.   Skim shovels have a thin edge that helps the archeologists remove a thin layer of soil each time they scoop.   Trowels are used to scrape and cut to see different layers of soil.   What Archeologists Do While Working         Archeologists have to be patient, so they won't be frustrated. If you are frustrated while working you won't get a lot of work done. They don't just zoom through their work, they take their time and handle the artifacts carefully. They use the tools I had listed earlier to uncover the artifacts they find. Once they find all the things they need they might take the artifacts to a museum,so that we can better understand the mysteries of the past.

Item_Response: A job of an archeologist is someone who discovers interesting artifacts from the past times. Archeologist can find interesting things of people that have vanished that might have did something great to change the world. An archeologist gets to learn about the history of someone if they didn't now anything about them. Some archeologist starts their dig with what are called skim shovels. These shovels are so small, flat and sharp that they can remove thin layers of soil, one at a time.               That soil is then placed in a box with a half-inch screen at the bottom. This lets the dirt fall out while the artifacts stay in. The diggers also use a process called a troweling. Troweling is when archeologist use small shovels, paintbrushes and wooden picks to remove dirt from the artifacts that are found. It can take up two weeks to dig a 25-square foot section! Another team spends days in the lab studying the objects that are found. The whole process is slow and tiresome, but worth it.            All the tools that are used by archeologist are the pick and shovel-most digs start with these two tools. Used to dig into the earth, close to the artifacts. Whisk and Dustpan- used to brush dirt off the artifcats and clear away dirt from the excavation site.                      There can be up to 35 people on a team! The first team maps the area using 3D computers that can track what is underground. The information is recorded so that the people will know what it looked like before people started digging. I think the job of an archeologist would be cool because you get to learn about the past history of many wonderful people.

Archeologists dig to find all things like that.       Archeologists use tools such as picks, shovels, Trowels, wheelbarrows, and knives. Digging for artifacts is very long process and you need to have enough strength to endure a lot of digging, as well as heat and sweat.       After artifacts are found the possessing team examines, cleans, and researches all the found artifacts and they either get thrown away or gets put in a museum.

Item_Response: The Job as an Archeologist                                                               By Braidyn Ruetten                             The job as an archeologist would be an interesting job, for sure. That is because there are many good and bad things about the job. You may call these pros and cons. In this report I will tell you about the job. After you read this you decide if you want to be an archeologist.                     In the Job of an archeologist you will learn about history by digging up, studying, and graphing famous places in history. now, you won't be doing all of this at once. The archeologist are broken up into teams. There can be up to thirty-five people on a team! The first team graphs and maps the area on three dimensional computers. How cool is that! The second team works on the actual digging. They start their digging with a tool called skim shovels. Skim shovels are flat, small, and sharp. Troweling is another process. Troweling is when archeologist use small shovels, paint brushes, and wooden picks to remove dirt from artifacts. When you are digging it can take up to two weeks to dig a twenty-five square-foot section! The other team spends days in the lab studying the artifacts. It takes a long time to figure out the story and reason for the artifact, but the outcome is huge!                          In this paragraph I will tell you the good things about the job of an archeologist. One good thing about the job is that you would uncover, or dig up, pieces of history. When you uncover pieces of history it helps many people, including average Americans not just archeologist. When you help people you help them in these ways: You help American citizens a better understanding of the situation. It helps People understand why things are the way they are. The last reason is it helps historians learn how life was at the time. Another reason an archeologist is a good job to have is you could dig up one of a kind items like a cavemen spear so it could be a good paying job. A good thing about the job as an  archeologist is you could make new friends at the digging site. Those are all the good things about being a archeologist.                      Some bad things about the job of an archeologist is you probably not be around your family a lot unless they work with you. Another bad thing about the job is that you are working in the sun all day and you would get really hot and sweaty and you would probably get a lot of sun burns over the summer. You are working in mud all day if you are a digger so you would be filthy, so that is a bad thing about the job. Money would be a problem depending on the site and amount of things you find there so that could be good or bad.                         Now it's time for you to decide do you want to be an archeologist? I wouldn't do as a full time job but I would try it someday.

Item_Response: Digging up the Past                          Have you ever wondered how archeologists ever found out about the artifacts of the past? Well, you have come to the right place! In this article, you will learn all about the study of artifacts, otherwise known as archeology. If you want to learn more about this marvelous art, then read on!                      First of all, it helps us learn all of the facts that may not be seen in biographies. This was stated in the article titled Digging up George Washington's Past, 'Most of what we know of George Washington comes from his time as a soldier and president. Biographies don't have much information about his childhood. That's changing, however. Recent discoveries at Washington's childhood home have helped historians know more about Washington as a boy.' This shows how by archeology we can find out more about historical people, landmarks and place. Due to this compelling quote it should be easy for one to see how important archeology is.                      Also, there are six essential tools to learn about before becoming a world class architect: {from Tools Used by Archeologists}       Pick and Shovel: This is used to dig into the earth in order to get close to artifacts. Whisk and Dustpan: Together these are used to clear off dirt from artifacts and the excavation site. Knife: Used for careful digging. Wheelbarrow: To move items or carry away dirt. Skim Shovel: To remove a thin layer of soil. Trowel: To scrape and cut layers of soil.                       Last but not least, how do you practice the art of archeology. Well there are various methods but we will only cover there most basic ones today. There are three teams of people as large as 35 people. One team maps the area using 3 dimensional  computers to track the underground. Another team does the 'real digging'. The last team studies the artifacts that are found. Working together is very important in archeology.                          In my opinion, archeology must be fun and I would love to be an archeologist. All in all, archeology is a very important study. Maybe in the generations  of the generations of the future their will be technology to scan for artifacts and to analyze them. Who knows?                       Bibliography:   Source 2-   Digging up George Washington's Past   Digging up the Past   Source 3-   Tools Used by Archeologists

Item_Response: Archeologist             The job of an archeologist is to dig up the things from the past and study them. The things that they dig up is called artifacts. Artifacts can help us know about the people of the past. We could know how they lived, how they worked what they used to live, and etc.               Archeologists work in groups. Some study the artifacts, while others do the digging. Before the digging,there is a group with 3D computers that that track what is underground. People work in teams. there could be more than 35 people on a team . the digging site is called a dig. People dig out dirt to get the artifacts. Archeologists need patience. Digging could take month or even years. It can take two weeks to dig 25 square feet of dirt. Digs begin with pick and shovel, which is also the most common tools used by acheologists. Sometimes, you won't find anything at the dig, but other times, you will find artifacts. Some artifacts are very precious. It is worth the effort of digging for a very long time.                Many kinds of tools are used by archeologists. Pick and shovels are used to dig into the dirt to find artifacts. Whisk and dustpan are used to cean dust off artifacts. A knife is used to scrape the dirt around the artifact. Wheelbarrow is used to carry dirt and artifacts. Skim shovel is used to remove thing layers of dirt. A  Trowel is used to scape and cut to view different layers of dirt. It is one of the most common tools for archeology.                 Archeologist help us to study the past. We can know about how they lived, how they worked, and the things they used. Being an archeologist is a fun job.
